flavor_text_14: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

flavor_text_18: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokemon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.

name: golduck
flavor_text_0: Golduck is the fastest swimmer among all Pokemon. It swims effortlessly, even in a rough, stormy sea. It sometimes rescues people from wrecked ships floundering in high seas.
flavor_text_1: The flippers of its well-developed limbs give it shocking speed. It is the best swimmer among Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: A professional swimmer, it can continue swimming for two days straight by waving its long tail skillfully.
flavor_text_3: A GOLDUCK is an adept swimmer. It sometimes joins competitive swimmers in training. It uses psychic powers when its forehead shimmers with light.
flavor_text_4: GOLDUCK is the fastest swimmer among all POKeMON. It swims effortlessly, even in a rough, stormy sea. It sometimes rescues people from wrecked ships floundering in high seas.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.
flavor_text_6: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use tele kinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.
flavor_text_7: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its fore head somehow be gins to glow.
flavor_text_8: Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.
flavor_text_9: It swims grace fully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.
flavor_text_10: It swims along the banks of lakes and catches fish Pokemon. It takes them to the shore and quietly eats them up.
flavor_text_11: Old tales tell of Golduck punishing those that defiled its river. The guilty were dragged into the water and taken away.
flavor_text_12: Its slim and long limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swim ming gracefully in lakes.
flavor_text_13: Even fast-swimming fish Pokemon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.
flavor_text_14: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of GOLDUCK give it frightening speed. This POKeMON is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.
flavor_text_15: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.
flavor_text_16: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.
flavor_text_17: Often seen swim ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.
flavor_text_18: Often seen swimming elegantly by lakeshores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster Kappa.
flavor_text_19: This Pokemon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.
flavor_text_20: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.
flavor_text_21: It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who possess one, so it was over-hunted in the past.
flavor_text_22: Its body is strong, and it has webbing on its hands and feet. Golduck can swim easily through rough seas, clawing its way through the high waves.
flavor_text_23: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.
flavor_text_24: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokemon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.
flavor_text_25: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use telekinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.

name: mankey
flavor_text_0: It is extremely ill-tempered. Groups of them will attack any handy target for no reason.
flavor_text_1: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.
flavor_text_2: It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages, and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.
flavor_text_3: The smallest of things could cause it to lose its temper. Because it doesn't hold in its stress, this Pokemon can live a long time.
flavor_text_4: It's unsafe to approach if it gets violently enraged for no reason and can't distinguish friends from foes.
flavor_text_5: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.
flavor_text_6: An agile POKeMON that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.
flavor_text_7: When it starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it's a sure sign of anger. However, since this happens instantly, there is no time to flee.
flavor_text_8: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.
flavor_text_9: It's unsafe to ap proach if it gets violently enraged for no reason and can't distinguish friends from foes.
flavor_text_10: If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.
flavor_text_11: When Mankey starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it's a sure sign that it is becoming angry. However, because it goes into a towering rage almost instantly, it is impossible for anyone to flee its wrath.
flavor_text_12: When MANKEY starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it's a sure sign that it is becoming angry. However, because it goes into a towering rage almost instantly, it is impossible for anyone to flee its wrath.
flavor_text_13: Light and agile on its feet, and ferocious in temperament. When angered, it flies into an uncontrollable frenzy.
flavor_text_14: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away  the next instant.
flavor_text_15: An agile Pokemon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.
flavor_text_16: Its raging tires it out and causes it to fall asleep, but the anger resonating in its dreams causes it to wake up--which infuriates it all over again.

name: primeape
flavor_text_0: The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokemon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.
flavor_text_1: It will beat up anyone who makes it mad, even if it has to chase them until the end of the world.
flavor_text_2: When it becomes furious, its blood circulation becomes more robust, and its muscles are made stronger. But it also becomes much less intelligent.
flavor_text_3: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poke Ball.
flavor_text_4: If approached while asleep, it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.
flavor_text_5: When PRIMEAPE becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.
flavor_text_6: When Primeape becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.
flavor_text_7: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.
flavor_text_8: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.
flavor_text_9: It will never forgive opponents who have angered it. Even after it has beaten them down until they can't move, it never ever forgives.
flavor_text_10: It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.
flavor_text_11: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.
flavor_text_12: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.
flavor_text_13: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.
flavor_text_14: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it catches up.

name: growlithe
flavor_text_0: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
flavor_text_1: GROWLITHE has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this POKeMON won't forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.
flavor_text_2: It has lived alongside humans since ages ago. Its bones have been found in excavations of ruins from the Stone Age.
flavor_text_3: While it's quite friendly toward humans once it's grown used to them, in the wild it must be quite fierce to defend its territory from Rockruff.
flavor_text_4: A POKeMON with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.
flavor_text_5: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.
flavor_text_6: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this Pokemon won't forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.
flavor_text_7: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.
flavor_text_8: It has a brave and trustworthy na ture. It fear lessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
flavor_text_9: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.
flavor_text_10: Its superb sense of smell ensures that this POKeMON won't forget any scent, no matter what. It uses its sense of smell to detect the emotions of others.
flavor_text_11: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.
flavor_text_12: A Pokemon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.
flavor_text_13: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any oppo nent to protect its own trainer from harm.
flavor_text_14: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
flavor_text_15: A Pokemon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.
flavor_text_16: It looks cute, but when you approach another Trainer's Growlithe, it will bark at you and bite.
flavor_text_17: It controls a big territory. If it detects an unknown smell, it roars loudly to force out the intruder.
flavor_text_18: It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.
flavor_text_19: It is very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

name: arcanine
flavor_text_0: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.
flavor_text_1: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were attracted to its movement as it ran through prairies.
flavor_text_2: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokemon's body is its source of power.
flavor_text_3: This legendary Chinese Pokemon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.
flavor_text_4: A Pokemon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_5: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.
flavor_text_6: Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.
flavor_text_7: Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokemon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.
flavor_text_8: A legendary POKe MON in China. Many people are charmed by its grace and beauty while running.
flavor_text_9: The fire burning inside its body serves as the energy to fuel it as it runs great distances. It appears in many legends.
flavor_text_10: A POKeMON that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_11: There are so many old tales about them that they're called legendary Pokemon, but there are way more of them around than you'd expect.
flavor_text_12: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.
flavor_text_13: This fleet-footed POKeMON is said to run over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within its body is its source of power.
flavor_text_14: This legendary Chinese POKEMON is considered magnif icent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.
flavor_text_15: A POKeMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_16: A legendary Pokemon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.
flavor_text_17: A POKeMON that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.
flavor_text_18: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
flavor_text_19: ARCANINE is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this POKeMON's body is its source of power.

name: poliwag
flavor_text_0: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokemon's innards showing through the skin.
flavor_text_1: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It looks clearer after it eats.
flavor_text_2: It is possible to see this POKeMON's spiral innards right through its thin skin. However, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.
flavor_text_3: The swirl on its belly is its internal organs showing through. If the swirl is tinged white, that means it's affected by some disease.
flavor_text_4: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.
flavor_text_5: Because it is inept at walking on its newly grown legs, it always  swims around in water.
flavor_text_6: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.
flavor_text_7: Because it is in ept at walking on its newly grown legs, it always  swims around in water.
flavor_text_8: Its newly grown legs prevent it from walking well. It appears to prefer swimming over walking.
flavor_text_9: It's still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokemon to walk every day.

flavor_text_11: Despite the danger, it wants to come up on land. So it does its best to waddle along, but when an enemy finds it, it rushes back to the water.

flavor_text_13: Poliwag has a very thin skin. It is possible to see the Pokemon's spiral innards right through the skin. Despite its thinness, however, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.
flavor_text_14: The direction of the swirl on their stomachs differs depending on where they live. Poliwag aficionados can tell them apart at a glance.
flavor_text_15: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokemon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.
flavor_text_16: The direction of its belly spiral differs by area. The equator is thought to have an effect on this.
flavor_text_17: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

name: poliwhirl
flavor_text_0: Its health suffers when its skin dries out, so be sure to moisturize it diligently.
flavor_text_1: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon's sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies' grasp and escape.
flavor_text_3: The swirl on its belly subtly un dulates. Staring at it may gradual ly cause drowsi ness.

flavor_text_5: The swirl on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.
flavor_text_6: Under attack, it uses its belly  spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.
flavor_text_7: Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.
flavor_text_8: Though it is skilled at walk ing, it prefers to live underwater where there is less danger.
flavor_text_9: The surface of Poliwhirl's body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.
flavor_text_10: Although it has become capable of living on land, it spends its time in the water, where its prey, fish Pokemon, are plentiful.
flavor_text_11: Although it can live on land, it prefers to stay in the water, where it has fewer natural enemies.
flavor_text_12: It can live in or out of water. When out of water, it constantly sweats to keep its body slimy.
flavor_text_13: It marches over the land in search of bug Pokemon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it's safe.
flavor_text_14: The surface of POLIWHIRL's body is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.
flavor_text_15: Its body surface is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.
flavor_text_16: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.
flavor_text_17: The skin on most of its body is moist. However, the skin on its belly spiral feels smooth.
flavor_text_18: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

name: poliwrath
flavor_text_0: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
flavor_text_1: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.
flavor_text_2: The muscles it has developed through swimming are thick and powerful. When it lands a square punch, it can turn huge boulders to dust.
flavor_text_3: This strong and skilled swimmer is even capable of crossing the Pacific Ocean just by kicking.
flavor_text_4: Poliwrath's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokemon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.
flavor_text_5: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.
flavor_text_6: POLIWRATH's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this POKeMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
flavor_text_7: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.
flavor_text_8: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.
flavor_text_9: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.
flavor_text_10: Although an ener getic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its mus cles, it lives on dry land.
flavor_text_11: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This POKeMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
flavor_text_12: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake champion swimmers.
flavor_text_13: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.
flavor_text_14: It's quite a gifted swimmer, even among Water-type Pokemon, but it normally spends its time on land.
flavor_text_15: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.
flavor_text_16: Poliwrath in the Alola region are strong swimmers that use the breaststroke. Many children learn to swim by imitating Poliwrath.
flavor_text_17: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
flavor_text_18: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

name: abra
flavor_text_0: ABRA needs to sleep for eighteen hours a day. If it doesn't, this POKeMON loses its ability to use telekinetic powers. If it is attacked, ABRA escapes using TELEPORT while it is still sleeping.
flavor_text_1: Using its ability to read minds, it will sense impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.
flavor_text_2: If it decides to TELEPORT randomly, it creates the illusion that it has created copies of itself.
flavor_text_3: Abra sleeps for eighteen hours a day. However, it can sense the presence of foes even while it is sleeping. In such a situation, this Pokemon immediately teleports to safety.
flavor_text_4: It hypnotizes itself so that it can teleport away when it senses danger, even if it is asleep.
flavor_text_5: It senses impend ing attacks and TELEPORTS away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.
flavor_text_6: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.
flavor_text_7: Spends 18 hours of the day sleeping. Even while asleep, Abra can control its psychic powers--should danger approach, the Pokemon will simply teleport away.
flavor_text_8: A POKeMON that sleeps 18 hours a day. Observation revealed that it uses TELEPORT to change its location once every hour.
flavor_text_9: It can teleport itself to safety while it's asleep, but when it wakes, it doesn't know where it is, so it panics.
flavor_text_10: ABRA sleeps for eighteen hours a day. However, it can sense the presence of foes even while it is sleeping. In such a situation, this POKeMON immediately teleports to safety.
flavor_text_11: It senses impending attacks and teleports away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.
flavor_text_12: It uses various psychic powers even while it's sleeping, so you can't tell whether or not it's awake.
flavor_text_13: It sleeps 18 hours a day. Even while sleeping, it will teleport itself to treetops and pick and eat berries there.
flavor_text_14: This Pokemon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra's dreams affect the powers that the Pokemon wields.
flavor_text_15: If it decides to teleport randomly, it evokes the illusion that it has created copies of itself.
flavor_text_16: Even while asleep, it maintains a telepathic radar. It teleports when it is threatened.
flavor_text_17: Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.
flavor_text_18: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.
flavor_text_19: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. It uses a variety of extrasensory powers even while asleep.
flavor_text_20: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. Even when awake, it teleports itself while remaining seated.
flavor_text_21: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.
flavor_text_22: It can read others' minds and will teleport away when danger approaches. You must clear your mind if you want to catch it.
flavor_text_23: Abra needs to sleep for eighteen hours a day. If it doesn't, this Pokemon loses its ability to use telekinetic powers. If it is attacked, Abra escapes using Teleport while it is still sleeping.

name: kadabra
flavor_text_0: KADABRA emits a peculiar alpha wave if it develops a headache. Only those people with a particularly strong psyche can hope to become a TRAINER of this POKeMON.
flavor_text_1: KADABRA holds a silver spoon in its hand. The spoon is used to amplify the alpha waves in its brain. Without the spoon, the POKeMON is said to be limited to half the usual amount of its telekinetic powers.
flavor_text_2: If it uses its abilities, it emits special alpha waves that cause machines to malfunction.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon's telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.
flavor_text_4: Many odd things happen if this POKeMON is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backwards.
flavor_text_5: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.
flavor_text_6: When it uses its psychic power, it emits strong alpha waves that can ruin precision devices.
flavor_text_7: If one is nearby, an eerie shadow appears on TV screens. Seeing the shadow is said to bring bad luck.
flavor_text_8: Kadabra holds a silver spoon in its hand. The spoon is used to amplify the alpha waves in its brain. Without the spoon, the Pokemon is said to be limited to half the usual amount of its telekinetic powers.
flavor_text_9: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close.
flavor_text_10: A theory exists that this Pokemon was a young boy who couldn't control his psychic powers and ended up transformed into this Pokemon.
flavor_text_11: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.
flavor_text_12: Many odd things happen if this Pokemon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.
flavor_text_13: It possesses strong spiritual power. The more danger it faces, the stronger its psychic power.
flavor_text_14: Kadabra's presence infests televisions and monitors with creepy shadows that bring bad luck.
flavor_text_15: When it closes its eyes, twice as many alpha parti cles come out of the surface of its body.
flavor_text_16: When it uses its psychic power, it emits strong ha waves that can ruin precision devices.
flavor_text_17: It stares at a silver spoon to amplify its psychic powers before it lets loose. Apparently, gold spoons are no good.
flavor_text_18: It possesses strong mental capabilities, but its psychic powers are halved when it's not holding a silver spoon.
flavor_text_19: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.
flavor_text_20: It is rumored that a boy with psychic abilities suddenly transformed into KADABRA while he was assisting research into extrasensory powers.
flavor_text_21: Kadabra emits a peculiar alpha wave if it develops a headache. Only those people with a particularly strong psyche can hope to become a Trainer of this Pokemon.
flavor_text_22: It happened one morning - a boy with extrasensory powers awoke in bed transformed into KADABRA.
flavor_text_23: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: alakazam
flavor_text_0: ALAKAZAM's brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this POKeMON an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.
flavor_text_1: A POKeMON that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns-- that's why this POKeMON is smart.
flavor_text_2: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.
flavor_text_3: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
flavor_text_4: Its highly developed brain is on par with a supercomputer. It can use all forms of psychic abilities.
flavor_text_5: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
flavor_text_6: ALAKAZAM's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This POKeMON holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
flavor_text_7: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.
flavor_text_8: It has an IQ of 5000. It calcu lates many things in order to gain the edge in every battle.
flavor_text_9: It does not like physical attacks very  much. Instead, it freely uses extra sensory powers to defeat foes.
flavor_text_10: Alakazam wields potent psychic powers. It's said that this Pokemon used these powers to create the spoons it holds.

flavor_text_1: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

flavor_text_13: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can't harm it.
flavor_text_14: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.
flavor_text_15: It is said to live in volcanic craters on mountain peaks. Once a year, it sheds its hide and grows larger. The shed hide crumbles and returns to the soil.
flavor_text_16: Golem is known for rolling down from mountains. To prevent them from rolling into the homes of people downhill, grooves have been dug into the sides of mountains to serve as guideways for diverting this Pokemon's course.
flavor_text_17: Golem live up on mountains. If there is a large earthquake, these Pokemon will come rolling down off the mountains en masse to the foothills below.
flavor_text_18: Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.
flavor_text_19: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.
flavor_text_20: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without taking damage.
flavor_text_21: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it's exposed to air.

name: ponyta

flavor_text_1: A PONYTA is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. Its legs become stronger as it stumbles and falls while trying to keep up with its parent.
flavor_text_2: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.
flavor_text_3: Its hind legs, which have hard er-than-diamond hooves, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.
flavor_text_4: Its hind legs, which have hooves that are harder than diamond, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.
flavor_text_5: Training by jumping over grass that grows longer every day has made it a world-class jumper.
flavor_text_6: Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokemon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.
flavor_text_7: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.
flavor_text_8: If you've been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.
flavor_text_9: PONYTA is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This POKeMON becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.
flavor_text_10: Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.
flavor_text_11: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.
flavor_text_12: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.
flavor_text_13: It is a weak runner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.
flavor_text_14: Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.
flavor_text_15: These Pokemon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.
flavor_text_16: Its hooves are ten times harder than diamond. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.
flavor_text_17: It is a weak run ner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.

name: rapidash
flavor_text_0: RAPIDASH usually can be seen casually cantering in the fields and plains. However, when this POKeMON turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.
flavor_text_1: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.
flavor_text_2: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.
flavor_text_3: Rapidash usually can be seen casually cantering in the fields and plains. However, when this Pokemon turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.
flavor_text_4: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just 10 steps.
flavor_text_5: Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.
flavor_text_6: It just loves to gallop. The faster it goes, the long er the swaying flames of its mane will become.
flavor_text_7: At full gallop, its four hooves barely touch the ground because it moves so incredi bly fast.
flavor_text_8: At full gallop, its four hooves barely touch the ground because it moves so incredibly fast.
flavor_text_9: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd's pace and direction of travel.
flavor_text_10: Very competitive, this POKeMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.
flavor_text_11: It has astounding acceleration. From a standstill, it can reach top speed within 10 steps.
flavor_text_12: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.
flavor_text_13: It can gallop at a top speed of 150 miles per hour. It can race as fast as a bullet train while ablaze.
flavor_text_14: It usually canters casually in the fields and plains. But once a RAPIDASH turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.
flavor_text_15: Very competitive, this Pokemon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.
flavor_text_16: Just loves to run. If it sees some thing faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.
flavor_text_17: This Pokemon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.
flavor_text_18: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just ten steps.

name: slowpoke
flavor_text_0: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.
flavor_text_1: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokemon often forgets what it's doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.
flavor_text_2: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.
flavor_text_3: There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.
flavor_text_4: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.
flavor_text_5: It is always so absent-minded that it won't react, even if its flavorful tail is bitten.
flavor_text_6: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.
flavor_text_7: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn't really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn't particularly bothered.
flavor_text_8: Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.
flavor_text_9: A sweet sap leaks from its tail's tip. Although not nutritious, the tail is pleasant to chew on.
flavor_text_10: SLOWPOKE uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this POKeMON often forgets what it's doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.
flavor_text_11: Alolan home cooking involves drying Slowpoke tails and then simmering them into a salty stew.
flavor_text_12: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won't even notice for a whole day.
flavor_text_13: Although their tails, which fall off naturally, can easily be found lying around, they're a precious ingredient for cooking.
flavor_text_14: When this Pokemon's tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokemon.
flavor_text_15: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokemon won't feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won't notice when its tail grows back, either.
flavor_text_16: It catches prey by dipping its tail in water at the side of a river. But it often forgets what it is doing and spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.

name: slowbro
flavor_text_0: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.
flavor_text_1: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to SHELLDER's seeping poison.
flavor_text_2: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the SHELLDER on its tail bites down.
flavor_text_3: Its tail has a SHELLDER firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.
flavor_text_4: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.
flavor_text_5: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
flavor_text_6: An attached Shellder won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
flavor_text_7: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokemon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.
flavor_text_8: When a SLOWPOKE went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a SHELLDER. That made it evolve into SLOWBRO.
flavor_text_9: An attached SHELLDER won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
flavor_text_10: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder's poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.
flavor_text_11: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
flavor_text_12: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.
flavor_text_13: Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.
flavor_text_14: The SHELLDER that latches onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's leftover scraps.
flavor_text_15: Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.
flavor_text_16: Lives lazily by the sea. If the SHELLDER on its tail comes off, it becomes a SLOWPOKE again.
flavor_text_17: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
flavor_text_18: SLOWBRO's tail has a SHELLDER firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes SLOWBRO to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
flavor_text_19: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary SLOWPOKE.
flavor_text_20: Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more sweetness from Slowbro's tail, has metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.
flavor_text_21: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordi nary SLOWPOKE.

name: magnemite
flavor_text_0: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.
flavor_text_1: The electricity emitted by the units on each side of its body cause it to become a strong magnet.
flavor_text_2: It is born with the ability to defy gravity. It floats in air on powerful electro magnetic waves.
flavor_text_3: It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.
flavor_text_4: The units at the sides of its body generate anti gravity energy to keep it aloft in the air.
flavor_text_5: It is attracted by electromagnetic waves. It may approach trainers if they are using their POKeGEAR.
flavor_text_6: It subsists on electricity. As Magnemite flies, it emits electromagnetic waves from the units on each side of its body.
flavor_text_7: The faster the units at its sides rotate, the greater the magnetic force they generate.

flavor_text_9: The units at its sides are extremely powerful magnets. They generate enough magnetism to draw in iron objects from over 300 feet away.
flavor_text_10: The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.
flavor_text_11: The units at the sides of its body generate antigravity energy to keep it aloft in the air.
flavor_text_12: Perhaps because electrical lines are often buried these days, the number of Magnemite attacks on power plants has increased.
flavor_text_13: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.
flavor_text_14: Magnemite floats in the air by emitting electromagnetic waves from the units at its sides. These waves block gravity. This Pokemon becomes incapable of flight if its internal electrical supply is depleted.
flavor_text_15: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges THUNDER WAVE and so on from the units at its sides.
flavor_text_16: It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it's eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.
flavor_text_17: At times, Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite, it'll start moving again.

flavor_text_20: It is attracted by electromagnetic waves. It may approach Trainers if they are using their Pokegear.
flavor_text_21: A bizarre Pokemon with but a single eye embedded in an iron sphere. I suspect this creature levitates due to the magnetism it emits from its arms, which resemble horseshoe-shaped magnets.
flavor_text_22: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.
flavor_text_23: MAGNEMITE floats in the air by emitting electromagnetic waves from the units at its sides. These waves block gravity. This POKeMON becomes incapable of flight if its internal electrical supply is depleted.
flavor_text_24: Magnemite attaches itself to power lines to feed on electricity. If your house has a power outage, check your circuit breakers. You may find a large number of this Pokemon clinging to the breaker box.
flavor_text_25: Uses antigravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

name: magneton
flavor_text_0: When rain clouds form, many Magneton gather in high places to wait for lightning to strike.
flavor_text_1: A linked cluster formed of several Magnemite. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.
flavor_text_2: MAGNETON emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to electronics and precision instruments. Because of this, it is said that some towns warn people to keep this POKeMON inside a POKe BALL.
flavor_text_3: A linked cluster formed of several MAGNEMITE. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.
flavor_text_4: When three Magnemite link together, their brains also become one. They do not become three times more intelligent.
flavor_text_5: The MAGNEMITE are united by a mag netism so power ful, it dries all moisture in its vicinities.
flavor_text_6: When many MAGNETON gather together, the resulting magnetic storm disrupts radio waves.
flavor_text_7: The MAGNEMITE are united by a magnetism so powerful, it dries all moisture in its vicinity.
flavor_text_8: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this Pokemon.
flavor_text_9: Delicate equipment can malfunction in areas inhabited by Magneton, which send out mysterious electrical signals.
flavor_text_10: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to electronics and precision instruments. Because of this, it is said that some towns warn people to keep this Pokemon inside a Poke Ball.
flavor_text_11: Many mysteriously appear when more sunspots dot the sun. They stop TV sets from displaying properly.
flavor_text_12: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.
flavor_text_13: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
flavor_text_14: This Pokemon is constantly putting out a powerful magnetic force. Most computers go haywire when a Magneton approaches.
flavor_text_15: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.
flavor_text_16: It is actually three MAGNEMITE linked by magnetism. A group can set off a magnetic storm.
flavor_text_17: Three MAGNEMITE are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.
flavor_text_18: This Pokemon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.
flavor_text_19: Formed by several MAGNEMITE linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
flavor_text_20: Three Magnemite gathered to evolve into this Pokemon. The source of much vexation on my part, as its powerful magnetism destroys my research equipment.
flavor_text_21: MAGNETON emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this POKeMON.
flavor_text_22: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the tem perature by 3.6F degrees within 3,300 feet.

flavor_text_24: It is actually three MAGNEMITE linked by magnetism. It generates powerful radio waves that raise temperatures by 3.6 degrees F within a 3,300-foot radius.

name: farfetchd
flavor_text_0: The plant stalk it holds is its weapon. The stalk is used like a sword to cut all sorts of things.
flavor_text_1: If it eats the plant stalk it carries as emergency rations, it runs off in search of a new stalk.
flavor_text_2: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.
flavor_text_3: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.
flavor_text_4: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
flavor_text_5: If anyone tries to disturb where the essential plant sticks grow, it uses its own stick to thwart them.
flavor_text_6: If anyone tries to disturb where the essential plant stalks grow, it uses its own stalk to thwart them.
flavor_text_7: It is always seen with a stick from a plant. Apparently, there are good sticks and bad sticks. This POKeMON occasionally fights with others over choice sticks.
flavor_text_8: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.
flavor_text_9: They live where reedy plants grow. Farfetch'd are rarely seen, so it's thought their numbers are decreasing.
flavor_text_10: In order to pre vent their extinction, more people have made an effort to breed these POKeMON.
flavor_text_11: FARFETCH'D is always seen with a stick from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good sticks and bad sticks. This POKeMON has been known to fight with others over sticks.
flavor_text_12: If it eats the plant stick it carries as emer gency rations, it runs off in search of a new stick.
flavor_text_13: The stalk this Pokemon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.
