flavor_text_15: Farfetch'd is always seen with a stalk from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good stalks and bad stalks. This Pokemon has been known to fight with others over stalks.

name: doduo
flavor_text_0: Its short wings make flying dif ficult. Instead, this POKeMON runs at high speed on developed legs.
flavor_text_1: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokemon runs at high speed on developed legs.
flavor_text_2: Doduo's two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.
flavor_text_3: Doduo's two heads contain completely identical brains. A scientific study reported that on rare occasions, there will be examples of this Pokemon possessing different sets of brains.
flavor_text_4: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.
flavor_text_5: DODUO's two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.
flavor_text_6: By alternately raising and lower ing its two heads, it balances itself to be more stable while running.
flavor_text_7: Even while eating or sleeping, one of the heads remains always vigilant for any sign of danger. When threatened, it flees at over 60 miles per hour.
flavor_text_8: A two-headed POKeMON that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.
flavor_text_9: It lives on a grassy plain where it can see a long way. If it sees an enemy, it runs away at 60 mph.
flavor_text_10: By alternately raising and lowering its two heads, it balances itself to be more stable while running.
flavor_text_11: It races through grassy plains with powerful strides, leaving footprints up to four inches deep.
flavor_text_12: DODUO's two heads contain completely identical brains. A scientific study reported that on rare occasions, there will be examples of this POKeMON possessing different sets of brains.
flavor_text_13: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
flavor_text_14: A two-headed Pokemon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

name: dodrio
flavor_text_0: Watch out if Dodrio's three heads are looking in three separate directions. It's a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don't go near this Pokemon if it's being wary--it may decide to peck you.
flavor_text_1: An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads--even for a second--will get pecked severely.
flavor_text_2: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head is said to stay awake.
flavor_text_3: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.
flavor_text_4: Apparently, the heads aren't the only parts of the body that DODRIO has three of. It has three sets of hearts and lungs as well, so it is capable of running long distances without rest.
flavor_text_5: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.
flavor_text_6: It collects data  and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and be come immobilized.
flavor_text_7: It collects data and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and fall into a state of immobility.
flavor_text_8: One of DODUO's 2 heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 MPH in prairies.
flavor_text_9: One of Doduo's two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.
flavor_text_10: A peculiar POKeMON species with three heads. It vigorously races across grassy plains even in arid seasons with little rainfall.
flavor_text_11: When DODUO evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.
flavor_text_12: Watch out if DODRIO's three heads are looking in three separate directions. It's a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don't go near this POKeMON if it's being wary - it may decide to peck you.
flavor_text_13: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.
flavor_text_14: If one of the heads gets to eat, the others will be satisfied, too, and they will stop squabbling.
flavor_text_15: Apparently, the heads aren't the only parts of the body that Dodrio has three of. It has three sets of hearts and lungs as well, so it is capable of running long distances without rest.

name: seel
flavor_text_0: SEEL hunt for prey in frigid, ice-covered seas. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.
flavor_text_1: Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.
flavor_text_2: The light blue fur that covers it keeps it protected against the cold. It loves iceberg- filled oceans.
flavor_text_3: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_4: Loves freezing cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid cli mate of around 14F degrees.
flavor_text_5: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_6: In daytime, it is often found asleep on the seabed in shallow waters. Its nostrils close while it swims.
flavor_text_7: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.
flavor_text_8: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_9: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick icebergs.
flavor_text_10: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.
flavor_text_11: A Pokemon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.
flavor_text_12: It has always been supposed that Seel live only in cold seas. Their having shown up in Alola is a mystery.
flavor_text_13: Although it can't walk well on land, it is a graceful swimmer. It espe cially loves being in frigid seas.
flavor_text_14: SEEL hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.
flavor_text_15: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.
flavor_text_16: Although it can't walk well on land, it is a graceful swimmer. It especially loves being in frigid seas.

name: dewgong
flavor_text_0: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.
flavor_text_1: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokemon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
flavor_text_2: DEWGONG loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this POKeMON sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
flavor_text_3: It loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this POKeMON sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.
flavor_text_4: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.
flavor_text_5: Its entire body is a snowy-white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.
flavor_text_6: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it's cold.
flavor_text_7: It swims through the ocean at a speed of eight knots, searching for Pokemon that will become its prey. It's especially fond of Wishiwashi.
flavor_text_8: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
flavor_text_9: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.
flavor_text_10: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.
flavor_text_11: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.
flavor_text_12: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.
flavor_text_13: It stores thermal energy in the body. It swims at a steady eight knots even in intensely cold waters.
flavor_text_14: It loves frigid seas with ice floes. It uses its long tail to change swimming direction quickly.

name: grimer
flavor_text_0: Sludge exposed to X rays from the moon transformed into GRIMER. It loves feeding on filthy things.
flavor_text_1: Made of hardened sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.
flavor_text_2: GRIMER emerged from the sludge that settled on a polluted seabed. This POKeMON loves anything filthy. It constantly leaks a horribly germ- infested fluid from all over its body.
flavor_text_3: Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
flavor_text_4: Wherever GRIMER has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.
flavor_text_5: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.
flavor_text_6: Grimer emerged from the sludge that settled on a polluted seabed. This Pokemon loves anything filthy. It constantly leaks a horribly germ-infested fluid from all over its body.
flavor_text_7: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.
flavor_text_8: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
flavor_text_9: As it moves, it loses bits of its body, from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.
flavor_text_10: Sludge exposed to X-rays from the moon transformed into Grimer. It loves feeding on filthy things.
flavor_text_11: Born from sludge, these Pokemon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.
flavor_text_12: GRIMER's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This POKeMON enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.
flavor_text_13: When two of these POKeMON's bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.
flavor_text_14: The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They're said to be on the verge of extinction.
flavor_text_15: It was born from sludge transformed by exposure to X-rays from the moon. When its internal load of germs decreases, it dies.
flavor_text_16: Born from polluted sludge in the sea, GRIMER's favorite food is anything filthy. They feed on wastewater pumped out from factories.
flavor_text_17: Grimer's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokemon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.
flavor_text_18: As it moves, it loses bits of its body from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.
flavor_text_19: It was born from sludge on the ocean floor. In a sterile environment, the germs within its body can't multiply, and it dies.
flavor_text_20: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokemon's numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

name: muk
flavor_text_0: As it moves, a very strong poison leaks from it, making the ground there barren for three years.
flavor_text_1: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they've long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, Muk are certain to gather.
flavor_text_3: From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokemon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
flavor_text_4: From MUK's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this POKeMON's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
flavor_text_5: Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.
flavor_text_6: They love to gath er in smelly areas where sludge ac cumulates, making the stench around them worse.
flavor_text_7: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that's a good thing.
flavor_text_8: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
flavor_text_9: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.
flavor_text_10: This POKeMON's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, MUK are certain to gather.
flavor_text_11: Its body is made of a powerful poi son. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.
flavor_text_12: It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.
flavor_text_13: It's so stinky! Muk's body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.
flavor_text_14: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration, it lost its sense of smell.
flavor_text_15: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.
flavor_text_16: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.
flavor_text_17: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates, making the stench around them worse.
flavor_text_18: After recent environmental improvements, this Pokemon is now hardly seen at all. People speculate that it may go extinct at some point.
flavor_text_19: It prefers warm and humid habitats. In the summertime, the toxic substances in its body intensify, making MUK reek like putrid kitchen garbage.

name: shellder
flavor_text_0: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.
flavor_text_1: At night, this POKeMON uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, SHELLDER closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.
flavor_text_2: At night, it burrows a hole in the seafloor with its broad tongue to make a place to sleep. While asleep, it closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.
flavor_text_3: Grains of sand trapped in its shells mix with its body fluids to form beautiful pearls.
flavor_text_4: The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon's tongue is always hanging out. It uses its tongue with great dexterity to dig up sand from the seabed in its search for food.
flavor_text_6: The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.
flavor_text_7: It swims facing backward by open ing and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.
flavor_text_8: Even when its shell is closed, its tongue still hangs out. If you give its tongue a good yank, the shock will cause Shellder to open its shell.
flavor_text_9: The sand that accumulates inside its shell eventually becomes a pearl. But the pearl gets in the way, so it spits it out and discards it.
flavor_text_10: At night, this Pokemon uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, Shellder closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.
flavor_text_11: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.
flavor_text_12: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
flavor_text_13: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.
flavor_text_14: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: cloyster
flavor_text_0: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.
flavor_text_1: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
flavor_text_2: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.
flavor_text_3: For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamond shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.
flavor_text_4: CLOYSTER is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This POKeMON shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.
flavor_text_5: For protection, it uses its harder- than-diamonds shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.
flavor_text_6: Its hard shell cannot be shattered--not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.
flavor_text_7: CLOYSTER that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.
flavor_text_8: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superi or strength.
flavor_text_9: It swims in the sea by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. The CLOYSTER shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.
flavor_text_10: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.
flavor_text_11: Excavation of the tombs of ancient hunting tribes has turned up many spears tipped with spikes that had fallen off this Pokemon's shell.
flavor_text_12: Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokemon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.
flavor_text_13: If areas of Cloyster's very hard shell get damaged, those areas swell, gradually growing into large sharp spikes.
flavor_text_14: Slowpoke tails are its favorite food. It has even been known to come up on land to look for Slowpoke from time to time.
flavor_text_15: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.
flavor_text_16: Even a missile can't break the spikes it uses to stab opponents. They're even hard er than its shell.

name: gastly
flavor_text_0: It wraps its op ponent in its gas- like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.
flavor_text_1: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape, as it appears to be made of a gas.
flavor_text_2: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.
flavor_text_3: It's said that gas emanating from a graveyard was possessed by the grievances of the deceased and thus became a Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.
flavor_text_5: When exposed to a strong wind, a GASTLY's gaseous body quickly dwindles away. They cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.
flavor_text_6: Gaseous and completely impalpable. Also highly dangerous-- inhaling part of its poisonous body will cause one to faint instantly.
flavor_text_7: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKeMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.
flavor_text_8: This Pokemon's body is 95% made up of gases, which are blown away by strong gusts of wind.
flavor_text_9: GASTLY is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this POKeMON cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.
flavor_text_10: Its thin body is made of gas. It can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.
flavor_text_11: With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.
flavor_text_12: A being that exists as a thin gas. It can topple an Indian elephant by enveloping the prey in two seconds.
flavor_text_13: Poisonous gas comprises 95% of its body. It's said that the remaining 5% is made up of the souls of those who died from the gas.
flavor_text_14: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape as it appears to be made of a gas.
flavor_text_15: Should a strange light be seen flickering in an abandoned building, Gastly is lurking there.
flavor_text_16: Although Gastly is barely visible, when it's near, a faint sweet smell lingers.
flavor_text_17: Gastly is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this Pokemon cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.
flavor_text_18: A Pokemon born from poison gases. It defeats even the largest foes by enveloping them in gas.

name: haunter
flavor_text_0: It strikes at humans from total darkness. Those licked by its cold tongue grow weaker with each passing day until they die.
flavor_text_1: Haunter is a dangerous Pokemon. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This Pokemon will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.
flavor_text_2: On moonless nights, Haunter searches for someone to curse, so it's best not to go out walking around.
flavor_text_3: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death even tually comes.
flavor_text_4: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, HAUNTER lurks, silently stalking its next victim.
flavor_text_5: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.
flavor_text_6: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.
flavor_text_7: This frightful, malevolent spirit can glide through walls, appearing wherever it likes. According to rumor, victims of a Haunter's lick will wither to death day by day.
flavor_text_8: It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal the victim's life force. It lurks in darkness for prey.
flavor_text_9: It fears the light and revels in the dark. It may be on the verge of extinction in cities that stay brightly lit at night.
flavor_text_10: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, HAUNTER is there.
flavor_text_11: If a HAUNTER beckons you while it is floating in darkness, don't approach it. This POKeMON will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.
flavor_text_12: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an other dimension.
flavor_text_13: By licking, it saps the victim's life. It causes shaking that won't stop until the victim's demise.
flavor_text_14: It can slip through any obstacle. It lurks inside walls to keep an eye on its foes.
flavor_text_15: It's dangerous to go outside alone on nights when you're feeling sad. Haunter will catch you, and you won't be able to go back home.
flavor_text_16: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
flavor_text_17: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.
flavor_text_18: It hides in the dark, planning to take the life of the next living thing that wanders close by.
flavor_text_19: HAUNTER is a dangerous POKeMON. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This POKeMON will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.

name: gengar
flavor_text_0: Lurking in the shadowy corners of rooms, it awaits chances to steal its prey's life force.
flavor_text_1: A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_2: A GENGAR is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_3: Under a full moon, this POKeMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.
flavor_text_4: It steals heat from its surround ings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_5: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
flavor_text_6: It hides in shadows. It is said that if Gengar is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_7: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_8: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be GENGAR's doing.
flavor_text_9: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_10: Even your home isn't safe. Gengar will lurk in whatever dark corner of a room it can find and wait for its chance to catch its prey.
flavor_text_11: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!
flavor_text_12: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.
flavor_text_13: It apparently wishes for a traveling companion. Since it was once human itself, it tries to create one by taking the lives of other humans.
flavor_text_14: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.
flavor_text_15: It steals heat from its surroundings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_16: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_17: Deep in the night, your shadow cast by a streetlight may suddenly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_18: It hides in shadows. It is said that if GENGAR is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees F.
flavor_text_19: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a GENGAR delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_20: Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.
flavor_text_21: You can hear tales told all over the world about how Gengar will pay a visit to children who are naughty.
flavor_text_22: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

name: onix
flavor_text_0: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by DIGLETTs.
flavor_text_1: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
flavor_text_2: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
flavor_text_3: It squirms through the ground using its long and rugged body. It always eats while burrowing.
flavor_text_4: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.
flavor_text_5: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.
flavor_text_6: When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.
flavor_text_7: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to black-colored diamonds.
flavor_text_8: This chain of immense stones resembles a giant serpent. Tremors shake the earth above as it burrows deep beneath the ground, feeding on boulders as it goes.
flavor_text_9: There is a magnet in its brain that prevents an ONIX from losing direction while tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes steadily rounder and smoother.
flavor_text_10: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its mas sive, rugged body.
flavor_text_11: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokemon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
flavor_text_12: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.
flavor_text_13: ONIX has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this POKeMON does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.
flavor_text_14: It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.
flavor_text_15: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.
flavor_text_16: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.
flavor_text_17: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: drowzee
flavor_text_0: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.
flavor_text_1: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.
flavor_text_2: It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it's ever eaten.
flavor_text_3: A Pokemon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.
flavor_text_4: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these Pokemon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
flavor_text_5: It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn't particularly like eating them.
flavor_text_6: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that a DROWZEE is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
flavor_text_7: Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating only bad dreams.
flavor_text_8: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it has eaten in the past.
flavor_text_9: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.
flavor_text_10: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.
flavor_text_11: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a DROWZEE has probably eaten it.
flavor_text_12: It can be spotted near recreational facilities, intending to eat the pleasant dreams of children who enjoyed themselves there that day.
flavor_text_13: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.
flavor_text_14: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
flavor_text_15: If you think that you had a good dream, but you can't remember it, a DROWZEE has probably eaten it.
flavor_text_16: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it's a sure sign that one of these POKeMON is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.
flavor_text_17: A descendent of the legendary animal baku, which is said to eat dreams. It is skilled at hypnotism.

name: hypno
flavor_text_0: HYPNO holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this POKeMON searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.
flavor_text_1: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.
flavor_text_2: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took  away a child it hypnotized.
flavor_text_3: When it is very hungry, it puts humans it meets to sleep, then it feasts on their dreams.
flavor_text_4: As a matter of course, it makes anyone it meets fall asleep and has a taste of their dreams. Anyone having a good dream, it carries off.
flavor_text_5: There are some Hypno that assist doctors with patients who can't sleep at night in hospitals.
flavor_text_6: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.
flavor_text_7: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.
flavor_text_8: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took away a child it hypnotized.
flavor_text_9: While it is an extremely dangerous Pokemon, people who are in need of a good, sound sleep call it their savior.
flavor_text_10: The longer it swings its pendulum, the longer the effects of its hypnosis last.
flavor_text_11: The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum in a HYPNO's hand lull the foe into deep hypnosis. While searching for prey, it polishes the pendulum.
flavor_text_12: In Alola, Komala is Hypno's main target. It rarely harms people.
flavor_text_13: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.
flavor_text_14: Hypno holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this Pokemon searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.
flavor_text_15: Always holding a pendulum that it rocks at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in any one nearby.

name: krabby
flavor_text_0: If it senses dan ger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.
flavor_text_1: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.
flavor_text_2: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.
flavor_text_3: If it is unable to find food, it will absorb nutrients by swallowing a mouthful of sand.
flavor_text_4: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.
flavor_text_5: The pincers break off easily. If it loses a pincer, it somehow becomes incapable of walking sideways.
flavor_text_6: KRABBY live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these POKeMON can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.
flavor_text_7: Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokemon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.
flavor_text_8: Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.
flavor_text_9: The pincers break off easily. If it loses a pincer, it somehow becomes incapable of walk ing sideways.
flavor_text_10: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.
flavor_text_11: KRABBY live in holes dug into beaches. On sandy shores with little in the way of food, they can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

name: kingler
flavor_text_0: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
flavor_text_1: One claw grew massively and as hard as steel. It has 10,000-HP strength. However, it is too heavy.
flavor_text_2: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.
flavor_text_3: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.
flavor_text_4: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it's not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.
flavor_text_5: It can hardly lift its massive, overgrown pincer. The pincer's size makes it difficult to aim properly.
flavor_text_6: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokemon quickly tires.
flavor_text_7: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.
flavor_text_8: The large pincer has 10,000-horsepower crushing force. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
flavor_text_9: KINGLER has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the POKeMON quickly tires.
flavor_text_10: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.
flavor_text_11: It waves its huge, oversized claw in the air to communicate with others. But since the claw is so heavy, this POKeMON quickly tires.
flavor_text_12: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its bal ance and staggers.
flavor_text_13: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: voltorb
flavor_text_0: VOLTORB was first sighted at a company that manufactures POKe BALLS. The link between that sighting and the fact that this POKeMON looks very similar to a POKe BALL remains a mystery.
flavor_text_1: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to SCREECH or suddenly SELFDESTRUCT.
flavor_text_2: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKe BALL, it has zapped many people.
flavor_text_3: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
flavor_text_4: It bears an uncanny and unexplained resemblance to a POKe BALL. Because it explodes at the slightest shock, even veteran TRAINERS treat it with caution.
flavor_text_5: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poke Ball, it has zapped many people.
flavor_text_6: It was discovered when Poke Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.
flavor_text_7: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.
flavor_text_8: Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poke Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokemon looks very similar to a Poke Ball remains a mystery.
flavor_text_9: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
flavor_text_10: An enigmatic Pokemon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poke Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.
flavor_text_11: It was discovered when POKe BALLS were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.
flavor_text_12: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKe BALL, they have zapped many people.
flavor_text_13: Voltorb is extremely sensitive--it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a Poke Ball was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.
flavor_text_14: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poke Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.
flavor_text_15: VOLTORB is extremely sensitive - it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a POKe BALL was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.
flavor_text_16: During the study of this POKeMON, it was discovered that its compo nents are not found in nature.
flavor_text_17: It is said to camouflage itself as a POKe BALL. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

name: electrode
flavor_text_0: It is dangerous. If it has too much electricity and has nothing to do, it amuses itself by exploding.
flavor_text_1: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.
flavor_text_2: One of ELECTRODE's characteristics is its attraction to electricity. It is a problematical POKeMON that congregates mostly at electrical power plants to feed on electricity that has just been generated.
flavor_text_3: ELECTRODE eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this POKeMON exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.
flavor_text_4: They appear in great numbers at electric power plants. Because they feed on electricity, they cause massive and chaotic blackouts in nearby cities.
flavor_text_5: It stores an over flowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
flavor_text_6: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokemon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.
flavor_text_7: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
flavor_text_8: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.
flavor_text_9: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."
flavor_text_10: Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokemon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.
flavor_text_11: One of Electrode's characteristics is its attraction to electricity. It is a problematical Pokemon that congregates mostly at electrical power plants to feed on electricity that has just been generated.
flavor_text_12: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.
flavor_text_13: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: exeggcute
flavor_text_0: If even one is separated from the group, the energy bond between the six will make them rejoin instantly.
flavor_text_1: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokemon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.
flavor_text_2: This POKeMON consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, EXEGGCUTE is close to evolution.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.
flavor_text_4: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.
flavor_text_5: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.
flavor_text_6: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokemon. It's often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.
flavor_text_7: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life- form more like plant seeds.
flavor_text_8: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.
flavor_text_9: Although they are the same size as other Exeggcute, the ones produced in Alola are quite heavy. Their shells are packed full.
flavor_text_10: Using telepathy only they can receive, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_11: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
flavor_text_12: Using telepathy only they can employ, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_13: It is often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.
flavor_text_14: Their shells are very durable. Even if they crack, they can survive without spilling their contents.
flavor_text_15: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.
flavor_text_16: The shell is very durable. Even if it cracks, it can survive without spilling the contents.
flavor_text_17: These Pokemon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.
flavor_text_18: It consists of six eggs that care for each other. The eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear, it is close to evolution.
flavor_text_19: Six of them form a single Pokemon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.
flavor_text_20: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be 6 heads for it to maintain balance.

name: exeggutor
flavor_text_0: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.
flavor_text_1: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_2: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokemon sluggish.
flavor_text_3: Each of its heads has its own will. They use telepathy to discuss their plans before coming to a joint decision.
flavor_text_4: Its three heads think independent ly. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.
flavor_text_5: Its three heads think independently. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.
flavor_text_6: It is called "The Walking Tropical Rainforest." Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.
flavor_text_7: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.
flavor_text_8: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the 3 heads thinks about whatever it likes.
flavor_text_9: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_10: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.
flavor_text_11: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_12: It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.
flavor_text_13: Living in a good environment makes it grow lots of heads. A head that drops off becomes an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_14: Originally from the tropics, EXEGGUTOR's heads grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall, they group to form an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_15: When the time comes, one of its three heads falls off. Before long, the fallen head grows into an Exeggcute.
flavor_text_16: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
flavor_text_17: If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an EXEGGCUTE cluster.
flavor_text_18: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.
flavor_text_19: EXEGGUTOR originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form EXEGGCUTE.

name: cubone
flavor_text_0: Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.
flavor_text_1: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKeMON's real face.
flavor_text_2: It lost its mother after its birth. It wears its mother's skull, never revealing its true face.
flavor_text_3: At night, it weeps loudly for its dead mother, but those cries only attract its natural enemy--Mandibuzz.
flavor_text_4: It wears its mother's skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it's clear that it's always crying.
flavor_text_5: When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.
flavor_text_6: The skull it wears on its head is that of its dead mother. According to some, it will evolve when it comes to terms with the pain of her death.
flavor_text_7: If it is sad or lonely, the skull it wears shakes, and emits a plain tive and mournful sound.
flavor_text_8: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone's dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.
flavor_text_10: It always wears the skull of its dead mother, so no one has any idea what its hidden face looks like.
flavor_text_11: If it is sad or lonely, the skull it wears shakes and emits a plaintive and mournful sound.
flavor_text_12: It wears the skull of its dead mother on its head. When it becomes lonesome, it is said to cry loudly.
flavor_text_13: It pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull it wears are from its tears.
flavor_text_14: Cubone pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the Pokemon wears are made by the tears it sheds.
flavor_text_15: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.
flavor_text_16: CUBONE pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the POKeMON wears are made by the tears it sheds.

name: marowak
flavor_text_0: It collects bones from an unknown place. Some whisper that a MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world.
flavor_text_1: It throws bones at Mandibuzz to knock it down. It's thought that Marowak is trying to avenge its parent.
flavor_text_2: Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.
flavor_text_3: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.
flavor_text_4: Somewhere in the world is a ceme tery just for MAROWAK. It gets its bones from those graves.
flavor_text_5: When this Pokemon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak's temperament also turned vicious at the same time.
flavor_text_6: Small and weak, this Pokemon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_7: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.
flavor_text_8: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.
flavor_text_10: MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This POKeMON's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_11: This Pokemon is out for vengeance on its natural enemy, Mandibuzz. It throws bones like boomerangs to try to take it down.
flavor_text_12: It collects bones from an unknown place. A MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world, rumors say.
flavor_text_13: From its birth, this savage Pokemon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.
flavor_text_14: A MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has grown tough by overcoming the grief of losing its mother. Its tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_15: Small and weak, this POKeMON is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_16: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.
flavor_text_17: Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokemon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_18: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out mes sages to others.

name: hitmonlee
flavor_text_0: If it starts kick ing repeatedly, both legs will stretch even long er to strike a fleeing foe.
flavor_text_1: This amazing POKe MON has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.
flavor_text_2: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.
flavor_text_3: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.
flavor_text_4: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra-long, loping strides.
flavor_text_5: If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.
flavor_text_6: When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.
flavor_text_7: This amazing Pokemon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.
flavor_text_8: Its legs freely stretch and contract. Using these springlike limbs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its tired legs.
flavor_text_9: When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on im pact and destroys its enemy.
flavor_text_10: It is also called the Kick Master. It uses its elastic legs to execute every known kick.
flavor_text_11: Hitmonlee's legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.
flavor_text_12: HITMONLEE's legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.
flavor_text_13: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

name: hitmonchan
flavor_text_0: HITMONCHAN is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working towards a world championship. This POKeMON has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.
flavor_text_1: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.
flavor_text_2: Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.
flavor_text_3: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this POKeMON. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.
flavor_text_4: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.
flavor_text_5: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.
flavor_text_6: To increase the strength of all its punch moves, it spins its arms just before making contact.
flavor_text_7: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.
flavor_text_8: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.
flavor_text_9: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokemon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.
flavor_text_10: A HITMONCHAN is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who aimed to become the world champion. Having an indomitable spirit means that it will never give up.
flavor_text_11: Punches in cork screw fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall in the same way as a drill.
flavor_text_12: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokemon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

name: lickitung
flavor_text_0: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to any thing, so it is very useful.
flavor_text_1: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
flavor_text_2: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.
flavor_text_3: Wields its long tongue deftly, as though it were an arm. The Pokemon's viscous saliva, once it has been collected and boiled down, yields a strong and highly useful adhesive.
flavor_text_4: Its tongue spans almost 7 feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.
flavor_text_5: When it extends its over-six-foot- long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.
flavor_text_6: It has a tongue that is over 6'6'' long. It uses this long tongue to lick its body clean.
flavor_text_7: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
flavor_text_8: Whenever LICKITUNG comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
flavor_text_9: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.
flavor_text_10: Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.
flavor_text_11: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
flavor_text_12: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it's really clean is...questionable.
flavor_text_13: It checks out whatever's around it by licking everything. If you don't clean off a spot where it's licked you, you'll break out in a rash!
flavor_text_14: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip, so it can be deft ly manipulated.
flavor_text_15: Whenever it sees something unfamiliar, it always licks the object because it memorizes things by texture and taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.
flavor_text_16: Bug Pokemon are Lickitung's main food source. This Pokemon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.
flavor_text_17: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip, so it can be deftly manipulated.
flavor_text_18: If this Pokemon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.
flavor_text_19: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

name: koffing
flavor_text_0: If KOFFING becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This POKeMON may also overinflate its round body, then explode.
flavor_text_1: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.
flavor_text_2: If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokemon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.
flavor_text_3: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.
flavor_text_4: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.
flavor_text_5: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.
flavor_text_6: Getting up close to a KOFFING will give you a chance to observe, through its thin skin, the toxic gases swirling inside. It blows up at the slightest stimulation.
flavor_text_7: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.
flavor_text_8: Its thin, filmy body is filled with gases that cause constant sniffles, coughs and teary eyes.
flavor_text_9: If one gets close enough to it when it expels poison ous gas, the gas swirling inside it can be seen.
flavor_text_10: KOFFING embodies toxic substances. It mixes the toxins with raw garbage to set off a chemical reaction that results in a terribly powerful poison gas. The higher the temperature, the more gas is concocted by this POKeMON.
flavor_text_11: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.
flavor_text_12: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air, keeping it slightly airborne.
flavor_text_13: Koffing embodies toxic substances. It mixes the toxins with raw garbage to set off a chemical reaction that results in a terribly powerful poison gas. The higher the temperature, the more gas is concocted by this Pokemon.
flavor_text_14: In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!
flavor_text_15: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air, keeping it slight ly airborne.

name: weezing
flavor_text_0: It can't suck in air quite as well as a Galarian Weezing, but the toxins it creates are more potent than those of its counterpart.
flavor_text_1: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the high est level.
flavor_text_2: WEEZING alternately shrinks and inflates its twin bodies to mix together toxic gases inside. The more the gases are mixed, the more powerful the toxins become. The POKeMON also becomes more putrid.
flavor_text_3: Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokemon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.
flavor_text_4: Weezing alternately shrinks and inflates its twin bodies to mix together toxic gases inside. The more the gases are mixed, the more powerful the toxins become. The Pokemon also becomes more putrid.
flavor_text_5: By diluting its toxic gases with a special process, the highest grade of perfume can be extracted. To WEEZING, gases emanating from garbage are the ultimate feast.
flavor_text_6: If one of the twin KOFFING inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.
flavor_text_7: It lives and grows by absorbing dust, germs and poison gases that are contained in toxic waste and garbage.
flavor_text_8: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small KOFFING twins becoming conjoined as a WEEZING.
flavor_text_9: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It's said that these Pokemon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.
flavor_text_10: If one of the twin KOFFING inflates, the other one deflates. It con stantly mixes its poisonous gases.
flavor_text_11: This Pokemon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.
flavor_text_12: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, two KOFFING can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.
flavor_text_13: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.
flavor_text_14: WEEZING loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This POKeMON will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.
flavor_text_15: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.
flavor_text_16: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.
flavor_text_17: When it inhales poisonous gases from garbage, its body expands, and its insides smell much worse.
flavor_text_18: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.
flavor_text_19: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.
flavor_text_20: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.

name: rhyhorn
flavor_text_0: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.
flavor_text_1: Its body is clad in a thick hide, and its tackles topple buildings. Unfortunately, it is not smart.
flavor_text_2: Ludicrously strong--when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.
flavor_text_3: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokemon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.
flavor_text_4: Rhyhorn's brain is very small. It is so dense, while on a run it forgets why it started running in the first place. It apparently remembers sometimes if it demolishes something.
flavor_text_5: It doesn't care if there is anything in its way. It just charges and destroys all ob stacles.
flavor_text_6: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.
flavor_text_7: Once it starts running, it doesn't stop. Its tiny brain makes it so stupid that it can't remember why it started running in the first place.
flavor_text_8: RHYHORN runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This POKeMON may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.
flavor_text_9: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokemon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.
flavor_text_10: RHYHORN's brain is very small. It is so dense, while on a run it forgets why it started running in the first place. It apparently remembers sometimes if it demolishes something.
flavor_text_11: A POKeMON with a one-track mind. Once it charges,  it won't stop running until it falls asleep.
flavor_text_12: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.
flavor_text_13: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.
flavor_text_14: Its massive bones are 1,000 times harder than human bones. Its TACKLE can knock a semitrailer flying.
flavor_text_15: A Pokemon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won't stop running until it falls asleep.
flavor_text_16: It doesn't care if there is anything in its way. It just charges and destroys all obstacles.
flavor_text_17: Strong, but not too bright, this POKeMON can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging TACKLES.
flavor_text_18: Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokemon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.

name: rhydon
flavor_text_0: Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.
flavor_text_1: Its brain devel oped when it began walking on hind legs. Its thick hide protects it even in magma.
flavor_text_2: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: By lightly spin ning its drill- like horn, it can easily shatter even a diamond in the rough.
flavor_text_4: Its brain developed after it stood up on its hind legs. Its drill horn bores tunnels through solid rock.
flavor_text_5: Rhydon has a horn that serves as a drill. It is used for destroying rocks and boulders. This Pokemon occasionally rams into streams of magma, but the armor-like hide prevents it from feeling the heat.
flavor_text_6: Its brain developed when it began walking on hind legs. Its thick hide protects it even in magma.
flavor_text_7: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava's heat by its tough, armorlike hide.
flavor_text_8: RHYDON's horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This POKeMON's hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don't leave a scratch.
flavor_text_9: Its horn, which rotates like a drill, destroys tall buildings with one strike. It stands on its hind legs, and its brain is well developed.
flavor_text_10: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.
flavor_text_11: Walks on its hind legs. Shows signs of intelligence. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.
flavor_text_12: Rhydon's horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokemon's hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don't leave a scratch.
flavor_text_13: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.
flavor_text_14: RHYDON has a horn that serves as a drill. It is used for destroying rocks and boulders. This POKeMON occasionally rams into streams of magma, but the armor-like hide prevents it from feeling the heat.
flavor_text_15: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.
flavor_text_16: Its rugged hide protects it from even the heat of lava. However, the hide also makes it insensitive.

name: chansey
flavor_text_0: Because the eggs on their bellies have been overharvested by people in the past, the Chansey population remains very small.
flavor_text_1: A rare and elusive POKeMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch one.
flavor_text_2: CHANSEY lay nutritionally excellent eggs every day. The eggs are so delicious, they are eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.
flavor_text_3: CHANSEY lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.
flavor_text_4: A gentle and kindhearted Pokemon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: This species was once very slow. To protect their eggs from other creatures, these Pokemon became able to flee quickly.
flavor_text_6: A gentle and kind hearted POKeMON that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured POKeMON.
flavor_text_7: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

flavor_text_3: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.

flavor_text_6: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

flavor_text_10: Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food--it will eat anything. This Pokemon has no trouble living in filthy water.

flavor_text_2: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokemon from its pond.
flavor_text_3: CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this POKeMON, making them desolate places.
flavor_text_4: A brutish POKeMON that loves to battle. A veteran CRAWDAUNT that has prevailed in hundreds of battles has giant pincers marked with countless scars.
flavor_text_5: Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokemon, making them desolate places.
flavor_text_6: Its pincers often fall off. Unlike with Crabrawler or Clauncher, the meat in its claws is utterly nasty and stinking.
flavor_text_7: Its temperament is rough and it loves to fight, but as soon as its pincers break off, it turns cowardly. It stays timid until they grow back.
flavor_text_8: Loving to battle, this Pokemon pinches all Pokemon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.
flavor_text_9: Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokemon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.
flavor_text_10: A brutish Pokemon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

flavor_text_1: It disguises itself as seaweed by making its tentacles sway. Unsuspecting prey that come too close are swallowed whole. It became extinct 100 million years ago.

flavor_text_3: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKeMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.

name: cradily

flavor_text_1: CRADILY's body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This POKeMON secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.
flavor_text_2: Cradily's body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokemon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.
flavor_text_3: Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokemon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.
flavor_text_4: It has short legs and can't walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

flavor_text_4: Anorith is said to be a type of Pokemon predecessor, with eight wings at the sides of its body. This Pokemon swam in the primordial sea by undulating these eight wings.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.

flavor_text_1: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.
flavor_text_2: Armaldo's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokemon's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
flavor_text_3: Though it lives on land, it's also a good swimmer. It dives into the ocean in search of prey, using its sharp claws to take down its quarry.
flavor_text_4: ARMALDO's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This POKeMON's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.
flavor_text_5: Armaldo adapted from living in water to living on land. It has been determined that it is the ancestor of some bug Pokemon.

flavor_text_11: ARMALDO usually lives on land. However, when it hunts for prey, it dives beneath the ocean. It swims around using its two large wings.

name: feebas
flavor_text_0: It is the shabbiest Pokemon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

flavor_text_2: It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.
flavor_text_3: While FEEBAS's body is in tatters, it has a hardy and tenacious life force that enables it to live anywhere. However, this POKeMON is also slow and dimwitted, making it an easy catch.
flavor_text_4: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.
flavor_text_5: Feebas's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokemon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.
flavor_text_6: While Feebas's body is in tatters, it has a hardy and tenacious life force that enables it to live anywhere. However, this Pokemon is also slow and dimwitted, making it an easy catch.

flavor_text_8: A tough Pokemon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.
flavor_text_9: Because of its wretched appearance, most people pay it no attention, but there are some who collect Feebas--and Feebas alone!
flavor_text_10: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokemon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.
flavor_text_11: FEEBAS's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKeMON is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.
flavor_text_12: They look ragged, so no one catches them. They look like they'd taste bad, so predators won't eat them. And their numbers continue to grow.
flavor_text_13: Ridiculed for its shabby appearance, it is ignored by researchers. It lives in ponds choked with weeds.

flavor_text_1: MILOTIC is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.

flavor_text_3: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people's minds and hearts.
flavor_text_4: It's said that a glimpse of a MILOTIC and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.
flavor_text_5: Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokemon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.
flavor_text_6: Milotic live at the bottom of large lakes. When this Pokemon's body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to troubled hearts.
flavor_text_7: It's said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.
flavor_text_8: MILOTIC is said to be the most beautiful of all the POKeMON. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.
flavor_text_9: While Milotic is said to be the most beautiful Pokemon, Trainers who like Feebas and have raised it are seemingly disappointed by Milotic.
flavor_text_10: When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.
flavor_text_11: It is said to live at the bottom of large lakes. Considered to be the most beautiful of all POKeMON, it has been depicted in paintings and statues.
flavor_text_12: Milotic is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.
flavor_text_13: Its dwelling place is the bottom of big lakes. Those who behold its loveliness are said to have their hearts purified.

flavor_text_8: Kecleon alters its body coloration to blend in with its surroundings, allowing it to sneak up on its prey unnoticed. Then it lashes out with its long, stretchy tongue to instantly ensnare the unsuspecting target.
flavor_text_9: KECLEON alters its body coloration to blend in with its surroundings, allowing it to sneak up on its prey unnoticed. Then it lashes out with its long, stretchy tongue to instantly ensnare the unsuspecting target.

name: banette
flavor_text_0: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
flavor_text_1: Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokemon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.
flavor_text_2: A doll that became a Pokemon over its grudge of being thrown away. It seeks the child who disowned it.
flavor_text_3: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a POKeMON. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
