flavor_text_11: BANETTE generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This POKeMON was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

name: duskull
flavor_text_0: I've heard that the children of Hisui all begin to behave once they've been told the story of how this Pokemon roams about before the witching hour to spirit away misbehaving children.
flavor_text_1: A glare from its single scarlet eye makes even burly grown-ups freeze in utter fear. It is a nocturnal POKeMON that roams about under the cloak of darkness.
flavor_text_2: DUSKULL can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this POKeMON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
flavor_text_3: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.
flavor_text_4: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.
flavor_text_5: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokemon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.
flavor_text_6: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it's said.
flavor_text_7: Making itself invisible, it silently sneaks up to prey. It has the ability to slip through thick walls.
flavor_text_8: Duskull wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft-told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this Pokemon will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.
flavor_text_9: DUSKULL wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft- told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this POKeMON will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.

name: dusclops
flavor_text_0: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.
flavor_text_1: Dusclops absorbs anything, however large the object may be. This Pokemon hypnotizes its foe by waving its hands in a macabre manner and by bringing its single eye to bear. The hypnotized foe is made to do Dusclops's bidding.
flavor_text_2: DUSCLOPS absorbs anything, however large the object may be. This POKeMON hypnotizes its foe by waving its hands in a macabre manner and by bringing its single eye to bear. The hypnotized foe is made to do DUSCLOPS's bidding.
flavor_text_3: There are rumors that peeking inside its bandage-wrapped body will cause one to get pulled in through the gaps between the bandages, never to return. I've been too scared to verify.
flavor_text_4: It is thought that its body is hollow with only a spectral ball of fire burning inside. However, no one has been able to confirm this theory as fact.
flavor_text_5: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.
flavor_text_6: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.
flavor_text_7: DUSCLOPS's body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKeMON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

flavor_text_9: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.

name: tropius
flavor_text_0: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of TROPIUS. This POKeMON flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.
flavor_text_1: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.
flavor_text_2: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokemon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.
flavor_text_3: The bunches of fruit around Tropius's neck are very popular with children. This Pokemon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
flavor_text_4: The bunches of fruit growing around the necks of Tropius in Alola are especially sweet compared to those in other regions.
flavor_text_5: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.
flavor_text_6: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.
flavor_text_7: The bunches of fruit around TROPIUS's neck are very popular with children. This POKeMON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.
flavor_text_8: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.
flavor_text_9: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.
flavor_text_10: Because it continually ate only its favorite fruit, the fruit started growing around its neck.
flavor_text_11: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

name: chimecho
flavor_text_0: They fly about very actively when the hot season arrives. They communicate among themselves using seven different and distinguishing cries.

flavor_text_13: Overjoyed at finally being able to fly, it flies all over the place and usually doesn't land until it's completely exhausted and needs to sleep.

name: beldum

flavor_text_2: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout BELDUM's body. This POKeMON communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.
flavor_text_3: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
flavor_text_4: BELDUM keeps itself floating by generating a magnetic force that repels earth's natural magnetism. When it sleeps, this POKeMON anchors itself to a cliff using the hooks on its rear.
flavor_text_5: It uses magnetic waves to converse with its kind. All the cells in its body are magnetic.
flavor_text_6: The cells in this Pokemon's body are composed of magnetic material. Instead of blood, magnetic forces flow through Beldum's body.
flavor_text_7: When BELDUM gather in a swarm, they move in perfect unison as if they were but one POKeMON. They communicate with each other using brain waves.
flavor_text_8: Beldum keeps itself floating by generating a magnetic force that repels earth's natural magnetism. When it sleeps, this Pokemon anchors itself to a cliff using the hooks on its rear.
flavor_text_9: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout Beldum's body. This Pokemon communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.

flavor_text_12: Instead of blood, magnetism flows through its body. When it's feeling bad, try giving it a magnet.
flavor_text_13: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.
flavor_text_14: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.

flavor_text_2: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. This Pokemon turns its arms to the rear for traveling at high speed.
flavor_text_3: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this Pokemon generates strong psychokinetic power.

flavor_text_6: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.
flavor_text_7: With its two brains, it fires powerful psychic energy to stop its prey in their tracks.
flavor_text_8: When two BELDUM fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.
flavor_text_9: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.
flavor_text_10: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft, this Pokemon flies at high speeds, weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.
flavor_text_11: It floats midair using magnetism. Its body is so tough, even a crash with a jet plane won't leave a scratch.

name: metagross
flavor_text_0: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
flavor_text_1: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.
flavor_text_2: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokemon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
flavor_text_3: It boasts not only psychic powers but also fantastic strength. It grabs its prey with its four legs and holds them in place with its claws.
flavor_text_4: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokemon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.
flavor_text_5: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.
flavor_text_6: It is formed by two METANG fusing. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.
flavor_text_7: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokemon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.
flavor_text_8: METAGROSS has four brains that are joined by a complex neural network. As a result of integration, this POKeMON is smarter than a supercomputer.
flavor_text_9: METAGROSS is the result of two METANG achieving fusion. When hunting, this POKeMON pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large  mouth on its stomach.
flavor_text_10: METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKeMON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
flavor_text_11: METANG combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
flavor_text_12: With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.

flavor_text_15: A linkage of two Metang, this Pokemon can perform any calculation in a flash by utilizing parallel processing in its four brains.

name: regirock
flavor_text_0: It is entirely composed of rocks with no sign of a brain or heart. It is a mystery even to modern scientists.
flavor_text_1: REGIROCK's body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.
flavor_text_2: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokemon's rock body, but nothing was found--not even a brain or a heart.
flavor_text_3: REGIROCK was sealed away by people long ago. If this POKeMON's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.
flavor_text_4: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
flavor_text_5: Every bit of Regirock's body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokemon sticks rocks to itself to repair what's been lost.
flavor_text_6: Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokemon's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.
flavor_text_7: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.
flavor_text_8: Regirock's body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.
flavor_text_9: A POKeMON that is made entirely of rocks and boulders. If parts of its body chip off in battle, REGIROCK repairs itself by adding new rocks.

name: regice
flavor_text_0: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: REGICE's body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can't be melted, even by fire. This POKeMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.
flavor_text_2: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can't be melted, even by magma.
flavor_text_3: Regice cloaks itself with frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit. Things will freeze solid just by going near this Pokemon. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.
flavor_text_4: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as -328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.
flavor_text_5: Its entire body is made of Antarctic ice. After extensive studies, researchers believe the ice was formed during an ice age.
flavor_text_6: Research revealed that its body is made of the same kind of ice that is found at the South Pole.
flavor_text_7: REGICE cloaks itself with frigid air of negative 328 degrees F. Things will freeze solid just by going near this POKeMON. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.
flavor_text_8: Regice's body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can't be melted, even by fire. This Pokemon controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon's body is made of solid ice. It's said that Regice was born beneath thick ice in the ice age.

name: registeel
flavor_text_0: Registeel's body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.
flavor_text_1: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.
flavor_text_2: Registeel was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.
flavor_text_3: It's rumored that this Pokemon was born deep underground in the planet's mantle and that it emerged onto the surface 10,000 years ago.
flavor_text_4: Its body is harder than any other kind of metal. The body metal is composed of a mysterious substance. Not only is it hard, it shrinks and stretches flexibly.

flavor_text_6: Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokemon eats.

flavor_text_9: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

name: latias
flavor_text_0: LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKeMON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.
flavor_text_1: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
flavor_text_2: They make a small herd of only several members. They rarely make contact with people or other POKeMON. They disappear if they sense enemies.
flavor_text_3: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokemon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

flavor_text_5: LATIAS is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The POKeMON enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

flavor_text_7: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokemon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

flavor_text_2: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKeMON is intelligent and understands human speech.
flavor_text_3: Even in hiding, it can detect the locations of others and sense their emotions since it has telepathy. Its intelligence allows it to understand human languages.

flavor_text_6: LATIOS will only open its heart to a TRAINER with a compassionate spirit. This POKeMON can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.
flavor_text_7: It has a docile temperament and dislikes fighting. Tucking in its forelegs, it can fly faster than a jet plane.

name: kyogre
flavor_text_0: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
flavor_text_1: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.
flavor_text_2: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKeMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.
flavor_text_3: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
flavor_text_4: KYOGRE is named in mythology as the POKeMON that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with GROUDON.
flavor_text_5: A mythical Pokemon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.
flavor_text_6: KYOGRE has appeared in mythology as the creator of the sea. After long years of feuding with GROUDON, it took to sleep at the bottom of the sea.

flavor_text_8: This POKeMON is said to have expanded the sea by bringing heavy rains. It has the power to control water.

flavor_text_0: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought KYOGRE long ago.

flavor_text_2: This legendary POKeMON is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling KYOGRE.
flavor_text_3: GROUDON has the power to scatter rain clouds and make water evaporate with light and heat. It came as a savior to people who had been suffering from terrible floods.
flavor_text_4: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
flavor_text_5: GROUDON has appeared in mythology as the creator of the land. It sleeps in magma underground and is said to make volcanoes erupt on awakening.
flavor_text_6: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKeMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKeMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.
flavor_text_7: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.
flavor_text_8: This legendary Pokemon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.
flavor_text_9: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
flavor_text_10: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with KYOGRE.

flavor_text_2: RAYQUAZA is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth's ozone layer, above the clouds. Its existence had been completely unknown because it lived so high in the sky.
flavor_text_3: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

flavor_text_5: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth's ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKeMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.
flavor_text_6: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
flavor_text_7: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

name: jirachi
flavor_text_0: JIRACHI will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.
flavor_text_1: It is said to make any wish come true. It is awake for only seven days out of a thousand years.
flavor_text_2: A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKeMON senses danger, it will fight without awakening.
flavor_text_3: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokemon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

flavor_text_5: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

flavor_text_8: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.
flavor_text_9: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: deoxys
flavor_text_0: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKeMON's chest appears to be its brain.
flavor_text_1: When it changes form, an aurora appears. It absorbs attacks by altering its cellular structure.
flavor_text_2: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokemon's chest appears to be its brain.
flavor_text_3: This DEOXYS has transformed into its aggressive guise. It can fool enemies by altering its appearance.
flavor_text_4: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokemon. It appears where auroras are seen.
flavor_text_5: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokemon.
flavor_text_6: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokemon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.
flavor_text_7: DEOXYS emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This POKeMON shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.
flavor_text_8: A POKeMON that mutated from an extraterrestrial virus exposed to a laser beam. Its body is configured for superior agility and speed.

name: turtwig
flavor_text_0: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.
flavor_text_2: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy TURTWIG, the shell should feel moist.
flavor_text_3: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.
flavor_text_4: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.
flavor_text_5: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: grotle
flavor_text_0: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokemon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.
flavor_text_1: A GROTLE that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.
flavor_text_2: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokemon there on its back.
flavor_text_3: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
flavor_text_4: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.

name: torterra
flavor_text_0: Groups of this Pokemon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for "moving forests."
flavor_text_1: Small Pokemon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
flavor_text_2: Some Pokemon are born on a TORTERRA's back and spend their entire life there.
flavor_text_3: Some Pokemon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there.
flavor_text_4: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic TORTERRA dwelled.
flavor_text_5: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.
flavor_text_6: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokemon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.

name: chimchar
flavor_text_0: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.
flavor_text_1: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.
flavor_text_2: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name "Lantern-Tail" and feared as some kind of apparition.
flavor_text_3: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.
flavor_text_4: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: monferno
flavor_text_0: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.
flavor_text_1: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.
flavor_text_2: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.
flavor_text_3: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.
flavor_text_4: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.

name: infernape
flavor_text_0: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.
flavor_text_1: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.
flavor_text_2: A tall, hardy Pokemon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance--truly a sight to behold.
flavor_text_3: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
flavor_text_4: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: piplup
flavor_text_0: Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It's an adorable little thing--as cute as any child--but it's also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.
flavor_text_1: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.
flavor_text_2: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.
flavor_text_3: It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.
flavor_text_4: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: prinplup
flavor_text_0: It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.
flavor_text_1: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
flavor_text_2: Because every PRINPLUP considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.
flavor_text_3: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.
flavor_text_4: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.
flavor_text_5: Its wings deliver wicked blows that snap even the thickest of trees. It searches for prey in icy seas.

name: empoleon
flavor_text_0: Since ancient times, it has been revered by the people of Hisui, who call it the Master of the Waves. Its wings are a match for even master-crafted blades.
flavor_text_1: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.
flavor_text_2: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
flavor_text_3: It avoids unnecessary disputes, but it will decimate anything that threatens its pride.
flavor_text_4: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: starly
flavor_text_0: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
flavor_text_1: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
flavor_text_2: Usually with a large flock, it is barely noticeable when alone. Its cries are very strident.
flavor_text_3: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokemon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
flavor_text_4: They live in the fields and mountains, gathering in large flocks. Their cries are quite obnoxious. Though small, their wings are strong--a strike from them leaves pain that persists for a week.

name: staravia
flavor_text_0: They form remarkably large flocks and are constantly fighting amongst themselves. I suspect that those with magnificent plumes on their heads are the strong ones.
flavor_text_1: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a STARAVIA cries noisily.
flavor_text_2: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.
flavor_text_3: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
flavor_text_4: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokemon. It stays within a huge flock.
flavor_text_5: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

name: staraptor
flavor_text_0: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
flavor_text_1: It has left the flock, having gained strength enough to survive on its own. The astounding force with which Staraptor flies through the air allows it to carry away large, burly targets.
flavor_text_2: When STARAVIA evolve into STARAPTOR, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
flavor_text_3: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.
flavor_text_4: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
flavor_text_5: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokemon.

name: bidoof
flavor_text_0: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.
flavor_text_1: A comparison revealed that BIDOOF's front teeth grow at the same rate as RATTATA's.
flavor_text_2: It lives in groups by the water.  It chews up boulders and trees around its nest with its incisors.
flavor_text_3: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.
flavor_text_4: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
flavor_text_5: A comparison revealed that Bidoof's front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's.

name: bibarel
flavor_text_0: A river dammed by BIBAREL will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.
flavor_text_1: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokemon create dams on rivers to live in.
flavor_text_2: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
flavor_text_3: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.
flavor_text_4: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.
flavor_text_5: While its movements out of water are sluggish, it can swim as fast as any FEEBAS.

name: kricketot
flavor_text_0: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.
flavor_text_1: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.
flavor_text_2: When the trees take on new hues, more of these Pokemon appear. The tone they create by striking their antennae together resembles that of the marimba, an instrument of foreign lands.
flavor_text_3: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
flavor_text_4: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

name: kricketune
flavor_text_0: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.
flavor_text_1: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.
flavor_text_2: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.
flavor_text_3: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: It uses its cutlass-like arms to produce sound, the melody of which varies from individual to individual. It is a worthwhile endeavor to seek out one's favorite tunes.

name: shinx
flavor_text_0: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it's in trouble.
flavor_text_1: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.
flavor_text_3: Shakes its body to generate electricity. Its stature belies its aggression--one must be patient to tame this Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: Electricity makes this Pokemon's fur glow. Shinx sends signals to others of its kind by shaking the tip of its tail while the tail tip is shining brightly.
flavor_text_5: Its forelegs have a muscle-based system of generating electricity. Its body shines if endangered.
flavor_text_6: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: luxio
flavor_text_0: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokemon can receive some of the other Luxio's electricity and power up its own electric blasts.
flavor_text_1: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
flavor_text_2: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.
flavor_text_3: Proudly uses its electrified claws as weapons. It seems to be a gracious Pokemon, evenly sharing the spoils of the hunt with others of its kind.
flavor_text_4: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
flavor_text_5: Upon encountering an opponent, this Pokemon prepares for battle by extending its claws, which can put out 1,000,000 volts of electricity.
flavor_text_6: It rests its forelegs on others to communicate with rhythmic electric pulses from its claws.

name: luxray
flavor_text_0: LUXRAY's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
flavor_text_1: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.
flavor_text_2: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.
flavor_text_3: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey--even those taking shelter behind a wall.
flavor_text_4: They form packs, each having one male as leader. Legends say that when Luxray's two eyes shimmer with gold, the Pokemon can see through anything.
flavor_text_5: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
flavor_text_6: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.
flavor_text_7: Seeing through solid objects uses up a lot of Luxray's electricity, so the Pokemon sleeps for long periods of time to store up energy.

name: budew
flavor_text_0: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokemon is raised on clean water, the poison's toxicity is increased.
flavor_text_1: It lives alongside clear ponds. It scatters pollen that induces harsh sneezing and runny noses.
flavor_text_2: When the sun's light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokemon's head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.
flavor_text_3: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.
flavor_text_4: Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun's warm touch.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon is highly sensitive to temperature changes. When its bud starts to open, that means spring is right around the corner.
flavor_text_6: Sensitive to changing temperatures, the bud blooms when it's warm, releasing toxic pollen.
flavor_text_7: When it feels the sun's warm touch, it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

name: roserade
flavor_text_0: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.
flavor_text_1: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.
flavor_text_2: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.
flavor_text_3: Its sweet aroma attracts prey. Then it spews poison. The more toxic it is, the sweeter its aroma.
flavor_text_4: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.
flavor_text_5: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.
flavor_text_6: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.
flavor_text_7: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.

name: cranidos
flavor_text_0: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.
flavor_text_1: In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found, the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two are also often found.
flavor_text_2: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its headbutts.
flavor_text_3: An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.
flavor_text_4: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.
flavor_text_5: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.
flavor_text_6: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.
flavor_text_7: A primeval Pokemon, it possesses a hard and sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.
flavor_text_8: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.
flavor_text_9: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its head butts.
flavor_text_10: CRANIDOS toughen up their already rock-hard heads by headbutting one another.

name: rampardos
flavor_text_0: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result, its brain never gets the chance to grow.
flavor_text_1: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.
flavor_text_2: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.
flavor_text_3: In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of this Pokemon and use its skull, which is harder than steel, to make helmets.
flavor_text_4: The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with Cranidos's.
flavor_text_5: Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.
flavor_text_6: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.
flavor_text_7: Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.
flavor_text_8: This ancient Pokemon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.

name: shieldon
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it's thought.
flavor_text_1: A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokemon, it used its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on its face was plenty tough.
flavor_text_2: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it against tree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.
flavor_text_3: Many fossils of this Pokemon have been found, but almost none have shown signs of damage to the face.
flavor_text_4: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.
flavor_text_5: Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.
flavor_text_6: A Pokemon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.
flavor_text_7: Much remains unknown about this Pokemon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.
flavor_text_8: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

name: bastiodon
flavor_text_0: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.
flavor_text_1: When attacked, they form a wall with their shieldlike faces to protect their young.
flavor_text_2: It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together-- seemingly from after they'd fought to the finish.
flavor_text_3: Its face is sturdy--as strong as diamond--and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.
flavor_text_4: When attacked, they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks.
flavor_text_5: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokemon that feeds on grass and berries.
flavor_text_6: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.
flavor_text_8: The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pokemon was successfully restored.

name: burmy
flavor_text_0: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.
flavor_text_1: It covers itself with a cloak to shelter from the cold. When it's hot, its cloak is thinner.
flavor_text_2: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.
flavor_text_3: If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokemon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.
flavor_text_4: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: wormadam
flavor_text_0: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
flavor_text_1: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.
flavor_text_2: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.
flavor_text_3: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
flavor_text_4: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: mothim
flavor_text_0: It does not keep a nest. It flies over fields and mountains in constant search of floral honey.
flavor_text_1: While it loves floral honey, it won't gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from COMBEE.
flavor_text_2: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the COMBEE hive.
flavor_text_3: While it loves floral honey, it won't gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from Combee.
flavor_text_4: Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.
flavor_text_5: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.
flavor_text_6: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.
flavor_text_7: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

name: combee
flavor_text_0: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.
flavor_text_1: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please VESPIQUEN.
flavor_text_2: It ceaselessly gathers nectar from sunrise to sundown, all for the sake of Vespiquen and the swarm.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is a set of three. When they sleep, they gather up and form a giant hive of 100 Combee.
flavor_text_4: At night, COMBEE sleep in a group of about a thousand, packed closely together in a lump.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.
flavor_text_6: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.
flavor_text_7: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.
flavor_text_8: They swear fealty to a queen Pokemon and work diligently to gather nectar. Each swarm produces a different flavor of honey.

name: vespiquen
flavor_text_0: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control COMBEE.
flavor_text_1: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.
flavor_text_2: When endangered, grubs from its six-cell honeycomb strike back. There is only one in a colony.
flavor_text_3: It releases various pheromones to make the grubs in its body do its bidding while fighting foes.
flavor_text_4: Commands its subjects to build its hive. It will dispatch any interlopers who dare sneak into its nest and use them as nourishment for itself.
flavor_text_5: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.
flavor_text_6: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.
flavor_text_7: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.
flavor_text_8: Vespiquen that give off more pheromones have larger swarms of Combee attendants.

name: pachirisu
flavor_text_0: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It lives atop trees.
flavor_text_1: It's one of the kinds of Pokemon  with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.
flavor_text_2: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.
flavor_text_3: A species related to the Pikachu line. Though Pachirisu is a calm Pokemon, it still presents a danger should one touch its electrified tail or cheeks.
flavor_text_4: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

name: buizel
flavor_text_0: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.
flavor_text_1: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.
flavor_text_2: It moves freely in the water by spinning its forked tail for propulsion. The resemblance to the screw of a steamboat is coincidental.
flavor_text_3: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.
flavor_text_4: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.
flavor_text_5: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

name: floatzel
flavor_text_0: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.
flavor_text_1: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.
flavor_text_2: Has a long, rather splendid flotation sac, which prevents Floatzel from drowning even in stormy seas. One might glimpse this species around fishing hamlets from time to time.
flavor_text_3: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.
flavor_text_4: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: cherubi
flavor_text_0: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.
flavor_text_1: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokemon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.
flavor_text_2: Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.
flavor_text_3: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.
flavor_text_4: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.
flavor_text_5: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.
flavor_text_6: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. STARLY try to peck it off.
flavor_text_7: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

name: cherrim
flavor_text_0: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.
flavor_text_1: Motionless, save for the occasional quiver. A rich array of Pokemon can be found gathered around it, drawn by the scent exuded from Cherrim's folded petals.
flavor_text_2: It is docile as a bud, but turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.
flavor_text_3: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.
flavor_text_4: Its folded petals are pretty tough. Bird Pokemon can peck at them all they want, and Cherrim won't be bothered at all.
flavor_text_5: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.
flavor_text_6: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.

name: shellos
flavor_text_0: Found in abundance on seashores bordering warm waters. Shellos are unexpectedly friendly and will crawl toward any person they see. Take care not to get coated in mucus!
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon's habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories, life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.
flavor_text_2: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.
flavor_text_3: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.
flavor_text_4: It lives along bodies of water. Its body shape has changed to suit its habitat.
flavor_text_5: For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.
flavor_text_6: Subjecting this Pokemon to a strong force causes it to secrete a strange purple fluid. Though harmless, the fluid is awfully sticky.
flavor_text_7: When it senses danger, a purple liquid oozes out of it. The liquid is thought to be something like greasy sweat.
flavor_text_8: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.
flavor_text_9: Purple mucus sticks to the hands of anyone who touches it. Take care, as the substance is troublesome to wash off.
flavor_text_10: While they normally live in the sea, they can function on land, too, until their skin dries out.

name: gastrodon
flavor_text_0: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.
flavor_text_1: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purple fluid and escapes.
flavor_text_2: Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.
flavor_text_3: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.
flavor_text_4: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.
flavor_text_5: It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokemon, it will return to normal within a few hours.
flavor_text_6: Eats beach sand for nourishment. Should one Gastrodon encounter another of a different color, a fierce battle will inevitably ensue.
flavor_text_7: Their shape and color change, depending on their environment and diet. There are many of them at beaches where the waves are calm.
flavor_text_8: The softness of its body helps disperse the force of impacts, so although its body is uncommonly squishy, it's also surprisingly resilient.
flavor_text_9: Plankton, invisible to the naked eye, is its main food source. It comes onto the land periodically, but the reason for this is not known.
flavor_text_10: Long ago, it had a shell on its back. There's now a vestigial plate on its back that's hard but thin.

name: ambipom
flavor_text_0: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.
flavor_text_1: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.
flavor_text_2: They live on large trees. They are said to communicate by connecting their tails to those of others.
flavor_text_3: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.
flavor_text_4: It is very difficult to dodge the consecutive strikes of its two tails.
flavor_text_5: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.
flavor_text_6: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, AMBIPOM rarely uses its hands.
flavor_text_7: In their search for comfortable trees, they get into territorial disputes with groups of Passimian. They win about half the time.
flavor_text_8: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: drifloon
flavor_text_0: These Pokemon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.
flavor_text_1: Its round body is stuffed with souls and expands each time it leads someone away.
flavor_text_2: A Pokemon formed by the spirits of people and Pokemon. It loves damp, humid seasons.
flavor_text_3: Stories go that it grabs the hands of small children and drags them away to the afterlife. It dislikes heavy children.
flavor_text_4: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.
flavor_text_5: Wandering souls gathered together to form this Pokemon. When trying to make friends with children, Drifloon grabs them by the hand.
flavor_text_6: If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills out with a screaming sound.
flavor_text_7: Perhaps seeking company, it approaches children. However, it often quickly runs away again when the children play too roughly with it.
flavor_text_8: The gathering of many souls gave rise to this Pokemon. During humid seasons, they seem to appear in abundance.
flavor_text_9: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."
flavor_text_10: Said to lure away young children and carry them off to the afterlife. Some whisper that Drifloon are formed of reincarnated human souls, but these rumors are as yet unconfirmed.
flavor_text_11: It is whispered that any child who mistakes DRIFLOON for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: drifblim
flavor_text_0: It can generate and release gas within its body. That's how it can control the altitude of its drift.
flavor_text_1: It grabs people and Pokemon and carries them off somewhere. Where do they go? Nobody knows.
flavor_text_2: They carry people and Pokemon, but the wind can catch them, so there can't be a fixed destination.
flavor_text_3: Some say this Pokemon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.
flavor_text_4: It's drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.
flavor_text_5: There was once an incident in which a man took a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.
flavor_text_6: It drifts along at dusk, perfectly silent. Its transient, melancholy aspect touches some people deeply--every so often, one will come upon a song or poem devoted to Drifblim.
flavor_text_7: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.
flavor_text_8: It carries people and Pokemon when it flies. But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.
flavor_text_9: There's a rumor that if you catch a Drifblim floating on the wind at dusk, you'll be carried away to the afterlife.
flavor_text_10: Even while under careful observation, large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably disappear from view.
flavor_text_11: The raw material for the gas inside its body is souls. When its body starts to deflate, it's thought to carry away people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_12: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

name: buneary
flavor_text_0: Its arms and legs are weak, but when it rolls its ears up tight and then unleashes them with its full force, it can smash boulders to dust.
flavor_text_1: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.
flavor_text_2: You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it's scared, both ears are rolled up.
flavor_text_3: My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pokemon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears.
flavor_text_4: The reason it keeps one ear rolled up is so it can launch a swift counterattack if it's attacked by an enemy.
flavor_text_5: If both of Buneary's ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It's a sure sign the Pokemon is in need of care.
flavor_text_6: Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training.
flavor_text_7: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.
flavor_text_8: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.
flavor_text_9: By extending its rolled-up ears and striking the ground, it can bound so high it surprises itself.

name: lopunny
flavor_text_0: It's notably wary and has a dislike of fighting, but at the same time, it can deliver powerful kicks with its lithe legs.
flavor_text_1: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
flavor_text_2: An extremely cautious Pokemon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.
flavor_text_3: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.
flavor_text_4: It sheds its fur twice a year. Its winter fur is soft and fluffy.
flavor_text_5: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokemon responds with superdestructive kicks.
flavor_text_6: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.
flavor_text_7: Once hot seasons are over, Lopunny's coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.
flavor_text_8: Lopunny regrows its coat twice a year. Mufflers and hats made from its fur are really warm.
flavor_text_9: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokemon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.

name: mismagius
flavor_text_0: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.
flavor_text_1: Mismagius have been known to cast spells to make people fall in love, so some people search for this Pokemon as if their life depended on it.
flavor_text_2: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.
flavor_text_3: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.
flavor_text_4: It chants incantations. While they usually torment targets, some chants bring happiness.
flavor_text_5: Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokemon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.
flavor_text_6: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.
flavor_text_7: The incantations Mismagius chants can ward against misfortune, so a custom exists of inviting it into one's home. Incur the Pokemon's displeasure, however, and disaster will surely ensue.
flavor_text_8: It appears as if from nowhere--muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.

name: honchkrow
flavor_text_0: If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it, or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt them down wherever they are and punish them.
flavor_text_1: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.
flavor_text_2: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokemon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.
flavor_text_3: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."
flavor_text_4: If one utters a deep cry, many MURKROW gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."
flavor_text_5: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.
flavor_text_6: It will absolutely not forgive failure from or betrayal by its goons. It has no choice in this if it wants to maintain the order of the flock.
flavor_text_7: One cry from this Pokemon, and a murder of Murkrow come flying. At such times, one would think the curtain of night had fallen, plunging the world into jet-black darkness.
flavor_text_8: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.
flavor_text_9: It makes its MURKROW cronies bring it food. It idles its time away, grooming itself in its nest.
flavor_text_10: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its MURKROW followers.

name: glameow
flavor_text_0: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.
flavor_text_1: It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn't fed.
flavor_text_2: When it's happy, GLAMEOW demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.
flavor_text_3: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.
flavor_text_4: Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokemon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.
flavor_text_5: With its sharp glare, it puts foes in a mild hypnotic state. It is a very fickle Pokemon.

name: purugly
flavor_text_0: It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.
flavor_text_1: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokemon's nest and claims it as its own.
flavor_text_2: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.
flavor_text_3: It would claim another Pokemon's nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.
flavor_text_4: Though impudent and difficult to tame, Purugly enjoys great popularity due to its fur, the beauty of which surpasses even velveteen.

name: chingling
flavor_text_0: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.
flavor_text_1: It emits high-frequency cries that  people can't hear. Once it starts, it can cry for an awfully long time.
flavor_text_2: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.
flavor_text_3: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.

name: stunky
flavor_text_0: It sprays a nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear to repel attackers.
flavor_text_1: The poison that gushes from its aft end is accompanied by an utterly evil-smelling odor with such potency that one whiff can induce memory loss.
flavor_text_2: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.
flavor_text_3: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokemon away.
flavor_text_4: If it lifts its tail and points its rear at you, beware. It's about to spray you with a fluid stinky enough to make you faint.
flavor_text_5: From its rear, it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces, and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.
flavor_text_6: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: skuntank
flavor_text_0: It digs holes in the ground to make its nest. The stench of the fluid it lets fly from the tip of its tail is extremely potent.
flavor_text_1: Sprays a poisonous fluid to take down prey. Sometimes, unable to stomach the stench of its own fluid, it leaves the bested prey uneaten.
flavor_text_2: In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokemon's diet varies, so does the stench of its fluid.
flavor_text_3: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.
flavor_text_4: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.
flavor_text_5: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.
flavor_text_6: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

name: bronzor
flavor_text_0: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.
flavor_text_1: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.
flavor_text_2: There are researchers who believe this Pokemon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.
flavor_text_3: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure. Nothing appeared, however.
flavor_text_4: Floats using a mysterious energy. The pattern engraved upon its back is held as sacred and can sometimes be found in imagery from ancient cemeteries and other such timeworn places.
flavor_text_5: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.
flavor_text_6: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn't come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.
flavor_text_7: Ancient people believed that the pattern on BRONZOR's back contained a mysterious power.
flavor_text_8: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: bronzong
flavor_text_0: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.
flavor_text_1: It can summon rain clouds. People long ago revered it as the bringer of plentiful harvests.
flavor_text_2: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.
flavor_text_3: Ancient people believed that petitioning BRONZONG for rain was the way to make crops grow.
flavor_text_4: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.
flavor_text_5: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.
flavor_text_6: Some believe that its bell-like cry opens holes to another world. It has been revered as a deity since ancient times.
flavor_text_7: Many scientists suspect that this Pokemon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.
flavor_text_8: In ages past, this Pokemon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: bonsly
flavor_text_0: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.
flavor_text_1: It does not deal well with water, so it lives in dry locales. Since its surroundings tend to lack greenery, it stands out noticeably.
flavor_text_2: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body's fluid levels by eliminating excess.
flavor_text_3: If its body gets too damp, it will die. So, in a process reminiscent of sweating, its eyes expel moisture.
flavor_text_4: It expels both sweat and tears from its eyes. The sweat is a little salty, while the tears have a slight bitterness.
flavor_text_5: Its tears elicit sympathy from those who see them, but do not be deceived! This expulsion of body water is merely a physiological mechanism for keeping itself in good health.
flavor_text_6: It discharges moisture from its eyes, making it look like it's crying--apparently an effective way of getting enemies to let down their guard.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon lives in dry, rocky areas. As its green spheres dry out, their dull luster increases.
flavor_text_8: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.
flavor_text_9: It prefers arid environments. It leaks water from its eyes to adjust its body's fluid levels.
flavor_text_10: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body, it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

name: mime-jr
flavor_text_0: It does its absolute best to mimic the movements and expressions of its opponents, but it's still not very good at it.
flavor_text_1: Known to turn up in bustling marketplaces now and again. It mimics people much as a child would, then watches how they react, eyes sparkling.
flavor_text_2: It looks for a Mr. Rime that's a good dancer and carefully copies the Mr. Rime's steps like an apprentice.
flavor_text_3: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!
flavor_text_4: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: When this gifted mimic surprises an opponent, Mime Jr. feels so happy that it ends up forgetting it was imitating something.
flavor_text_6: It likes places where people gather. It mimics foes to confuse them, then makes its getaway.
flavor_text_7: It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.
flavor_text_8: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

name: happiny
flavor_text_0: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.
flavor_text_1: It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.
flavor_text_2: Happiny's willing to lend its precious round stone to those it's friendly with, but if the stone isn't returned, Happiny will cry and throw a tantrum.
flavor_text_3: In imitation of Chansey, it keeps a round stone tucked into its belly pouch and cherishes it dearly. It gets along well with children and will sometimes play house with them for fun.
flavor_text_4: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.
flavor_text_5: It's too small to lay eggs yet. As a surrogate, it searches out round white stones.
flavor_text_6: Mimicking Chansey, Happiny will place an egg- shaped stone in its belly pouch. Happiny will treasure this stone.
flavor_text_7: When it sees something round and white, Happiny puts it into the pouch on its stomach. It sometimes becomes overloaded and can't move.
flavor_text_8: It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its belly pouch and gives the rock to its friends.
flavor_text_9: Usually it's a well-behaved Pokemon, but if you take its round rock away, it will cry and fuss and throw a big old tantrum.
flavor_text_10: It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others' feet and cause them to stumble.

name: chatot
flavor_text_0: It mimics the cries of other Pokemon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack it.
flavor_text_1: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.
flavor_text_2: It keeps rhythm by flicking its tail feathers like a metronome. It imitates human speech.
flavor_text_3: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.
flavor_text_4: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: spiritomb
flavor_text_0: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.
flavor_text_1: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.
flavor_text_2: A Pokemon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
flavor_text_3: It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokemon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.
flavor_text_4: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.
flavor_text_5: All Spiritomb's mischief and misdeeds compelled a traveler to use a mysterious spell to bind Spiritomb to an odd keystone.
flavor_text_6: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokemon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

name: gible
flavor_text_0: It lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat. Even so, when the weather gets cold, it will huddle close with others of its kind.
flavor_text_1: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.
flavor_text_2: Gible attacks anything that moves, and it drags whatever it catches into the crevice that is its lair. Despite the big mouth, Gible's stomach is small.
flavor_text_3: It nests in caves untouched by sunlight. Its sharp teeth may fall out when worn away or after an impact, but they regrow within a few days.
flavor_text_4: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.
flavor_text_5: It once lived in the tropics. To avoid the cold, it lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat.
flavor_text_6: It reacts to anything that moves--flies right at it and bites it. Sometimes it injures itself, but it doesn't care too much.
flavor_text_7: Its original home is an area much hotter than Alola. If you're planning to live with one, your heating bill will soar.
flavor_text_8: Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.
flavor_text_9: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
flavor_text_10: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: gabite
flavor_text_0: It sheds its skin and gradually grows larger. Its scales can be ground into a powder and used as raw materials for traditional medicine.
flavor_text_1: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.
flavor_text_2: Jewels are buried in the caves these Pokemon nest in, but you'll be torn apart by claws and fangs the moment you enter one of these caves.
flavor_text_3: It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.
flavor_text_5: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.
flavor_text_6: It loves shiny things. When it finds a Sableye trying to catch a Carbink, Gabite becomes furiously angry and attacks the Sableye.
flavor_text_7: Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it's amassed or Carbink it has caught.
flavor_text_8: Though Gabite are usually of a violent disposition, when I gave one a glass bead it had been eyeing covetously, it suddenly became quite docile.
flavor_text_9: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.
flavor_text_10: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: garchomp
flavor_text_0: Its body is covered in fine scales that reduce drag, enabling it to fly at high speeds.
flavor_text_1: Soars across the heavens at blinding speed--a magnificent sight! It has a feral disposition. Utmost caution is required if one meets a Garchomp out in the wilds.
flavor_text_2: Its fine scales don't just reduce wind resistance--their sharp edges also cause injury to any opponent who attacks it.
flavor_text_3: It can fly at speeds rivaling jet planes. It dives into flocks of bird Pokemon and gulps the entire flock down whole.
flavor_text_4: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.
flavor_text_5: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.
flavor_text_6: It flies at the speed of sound while searching for prey, and it has midair battles with Salamence as the two compete for food.
flavor_text_7: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.
flavor_text_8: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
flavor_text_9: Garchomp is fast both underground and above. It can bring down prey and return to its den before its body has chilled from being outside.
flavor_text_10: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

name: munchlax
flavor_text_0: Stuffing itself with vast amounts of food is its only concern. Whether the food is rotten or fresh, yummy or tasteless--it does not care.
flavor_text_1: It hides food under its long fur, but it sometimes forgets about it and causes a stinky disturbance.
flavor_text_2: Anything that looks edible, Munchlax will go on and swallow whole. Its stomach is tough enough to handle it even if the food has gone rotten.
