flavor_text_3: When it finds something that looks like it might be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it whole. That's why it gets fatter day by day.
flavor_text_4: It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned, it's indifferent.
flavor_text_5: In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.
flavor_text_6: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.
flavor_text_7: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.
flavor_text_8: It stores food beneath its fur. It might share just one bite, but only if it really trusts you.
flavor_text_9: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.
flavor_text_10: Its robust stomach allows it to nonchalantly devour even rotted matter. It pays frequent visits to villages, seeking out food scraps intended for compost.

name: riolu
flavor_text_0: It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokemon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.
flavor_text_1: It's tough enough to run right through the night, and it's also a hard worker, but it's still just a youngster.
flavor_text_2: Its body is lithe yet powerful. It can crest three mountains and cross two canyons in one night.
flavor_text_3: It knows how people and Pokemon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn't approach dangerous opponents.
flavor_text_4: It uses waves called auras to communicate with others of its kind. It doesn't make any noise during this time, so its enemies can't detect it.
flavor_text_5: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.
flavor_text_6: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.
flavor_text_7: Though infantile in appearance, it has the mysterious ability to read the minds of humans. The pure of heart are met with Riolu's approval, while those of ill nature earn only its loathing.
flavor_text_8: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.
flavor_text_9: It can use waves called auras to gauge how others are feeling. These same waves can also tell this Pokemon about the state of the environment.
flavor_text_10: It uses the shapes of auras, which change according to emotion, to communicate with others.
flavor_text_11: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: lucario
flavor_text_0: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.
flavor_text_1: They can detect the species of a living being-- and its emotions--from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.
flavor_text_2: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.
flavor_text_3: A most gallant-looking creature. It emits energy waves and controls them with precision, using them to sense even faraway beings. I have given the name "aura" to this power.
flavor_text_4: It's said that no foe can remain invisible to LUCARIO, since it can detect auras. Even foes it could not otherwise see.
flavor_text_5: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
flavor_text_6: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.
flavor_text_7: Lucario reads its opponent's feelings with its aura waves. It finds out things it would rather not know, so it gets stressed out easily.
flavor_text_8: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.
flavor_text_9: It can tell what people are thinking. Only Trainers who have justice in their hearts can earn this Pokemon's trust.
flavor_text_10: It concentrates its mental energy and fires off mysterious waves called auras, which can crush boulders of large size to dust.
flavor_text_11: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.

name: hippopotas
flavor_text_0: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.
flavor_text_1: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.
flavor_text_2: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.
flavor_text_3: Though large and languid, Hippopotas is difficult to detect due to its tendency to burrow into and lurk beneath the soil. When agitated or excited, it expels sand from its nostrils.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is active during the day and passes the cold desert nights burrowed snugly into the sand.
flavor_text_5: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.
flavor_text_6: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.
flavor_text_7: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

name: hippowdon
flavor_text_0: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.
flavor_text_1: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.
flavor_text_3: Its huge mouth is almost seven feet across. It has enough power to completely crush a car.
flavor_text_4: When roused to violence by its rage, it spews out the quantities of sand it has swallowed and whips up a sandstorm.
flavor_text_5: Short-tempered and easily moved to violence. It whips up whirlwinds of sand to crush its foes' spirits, then goes in for the attack.
flavor_text_6: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

name: skorupi
flavor_text_0: Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokemon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.
flavor_text_1: As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.
flavor_text_2: It lives in arid regions and can go without food for a year while waiting for prey.
flavor_text_3: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
flavor_text_4: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.
flavor_text_5: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokemon and Sizzlipede share common descent.
flavor_text_6: It attacks using the claws on its tail. Once locked in its grip, its prey is unable to move as this Pokemon's poison seeps in.
flavor_text_7: It lives in arid lands. It buries itself in sand and lies in wait for unsuspecting prey.

name: drapion
flavor_text_0: Its body is encased in a sturdy shell. Its head rotates 180 degrees, eliminating blind spots.
flavor_text_1: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokemon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.
flavor_text_2: Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.
flavor_text_3: It attacks people and Pokemon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.
flavor_text_4: Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.
flavor_text_5: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.
flavor_text_6: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.
flavor_text_7: It's so vicious that it's called the Sand Demon. Yet when confronted by Hippowdon, Drapion keeps a low profile and will never pick a fight.

name: croagunk
flavor_text_0: Fluid squeezed from its finger, albeit poisonous, is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower-back pain.
flavor_text_1: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.
flavor_text_2: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
flavor_text_3: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.
flavor_text_4: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
flavor_text_5: Fluid squeezed from its finger, albeit poisonous, is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower back pain.
flavor_text_6: It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.
flavor_text_7: Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokemon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.
flavor_text_8: A poison wielder with a dastardly personality. Despite such qualities, this species is afforded a measure of popularity due to its peculiar cry and comical features.

name: toxicroak
flavor_text_0: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.
flavor_text_1: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.
flavor_text_2: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.
flavor_text_3: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
flavor_text_4: Its crimson claws contain a virulent toxin. This toxin can be made into a tonic by diluting it, mixing it with several types of wild grass, and boiling it down over two days.
flavor_text_5: It booms out a victory croak when its prey goes down in defeat. This Pokemon and Seismitoad are related species.
flavor_text_6: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.
flavor_text_7: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: carnivine
flavor_text_0: It walks around on its tentacles in search of a tree branch where it can dangle down and ambush prey.
flavor_text_1: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
flavor_text_2: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
flavor_text_3: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling drool and gulps them down.
flavor_text_4: Hanging from branches using its tentacles, it looks like a plant. It awaits prey, mouth wide open.
flavor_text_5: Though this is a plant Pokemon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.
flavor_text_6: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
flavor_text_7: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.

name: finneon
flavor_text_0: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
flavor_text_1: Swimming and fluttering its two tail fins, it looks like a BEAUTIFLY. At night, the patterns on its tail fins softly shine.
flavor_text_2: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.
flavor_text_3: What a gorgeous sight this Pokemon is as it swims with its long, pink-painted caudal fins fluttering behind it. Finneon's beautiful appearance has led to its nickname: "finery fish."
flavor_text_4: The way its two tail fins flutter while it swims has earned it the nickname "BEAUTIFLY of the Sea."
flavor_text_5: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.
flavor_text_6: Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps. When it breaks the surface of the sea, Wingull swoop down to grab it on the fly.
flavor_text_7: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.
flavor_text_8: When night falls, their pink patterns begin to shine. They're popular with divers, so there are resorts that feed them to keep them close.

name: lumineon
flavor_text_0: LUMINEON swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.
flavor_text_1: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokemon--its natural predators.
flavor_text_2: Deep down at the bottom of the ocean, prey is scarce. Lumineon get into fierce disputes with Lanturn over food.
flavor_text_3: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with LANTURN.
flavor_text_4: This deep-sea Pokemon lives at the bottom of the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in search of its favorite food--Starmie.
flavor_text_5: Uses its gleaming fins to hunt its prey. The view of Lumineon schooling near the surface of the sea at night is breathtaking-- it's as though there were shining stars right there.
flavor_text_6: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.
flavor_text_7: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.
flavor_text_8: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.
flavor_text_9: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with Lanturn.

name: mantyke
flavor_text_0: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.
flavor_text_1: A friendly Pokemon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.
flavor_text_2: Mantyke are friendly toward people and will approach boats closely. The patterns on their backs differ depending on their habitat.
flavor_text_3: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.
flavor_text_4: People organize tours to see this Pokemon frolic and skim the tops of waves with Remoraid.
flavor_text_5: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of Remoraid.
flavor_text_6: Scientists discovered that the distinctive patterns on its back differ by region.
flavor_text_7: It's highly friendly and easily tamed. Tours that take people swimming with Mantyke are a super-popular beach activity.
flavor_text_8: People organize tours to see this Pokemon frolic and skim the tops of waves with REMORAID.
flavor_text_9: It swims along with a school of Remoraid, and they'll all fight together to repel attackers.
flavor_text_10: Though ball-like in shape, this Pokemon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.

name: snover
flavor_text_0: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.
flavor_text_1: One is likely to encounter this Pokemon while out in the snow. There are stories of Snover appearing in human settlements but doing no harm--rather, they bond with the children.
flavor_text_2: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
flavor_text_3: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.
flavor_text_4: The berries that grow around its belly are like ice pops. Galarian Darumaka absolutely love these berries.
flavor_text_5: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.
flavor_text_6: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

name: abomasnow
flavor_text_0: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.
flavor_text_1: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
flavor_text_2: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.
flavor_text_4: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
flavor_text_5: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.
flavor_text_6: A powerful Pokemon that can split huge boulders with ease. Dislikes associating with others and chooses to live quietly deep within the mountains, playing with the snow.

name: weavile
flavor_text_0: One Weavile will trip a Sandshrew and flip it over, and then another Weavile will deal the finishing blow with its sharp claws.
flavor_text_1: It sends signals to others by carving odd patterns in frost- covered trees and ice.
flavor_text_2: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
flavor_text_3: Thanks to its increased intelligence, scrapping over food is a thing of the past. A scratch from its claws will give you a case of frostbite!
flavor_text_4: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.
flavor_text_5: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
flavor_text_6: They dwell in cold places. This Pokemon's main food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew, which they carefully divide among their group.
flavor_text_7: This species corners prey as a pack, under the guidance of a leader. Weavile displays increased cunning, leading me to speculate that its evolution caused further brain development.
flavor_text_8: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.
flavor_text_9: With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.
flavor_text_10: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.
flavor_text_11: They communicate by clawing signs in boulders and work together to surround enemies.

name: magnezone
flavor_text_0: A group tried to use scientific means to make MAGNEZONE evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.
flavor_text_1: I theorize that a special magnetic field influenced this Pokemon, changing its molecular structure and causing it to evolve. It emits strange radio waves toward space from its antenna.
flavor_text_2: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.
flavor_text_3: A group tried to use scientific means to make Magnezone evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.
flavor_text_4: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.
flavor_text_5: It's thought that a special magnetic field changed the molecular structure of this Pokemon's body, and that's what caused the Pokemon's evolution.
flavor_text_6: It uses radar to monitor its territory. Intruders are quickly disposed of with a hyper beam.
flavor_text_7: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed MAGNETON's molecular structure, turning it into MAGNEZONE.
flavor_text_8: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokemon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.
flavor_text_9: There are still people who believe that this Pokemon came from outer space. It emanates a powerful magnetic field.
flavor_text_10: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.
flavor_text_11: Three units generate magnetism. There have been many mistaken reports of UFO sightings when Magnezone flies through the night sky.

name: lickilicky
flavor_text_0: It has space in its throat to store saliva. It can also roll up its tongue and store it in the same spot.
flavor_text_1: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.
flavor_text_2: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.
flavor_text_3: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue, which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast, Lickilicky's use of its fingers is clumsy.
flavor_text_4: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
flavor_text_5: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.
flavor_text_6: Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky's height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.
flavor_text_7: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.
flavor_text_8: A contest is under way to determine which one can stick its tongue out the farthest. The current record is...more than 82 feet.
flavor_text_9: Its saliva can decompose anything. It wraps its long tongue around things to coat them with its sticky saliva.

name: rhyperior
flavor_text_0: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.
flavor_text_1: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.
flavor_text_2: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.
flavor_text_3: From holes in its palms, it fires out GEODUDE. Its carapace  can withstand volcanic eruptions.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.
flavor_text_5: It relies on its carapace to deflect incoming attacks and throw its enemy off balance. As soon as that happens, it drives its drill into the foe.
flavor_text_6: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.
flavor_text_7: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

name: tangrowth
flavor_text_0: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokemon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.
flavor_text_1: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.
flavor_text_2: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.
flavor_text_3: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.
flavor_text_4: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.
flavor_text_5: When it remains still, it appears to be a large shrub. Unsuspecting prey that wander near get ensnared by its vines.
flavor_text_6: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.
flavor_text_7: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: electivire
flavor_text_0: It grips its tail, which spews electricity, and then beats down opponents with the power of its electrified fist.
flavor_text_1: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.
flavor_text_2: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.
flavor_text_3: In terms of electrical-energy output, Electivire is one of the best among all Electric Pokemon. It discharges high-voltage currents from its tails.
flavor_text_4: Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.
flavor_text_5: Heedless of enemy attacks, it closes in, shoves its tails onto the foe, then looses high voltage.
flavor_text_6: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.
flavor_text_7: The instant it presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent, it sends over 20,000 volts of electricity into the foe.
flavor_text_8: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.
flavor_text_9: When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.
flavor_text_10: The amount of electrical energy this Pokemon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: magmortar
flavor_text_0: When shooting 3,600 degree F fireballs from its arms, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.
flavor_text_1: Use of a strange item caused this Pokemon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.
flavor_text_2: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: Living in the crater of a volcano has caused this Pokemon's body to resemble its environment-- it has an organ similar to a magma chamber.
flavor_text_4: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
flavor_text_5: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.
flavor_text_6: From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.
flavor_text_7: They dwell in volcanic craters. According to what is known, a single pair of male and female Magmortar lives in one volcano.
flavor_text_8: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.
flavor_text_9: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
flavor_text_10: When launching 3,600 degrees F fireballs, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.
flavor_text_11: There are still quite a few factories that rely on the flames provided by Magmortar to process metals.

name: togekiss
flavor_text_0: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.
flavor_text_1: Known as a bringer of blessings, it's been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.
flavor_text_2: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.
flavor_text_3: These Pokemon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they've hardly been seen at all.
flavor_text_4: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.
flavor_text_5: Scant few have ever sighted this Pokemon. After studying what literature remains, I am certain Togekiss will reveal itself when peace reigns in the land.

name: yanmega
flavor_text_0: Extremely violent. When hunting, it wastes none of its energy, aiming only for prey's most vulnerable spots. Any who manage to tame this Pokemon must be of incredible bravery.
flavor_text_1: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
flavor_text_2: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.
flavor_text_3: The beat of its wings is so powerful that it accidentally dislodges full-grown trees when it takes off in flight.
flavor_text_4: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.
flavor_text_5: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: leafeon
flavor_text_0: Although it doesn't like disputes, it will sharpen the leaf on its tail into a blade and fight if it has to protect its friends.
flavor_text_1: Its cellular composition is closer to that of a plant than an animal. It uses photosynthesis to produce its energy supply without eating food.
flavor_text_2: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.
flavor_text_3: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.
flavor_text_4: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokemon's leaves. There's a popular perfume made using that scent.
flavor_text_5: It gets its nutrition from photosynthesis. It lives a quiet life deep in forests where clean rivers flow.
flavor_text_6: With cells similar to those of plants, it performs photosynthesis inside its body and creates pure air.
flavor_text_7: Cells similar to those of plants have been found in its fur. Its hard tail can fell a large tree with one stroke, and the tail's sharpness exceeds even that of a sword crafted by a master.
flavor_text_8: When you see LEAFEON asleep in a patch of sunshine, you'll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.
flavor_text_9: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.
flavor_text_10: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you'll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.
flavor_text_11: This Pokemon's tail is blade sharp, with a fantastic cutting edge that can slice right though large trees.

name: glaceon
flavor_text_0: It protects itself by freezing its fur into sharp needles. It can drop its body temperature below -75 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: It can instantaneously freeze any moisture that's around it, creating ice pellets to shoot at its prey.
flavor_text_2: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.
flavor_text_3: Any who become captivated by the beauty of the snowfall that Glaceon creates will be frozen before they know it.
flavor_text_4: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.
flavor_text_5: It causes small ice crystals to form by lowering the temperature of the surrounding atmosphere.
flavor_text_6: Glaceon is able to lower its body temperature very quickly. It freezes the atmosphere, creating diamond dust that glitters like gems while it flutters and dances around.
flavor_text_7: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form, making it quite a popular Pokemon at ski resorts.
flavor_text_8: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.
flavor_text_9: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
flavor_text_10: It freezes its fur into icicles, spiky and sharp, and tackles its prey.

name: gliscor
flavor_text_0: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.
flavor_text_1: It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.
flavor_text_2: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
flavor_text_3: It dances silently through the sky. When it approaches prey, it can land a critical hit in an instant.
flavor_text_4: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: mamoswine
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.
flavor_text_1: It looks strong, and that's exactly what it is. As the weather grows colder, its ice tusks grow longer, thicker, and more impressive.
flavor_text_2: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.
flavor_text_3: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokemon has been around a long, long, long time.
flavor_text_4: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui's frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine's constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
flavor_text_5: A frozen MAMOSWINE was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokemon has been around a long, long, long time.
flavor_text_6: When the temperature rose at the end of the ice age, most Mamoswine disappeared.
flavor_text_7: It flourished worldwide during the ice age but its population declined when the masses of ice began to dwindle.
flavor_text_8: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.

name: porygon-z
flavor_text_0: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.
flavor_text_1: In order to create a more advanced Pokemon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.
flavor_text_2: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.
flavor_text_3: Its program was modified to facilitate extra-dimensional activities, but that led to noticeably strange behavior.
flavor_text_4: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokemon. It began acting oddly, however.
flavor_text_5: A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokemon's offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.
flavor_text_6: Its behavior is noticeably unstable, which is apparently due to the incompetence of the engineer who updated its programming.
flavor_text_7: Some say an additional program made this Pokemon evolve, but even academics can't agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.
flavor_text_8: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.
flavor_text_9: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

name: gallade
flavor_text_0: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
flavor_text_1: Sharply attuned to others' wishes for help, this Pokemon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.
flavor_text_2: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.
flavor_text_3: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
flavor_text_4: The blades extending from its elbows are sharper than the finest swords. Its swordsmanship, albeit self-taught, is astonishingly impressive.
flavor_text_5: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.

name: probopass
flavor_text_0: The main body controls three mobile units called Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.
flavor_text_1: It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.
flavor_text_2: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.
flavor_text_3: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.
flavor_text_4: It freely controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
flavor_text_5: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.
flavor_text_6: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack the foe from three directions.
flavor_text_7: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
flavor_text_8: Although it can control its units known as Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don't come back.

name: dusknoir
flavor_text_0: With the mouth on its belly, Dusknoir swallows its target whole. The soul is the only thing eaten-- Dusknoir disgorges the body before departing.
flavor_text_1: Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.
flavor_text_2: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokemon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.
flavor_text_3: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.
flavor_text_4: This feared Pokemon is said to travel to worlds unknown. Some even believe that it takes lost spirits along with it.
flavor_text_5: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

name: froslass
flavor_text_0: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
flavor_text_1: When it finds humans or Pokemon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.
flavor_text_2: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as FROSLASS
flavor_text_3: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.
flavor_text_4: It spits out cold air of nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon inhabited by the soul of a woman who died bearing a grudge in the snowy mountains. Legends of Froslass placing deathly curses on misbehaving men send shivers down my spine.
flavor_text_6: The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokemon. The food it most relishes is the souls of men.
flavor_text_7: After a woman met her end on a snowy mountain, her regrets lingered on. From them, this Pokemon was born. Its favorite food is frozen souls.
flavor_text_8: It's said that on nights of terrible blizzards, it comes down to human settlements. If you hear it knocking at your door, do not open it!
flavor_text_9: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as FROSLASS.
flavor_text_10: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.
flavor_text_11: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.
flavor_text_12: It freezes hikers who have come to climb snowy mountains and carries them back to its home. It only goes after men it thinks are handsome.

name: rotom
flavor_text_0: Research continues on this Pokemon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
flavor_text_1: This bizarre Pokemon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.
flavor_text_2: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
flavor_text_3: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.
flavor_text_4: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.
flavor_text_5: With a body made of plasma, it can inhabit all sorts of machines. It loves to surprise others.

name: uxie
flavor_text_0: When UXIE flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.
flavor_text_1: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.
flavor_text_2: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
flavor_text_3: A Pokemon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.
flavor_text_4: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.
flavor_text_5: According to some sources, this Pokemon provided people with the intelligence necessary to solve various problems.

name: mesprit
flavor_text_0: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
flavor_text_1: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.
flavor_text_2: Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokemon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.
flavor_text_3: When MESPRIT flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is said to have endowed the human heart with emotions, such as sorrow and joy.
flavor_text_5: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

name: azelf
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon is said to have endowed humans with the determination needed to face any of life's difficulties.
flavor_text_1: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
flavor_text_2: It is thought that UXIE, MESPRIT and AZELF all came from the same egg.
flavor_text_3: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.
flavor_text_4: When AZELF flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.
flavor_text_5: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.
flavor_text_6: The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokemon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.

name: dialga
flavor_text_0: A Pokemon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.
flavor_text_1: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga's heart beats.
flavor_text_2: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when DIALGA was born.
flavor_text_6: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when DIALGA's heart beats.

name: palkia
flavor_text_0: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
flavor_text_1: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with PALKIA's every breath.
flavor_text_2: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.
flavor_text_3: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia's every breath.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.
flavor_text_5: Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.

name: heatran
flavor_text_0: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.
flavor_text_1: Stories tell of this Pokemon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.
flavor_text_2: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.
flavor_text_3: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

name: regigigas
flavor_text_0: According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.
flavor_text_1: All over the world, there are legends that tell of Regigigas creating other Pokemon in its own image.
flavor_text_2: It is believed to have shaped REGIROCK, REGICE, and REGISTEEL out of clay, ice, and magma.
flavor_text_3: It's said that Regigigas created other Pokemon from many different materials before it moved the continents to where they are today.
flavor_text_4: It is said to have made Pokemon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
flavor_text_5: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokemon towed continents with ropes.

name: giratina
flavor_text_0: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
flavor_text_1: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
flavor_text_3: A Pokemon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: cresselia
flavor_text_0: Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.
flavor_text_1: Those who sleep holding CRESSELIA's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
flavor_text_2: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.
flavor_text_3: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
flavor_text_4: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: phione
flavor_text_0: A Pokemon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.
flavor_text_1: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
flavor_text_2: Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters--logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.
flavor_text_3: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: manaphy
flavor_text_0: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: Water makes up 80% of its body. This Pokemon is easily affected by its environment.
flavor_text_3: Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui's coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.
flavor_text_4: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: darkrai
flavor_text_0: It chases people and Pokemon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.
flavor_text_1: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village's inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.
flavor_text_2: To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.
flavor_text_3: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.
flavor_text_4: Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokemon will make people see horrific nightmares.

name: shaymin
flavor_text_0: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.
flavor_text_1: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.
flavor_text_2: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.
flavor_text_3: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
flavor_text_4: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
flavor_text_5: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings  of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: arceus
flavor_text_0: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokemon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.
flavor_text_1: It is told in mythology that this Pokemon was born before the universe even existed.
flavor_text_2: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing then shaped the world.
flavor_text_3: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.
flavor_text_4: It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokemon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.
flavor_text_5: It is described in mythology as the Pokemon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

name: victini
flavor_text_0: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.
flavor_text_1: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: snivy
flavor_text_0: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
flavor_text_1: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.
flavor_text_2: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: servine
flavor_text_0: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
flavor_text_1: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.
flavor_text_2: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: serperior
flavor_text_0: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
flavor_text_1: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.
flavor_text_2: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.

name: tepig
flavor_text_0: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.
flavor_text_1: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.
flavor_text_2: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

name: pignite
flavor_text_0: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.
flavor_text_1: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.
flavor_text_2: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: emboar
flavor_text_0: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
flavor_text_1: A flaring beard of fire is proof that it is fired up. It is adept at using many different moves.
flavor_text_2: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: oshawott
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I've conferred upon this shell the name "scalchop".
flavor_text_1: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.
flavor_text_2: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.
flavor_text_3: The scalchop on its stomach isn't just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

name: dewott
flavor_text_0: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.
flavor_text_1: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.
flavor_text_2: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.
flavor_text_3: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: samurott
flavor_text_0: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
flavor_text_1: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.
flavor_text_2: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.
flavor_text_3: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokemon's evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

name: patrat
flavor_text_0: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.
flavor_text_1: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.
flavor_text_2: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: watchog
flavor_text_0: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.
flavor_text_1: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.
flavor_text_2: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: lillipup
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won't forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.
flavor_text_1: Though it is a very brave Pokemon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.
flavor_text_2: Because it doesn't yelp, it's extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is popular with beginners because it's intelligent, obedient to its Trainer's commands, and easy to raise.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.
flavor_text_5: The long fur surrounding its face functions as radar, enabling it to probe the condition of its battle opponents.
flavor_text_6: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.
flavor_text_7: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokemon flees.
flavor_text_8: This Pokemon has excellent judgment. If it decides it can't defeat an opponent, it immediately turns tail and vamooses.

name: herdier
flavor_text_0: Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed makes this a troublesome Pokemon to train.
flavor_text_1: This very loyal Pokemon helps Trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.
flavor_text_3: The longer its black fur grows, the harder and more impervious it gets. Claws and fangs can't easily penetrate it.
flavor_text_4: It loyally follows its Trainer's orders. For ages, they have helped Trainers raise Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon obeys its master's orders faithfully. However, it refuses to listen to anything said by a person it doesn't respect.
flavor_text_6: It has been living with people for so long that portrayals of it can be found on the walls of caves from long, long ago.
flavor_text_7: The black fur that covers this Pokemon's body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.
flavor_text_8: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokemon. So much so that there's a theory that Herdier was the first Pokemon to partner with people.

name: stoutland
flavor_text_0: Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it's a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.
flavor_text_1: Its fur is long and thick. A long time ago in cold regions, every household kept a Stoutland.
flavor_text_2: This extremely wise Pokemon excels at rescuing people stranded at sea or in the mountains.
flavor_text_3: With this wise Pokemon, there could be no concern that it would ever attack people. Some parents even trust it to babysit.
flavor_text_4: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It's said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.
flavor_text_5: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.
flavor_text_6: These Pokemon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.
flavor_text_7: It pays no mind to the cold, thanks to its long warm coat. Stoutland in Alola look a little uncomfortable.
flavor_text_8: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: purrloin
flavor_text_0: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.
flavor_text_1: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokemon and Nickit.
flavor_text_2: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.
flavor_text_3: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.
flavor_text_4: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

name: liepard
flavor_text_0: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.
flavor_text_3: This stealthy Pokemon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
flavor_text_4: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

name: pansage
flavor_text_0: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokemon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.
flavor_text_2: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

name: simisage
flavor_text_0: It strikes its enemies with a thorn-covered tail. The leaf on its head is bitter.
flavor_text_1: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokemon is wild tempered.
flavor_text_2: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: pansear
flavor_text_0: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600deg F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.
flavor_text_1: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600deg F.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: simisear
flavor_text_0: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.
flavor_text_1: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
flavor_text_2: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: panpour
flavor_text_0: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.
flavor_text_1: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
flavor_text_2: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

name: simipour
flavor_text_0: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.
flavor_text_1: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.
flavor_text_2: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: munna
flavor_text_0: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.
flavor_text_1: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it's eating a good dream, and black when it's eating a nightmare.
flavor_text_2: Late at night, it appears beside people's pillows. As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.
flavor_text_3: It eats the dreams of people and Pokemon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon appears before people and Pokemon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

name: musharna
flavor_text_0: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.
flavor_text_1: It drowses and dreams all the time. It's best to leave it be if it's just woken up, as it's a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.
flavor_text_2: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: When dark mists emanate from its body, don't get too near. If you do, your nightmares will become reality.
flavor_text_4: With the mist from its forehead, it can create shapes of things from dreams it has eaten.

name: pidove
flavor_text_0: This very forgetful Pokemon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.
flavor_text_1: It's forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.
flavor_text_2: Each follows its Trainer's orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.
flavor_text_3: These Pokemon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.
flavor_text_4: Where people go, these Pokemon follow. If you're scattering food for them, be careful-- several hundred of them can gather at once.

name: tranquill
flavor_text_0: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.
flavor_text_1: These bright Pokemon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.
flavor_text_2: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
flavor_text_3: It can return to its Trainer's location regardless of the distance separating them.
flavor_text_4: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

name: unfezant
flavor_text_0: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.
flavor_text_1: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.
flavor_text_2: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is intelligent and intensely proud. People will sit up and take notice if you become the Trainer of one.
flavor_text_4: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: blitzle
flavor_text_0: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.
flavor_text_1: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.
flavor_text_2: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: zebstrika
flavor_text_0: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
flavor_text_1: When this ill-tempered Pokemon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.
flavor_text_2: This ill-tempered Pokemon is dangerous because when it's angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: roggenrola
flavor_text_0: The hexagonal hole is its ear. Deep in that ear is an energy core, so if you stick your hand in there, Roggenrola will be very angry!
flavor_text_1: The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.
flavor_text_2: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokemon slightly warm to the touch.
flavor_text_3: The hexagonal-shaped hole is its ear. It has a tendency to walk in the direction the sound is coming from.
flavor_text_4: Born deep within the ground, it compares itself with similar species, such as Geodude and Carbink, to settle which has the hardest body.
flavor_text_5: It was found in a fissure in a layer of exposed rock. The material that makes up its body is dirt from several hundred years ago.
flavor_text_6: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.
flavor_text_7: It's as hard as steel, but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.
flavor_text_8: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: boldore
flavor_text_0: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.
flavor_text_1: The energy overflowing from its body has turned into orange crystals that are hard enough to smash diamonds.
flavor_text_2: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.
flavor_text_3: If you see its orange crystals start to glow, be wary. It's about to fire off bursts of energy.
flavor_text_4: It relies on sound in order to monitor what's in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it's facing.
flavor_text_5: Its orange crystal is a mass of energy. Just one crystal fragment would provide enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.
flavor_text_6: Its orange crystals are lumps of powerful energy. They're valuable, so Boldore is sometimes targeted for them.
flavor_text_7: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.
flavor_text_8: It explores caves in search of underground water. It's not comfortable around water, so this Pokemon takes great care in lapping it up.

name: gigalith
flavor_text_0: This hardy Pokemon can often be found on construction sites and in mines, working alongside people and Copperajah.
flavor_text_1: The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it's not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.
flavor_text_2: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.
flavor_text_3: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.
flavor_text_4: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation-- they can only be fired when the sun is out.
flavor_text_5: Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokemon is a popular partner for construction workers.
flavor_text_6: It absorbs rays of sunlight and shoots out energy. It's usually lurking deep beneath the surface.
flavor_text_7: The solar energy absorbed by its body's orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.
flavor_text_8: When it fires off energy with all its might, the power creates countless fissures on its body.

name: woobat
flavor_text_0: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey--bug Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.
flavor_text_2: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.
flavor_text_3: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.
flavor_text_4: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it's evidence that Woobat live there.

name: swoobat
flavor_text_0: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.
flavor_text_1: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
flavor_text_2: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won't be able to fly for a little while.
flavor_text_3: The auspicious shape of this Pokemon's nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
flavor_text_4: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: drilbur
flavor_text_0: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.
flavor_text_1: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.
flavor_text_2: It's a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.
flavor_text_3: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.
flavor_text_4: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

name: excadrill
flavor_text_0: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
flavor_text_1: Known as the Drill King, this Pokemon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.
flavor_text_2: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.
flavor_text_3: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.
flavor_text_4: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.

name: audino
flavor_text_0: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.
flavor_text_1: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
flavor_text_2: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
flavor_text_3: Audino's sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino's ears.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures' feelings and physical conditions.

name: timburr
flavor_text_0: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.
flavor_text_1: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.
flavor_text_2: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.
flavor_text_3: These Pokemon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.
flavor_text_4: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

name: gurdurr
flavor_text_0: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.
flavor_text_1: Gurdurr excels at demolition--construction is not its forte. In any case, there's skill in the way this Pokemon wields its metal beam.
flavor_text_2: It shows off its muscles to Machoke and other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the other Pokemon, it lies low for a little while.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.
flavor_text_4: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.

name: conkeldurr
flavor_text_0: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
flavor_text_1: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.
flavor_text_2: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.
flavor_text_3: When going all out, this Pokemon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.
flavor_text_4: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

name: tympole
flavor_text_0: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.
flavor_text_1: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokemon species can't hear its cries of warning.
flavor_text_2: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.
flavor_text_3: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.
flavor_text_4: Graceful ripples running across the water's surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.

name: palpitoad
flavor_text_0: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.
flavor_text_1: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.
flavor_text_2: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.
flavor_text_3: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.
flavor_text_4: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

name: seismitoad
flavor_text_0: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
flavor_text_1: By putting power into its bumps, it creates vibrations and increases the power of its punches.
flavor_text_2: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.
flavor_text_3: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.

name: throh
flavor_text_0: They train in groups of five. Any member that can't keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.
flavor_text_1: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.
flavor_text_2: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh's belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer's sweat.
flavor_text_3: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.
flavor_text_4: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

name: sawk
flavor_text_0: The karate chops of a Sawk that's trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.
flavor_text_1: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.
flavor_text_2: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
flavor_text_3: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it's best to quietly pass by.
flavor_text_4: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

name: sewaddle
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
flavor_text_1: Since this Pokemon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
flavor_text_2: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: swadloon
flavor_text_0: Preferring dark, damp places, it spends the entire day eating fallen leaves that lie around it.
flavor_text_1: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
flavor_text_2: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: leavanny
flavor_text_0: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
flavor_text_1: Upon finding a small Pokemon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.
flavor_text_2: Upon finding a small Pokemon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: venipede
flavor_text_0: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokemon that try to prey on it.
flavor_text_1: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.
flavor_text_2: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokemon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.
