flavor_text_3: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey's location and state.
flavor_text_4: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: whirlipede
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.
flavor_text_1: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it'll need for evolution.
flavor_text_2: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.
flavor_text_3: Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.
flavor_text_4: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: scolipede
flavor_text_0: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.
flavor_text_1: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws' toxic spikes.
flavor_text_2: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.
flavor_text_3: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.
flavor_text_4: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.

name: cottonee
flavor_text_0: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that's highly prized by many luxury brands.
flavor_text_1: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.
flavor_text_2: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.
flavor_text_3: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.
flavor_text_4: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.
flavor_text_5: Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy, light and airy-- altogether top quality.
flavor_text_6: When attacked, it expels cotton from its body to create a diversion. The cotton it loses grows back in quickly.
flavor_text_7: When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.
flavor_text_8: To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can't move as well.

name: whimsicott
flavor_text_0: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.
flavor_text_1: Whimsicott doesn't live in a fixed location. It floats around on whirling winds, appearing all over the place to perform its mischief.
flavor_text_2: As long as this Pokemon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.
flavor_text_3: It rides on the wind and slips into people's homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton- filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.
flavor_text_4: This nuisance sneaks into people's homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.
flavor_text_5: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.
flavor_text_6: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon appears, riding upon the wind. But if the wind gusts up, it'll blow the cotton on this Pokemon's head clean off.
flavor_text_8: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokemon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

name: petilil
flavor_text_0: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.
flavor_text_1: Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness--even more so when boiled.
flavor_text_2: By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokemon can be grown into a fine plump shape.
flavor_text_3: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.
flavor_text_4: They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area.
flavor_text_5: The deeper the color of a Petilil's leaves, the healthier the Pokemon is. Petilil sometimes makes its home in a well-tended field or flowerbed.
flavor_text_6: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.
flavor_text_7: Some say if you dry the leaves on its head, boil them down, and drink the infusion, your vigor will return, so Petilil is popular with the elderly.
flavor_text_8: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.
flavor_text_9: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokemon's head results in a liquid that's sometimes used as a bug repellent.

name: lilligant
flavor_text_0: As soon as it finds a male to be its partner, the beautiful flower on its head darkens, droops, and withers away.
flavor_text_1: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.
flavor_text_2: Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they're also staggeringly expensive.
flavor_text_3: It's well liked by other Pokemon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.
flavor_text_4: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.
flavor_text_5: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokemon is popular with celebrities.
flavor_text_6: It's believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant's head to bloom.
flavor_text_7: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.
flavor_text_8: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
flavor_text_9: The fragrance of its flower differs slightly depending on the soil where it grew up. Sniffing the aroma calms your heart and mind.

name: basculin
flavor_text_0: In the past, it often appeared on the dinner table. The meat of red-striped Basculin is on the fatty side, and it's more popular with the youth.
flavor_text_1: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor--this one is gentle--I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
flavor_text_2: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.
flavor_text_3: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they'll start fighting instantly. These Pokemon are very hostile.
flavor_text_4: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.
flavor_text_5: When a school of Basculin appears in a lake, everything else disappears, except for Corphish and Crawdaunt. That's how violent Basculin are.
flavor_text_6: Savage, violent Pokemon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.
flavor_text_7: Anglers love the fight this Pokemon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch-- many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: sandile
flavor_text_0: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
flavor_text_1: Alola, where it's warm all year round, is a comfortable environment for this Pokemon. Sometimes you'll even see it outside of deserts.
flavor_text_2: Sandile's still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It's called "the cleaner of the desert."
flavor_text_3: The desert gets cold at night, so when the sun sets, this Pokemon burrows deep into the sand and sleeps until sunrise.
flavor_text_4: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.
flavor_text_5: Sandile is small, but its legs and lower body are powerful. Pushing sand aside as it goes, Sandile moves through the desert as if it's swimming.
flavor_text_6: It conceals itself in the sand and chomps down on the legs of any prey that unwarily walk over it. Its favorite food is Trapinch.
flavor_text_7: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.
flavor_text_8: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

name: krokorok
flavor_text_0: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.
flavor_text_1: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.
flavor_text_2: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.
flavor_text_3: Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost.
flavor_text_4: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.
flavor_text_5: Krokorok really hates it when its body gets cold. On nights when the temperature drops, it digs deep into the desert sands.
flavor_text_6: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.
flavor_text_7: They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.
flavor_text_8: Although this Pokemon has specialized eyes that allow it to see in the dark, Krokorok won't move much at night--the desert gets cold after sunset.

name: krookodile
flavor_text_0: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.
flavor_text_1: While terribly aggressive, Krookodile also has the patience to stay hidden under sand for days, lying in wait for prey.
flavor_text_2: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.
flavor_text_3: When it spots prey, even at a distance of over 30 miles, it swims through the desert as if it were water, then jumps out and chomps them.
flavor_text_4: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
flavor_text_5: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.
flavor_text_6: This Pokemon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile's mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.
flavor_text_7: Very violent Pokemon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.
flavor_text_8: After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

name: darumaka
flavor_text_0: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokemon will immediately fall asleep.
flavor_text_1: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it's pushed or pulled.
flavor_text_2: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.
flavor_text_4: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100deg F.
flavor_text_5: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

name: darmanitan
flavor_text_0: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokemon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.
flavor_text_1: Its internal fire burns at 2,500deg F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_2: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_3: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
flavor_text_4: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: maractus
flavor_text_0: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokemon and making them fly off in a hurry.
flavor_text_1: When it moves rhythmically, it makes a sound similar to maracas, making the surprised Pokemon flee.
flavor_text_2: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokemon that prey on its flower seeds.
flavor_text_3: Once each year, this Pokemon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.
flavor_text_4: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

name: dwebble
flavor_text_0: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.
flavor_text_1: When it finds a stone appealing, it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokemon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.
flavor_text_2: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.
flavor_text_4: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokemon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

name: crustle
flavor_text_0: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.
flavor_text_1: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.
flavor_text_2: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.
flavor_text_3: This highly territorial Pokemon prefers dry climates. It won't come out of its boulder on rainy days.
flavor_text_4: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.

name: scraggy
flavor_text_0: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: It protects itself with its durable skin. It's thought that this Pokemon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.
flavor_text_2: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.
flavor_text_3: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.
flavor_text_4: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.
flavor_text_5: They move in small groups, walking around lazily. Anyone who makes eye contact gets smacked with a headbutt.
flavor_text_6: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. The saggier their skin, the more respect they garner.

name: scrafty
flavor_text_0: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.
flavor_text_1: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.
flavor_text_2: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokemon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
flavor_text_3: As halfhearted as this Pokemon's kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr's concrete pillars.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon may be rude, but it takes very good care of its family, its friends, and its turf.
flavor_text_5: It taunts its opponents by spitting. It has a certain territory that it never leaves its whole life long.
flavor_text_6: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.

name: sigilyph
flavor_text_0: Psychic power allows these Pokemon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.
flavor_text_1: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.
flavor_text_2: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.
flavor_text_3: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.
flavor_text_4: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

name: yamask
flavor_text_0: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokemon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
flavor_text_1: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that's said to have been the face it had when it was still human.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.
flavor_text_3: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
flavor_text_4: These Pokemon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: cofagrigus
flavor_text_0: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.
flavor_text_1: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They're symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.
flavor_text_2: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.
flavor_text_4: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

name: tirtouga
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.
flavor_text_1: Its hunting grounds encompassed a broad area, from the land to more than half a mile deep in the ocean.
flavor_text_2: Reputed to be the ancestor of most turtle Pokemon, it lived in warm seas approximately a hundred million years ago.
flavor_text_3: About 100 million years ago, these Pokemon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.
flavor_text_4: It was restored from an ancient fossil. Tirtouga lived in the sea but came up onto the land to search for prey.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.
flavor_text_6: Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to ocean depths of over half a mile.
flavor_text_7: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokemon. It was restored to life from a fossil.
flavor_text_8: Restored from a fossil, this Pokemon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: carracosta
flavor_text_0: Incredible jaw strength enables them to chew up steel beams and rocks along with their prey.
flavor_text_1: Its jaws are terrifyingly powerful. It could eat Omastar and Omanyte whole and not be bothered in the slightest by their shells.
flavor_text_2: Carracosta eats every last bit of the prey it catches, even the shells and bones, to further strengthen its sturdy shell.
flavor_text_3: It constructed its sturdy shell by crunching and swallowing the hard shells or bones of its prey.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.
flavor_text_5: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.
flavor_text_6: Carracosta completely devours its prey--bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta's own shell grows thick and sturdy.
flavor_text_7: Active both on land and in the sea, this Pokemon drags its land-based prey into the water to finish it off.
flavor_text_8: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: archen
flavor_text_0: It is the ancestor of all bird Pokemon. Archen itself could not actually fly but moved by hopping from treetop to treetop.
flavor_text_1: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokemon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.
flavor_text_2: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it's very good at jumping.
flavor_text_4: Revived from a fossil, this Pokemon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: To all appearances flightless, it was able to glide down from tall treetops to snag its prey.
flavor_text_6: Once thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokemon, some of the latest research suggests that may not be the case.
flavor_text_7: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokemon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokemon.
flavor_text_8: Restored from a fossil, this ancient bird Pokemon has wings but can't yet fly.

name: archeops
flavor_text_0: Although apparently able to fly, they tended to run along the ground, averaging speeds of roughly 25 mph.
flavor_text_1: They hunted in flocks. When one Archeops had the prey cornered, another would swoop on it.
flavor_text_2: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokemon, the muscles it uses to flap its wings are still weak, so it needs a long runway in order to take off.
flavor_text_3: This ancient Pokemon's plumage is delicate, so if anyone other than an experienced professional tries to restore it, they will fail.
flavor_text_4: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.
flavor_text_5: It runs better than it flies. It catches prey by running at speeds comparable to those of an automobile.
flavor_text_6: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.
flavor_text_7: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.
flavor_text_8: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.

name: trubbish
flavor_text_0: It gorges on trash until its stomach is full. Then it belches toxic gas. An unlucky whiff of gas will put a person in the hospital.
flavor_text_1: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokemon living in your room.
flavor_text_2: Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.
flavor_text_3: If a young Pokemon or child breathes in the toxic gas that Trubbish belches out, it could be a life-threatening situation.
flavor_text_4: Poisonous gas leaks out of it when it breathes. Muk that catch a whiff of that stench will come drooling.
flavor_text_5: Wanting more garbage, they follow people who litter. They always belch poison gas.
flavor_text_6: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokemon.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.
flavor_text_8: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: garbodor
flavor_text_0: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.
flavor_text_1: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.
flavor_text_2: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
flavor_text_3: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.
flavor_text_4: Some say the reason Garbodor in Alola are a little stronger than their counterparts elsewhere is the presence of Muk, their natural enemy.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.
flavor_text_6: It locks opponents in place with its left hand, immobilizing them by entirely dousing their bodies with poisonous liquid.
flavor_text_7: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.
flavor_text_8: For a time, their numbers increased explosively in Alola. Since the arrival of Grimer, their population has decreased dramatically.

name: zorua
flavor_text_0: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.
flavor_text_1: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.
flavor_text_2: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon has a cowardly disposition, so when it's not around friends, it basically always stays transformed as something else.
flavor_text_4: Zorua sometimes transforms into a person and goes into cities to search for food. When Zorua does this, it usually takes on the form of a child.
flavor_text_5: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
flavor_text_6: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.
flavor_text_7: Zorua is a timid Pokemon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua's ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

name: zoroark
flavor_text_0: Bonds between these Pokemon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.
flavor_text_2: Seeking to ease the burden of their solitude, lonely Trainers tell Zoroark to show illusions to them.
flavor_text_3: It doesn't just transform itself--it also has the power to make hundreds of people see its illusions.
flavor_text_4: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
flavor_text_5: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.
flavor_text_6: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.
flavor_text_7: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.

name: minccino
flavor_text_0: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
flavor_text_1: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.
flavor_text_2: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest, Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean spring water.
flavor_text_3: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.
flavor_text_4: These Pokemon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
flavor_text_5: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.
flavor_text_6: A clean freak that will not allow even the slightest mess, it uses its tail like a mop to thoroughly clean any and all filth.

name: cinccino
flavor_text_0: The white parts of its coat are covered in an oil secreted from its body, so this Pokemon can slide right away from its enemies' attacks.
flavor_text_1: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.
flavor_text_2: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.
flavor_text_3: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.
flavor_text_4: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
flavor_text_5: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.
flavor_text_6: Its body secretes oil that this Pokemon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: gothita
flavor_text_0: Though they're still only babies, there's psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.
flavor_text_1: Even when nobody seems to be around, Gothita can still be heard making a muted cry. Many believe it's speaking to something only it can see.
flavor_text_2: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokemon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.
flavor_text_3: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn't notice attacks.
flavor_text_4: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: gothorita
flavor_text_0: It's said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokemon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.
flavor_text_1: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.
flavor_text_2: On nights when the stars shine, this Pokemon's psychic power is at its strongest. It's unknown just what link Gothorita has to the greater universe.
flavor_text_3: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokemon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.
flavor_text_4: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

name: gothitelle
flavor_text_0: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It's also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.
flavor_text_1: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.
flavor_text_2: It can see the future from the movement of the stars. When it learns its Trainer's life span, it cries in sadness.
flavor_text_3: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
flavor_text_4: A criminal who was shown his fate by a Gothitelle went missing that same day and was never seen again.

name: solosis
flavor_text_0: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.
flavor_text_1: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.
flavor_text_2: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.
flavor_text_3: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokemon's body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.
flavor_text_4: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

name: duosion
flavor_text_0: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile--but only if its two brains can agree with each other.
flavor_text_1: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokemon exhibit their maximum power.
flavor_text_2: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.
flavor_text_3: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.
flavor_text_4: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.

name: reuniclus
flavor_text_0: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.
flavor_text_1: It's said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.
flavor_text_2: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
flavor_text_3: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokemon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.
flavor_text_4: These remarkably intelligent Pokemon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

name: ducklett
flavor_text_0: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.
flavor_text_1: These bird Pokemon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.
flavor_text_2: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: swanna
flavor_text_0: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.
flavor_text_1: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.
flavor_text_2: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: vanillite
flavor_text_0: The temperature of their breath is -58deg F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.
flavor_text_1: The temperature of their breath is -58 degrees Fahrenheit. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.
flavor_text_2: It exhales cold air that is at -58 degrees Fahrenheit. When it's in a warm place, it shrinks little by little.
flavor_text_3: It feels pleasantly cool when embraced. This Pokemon is treasured by households in warm regions.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.
flavor_text_5: When the morning sun hit an icicle, it wished not to melt, and thus Vanillite was born. At night, it buries itself in snow to sleep.
flavor_text_6: Theoretically, this Pokemon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. Their breath is -58deg F.
flavor_text_7: Born of an icicle, this Pokemon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.
flavor_text_8: Supposedly, this Pokemon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at -58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.
flavor_text_9: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

name: vanillish
flavor_text_0: This hearty Pokemon survived the Ice Age. It's incredibly popular in very hot regions.
flavor_text_1: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokemon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon has existed since the Ice Age. It controls particles of ice, freezes its opponents, and then shatters them with a headbutt.
flavor_text_3: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.
flavor_text_4: Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.
flavor_text_5: Snowy mountains are this Pokemon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.
flavor_text_6: It sprays its enemies with grains of ice to freeze them. Most Vanillish in Alola are smaller than average.
flavor_text_7: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching -148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward--it's a kind Pokemon.
flavor_text_8: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.

name: vanilluxe
flavor_text_0: It blasts blizzards from its two mouths. It can create snow anywhere, so it gets a lot of love from skiers and snowboarders.
flavor_text_1: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.
flavor_text_2: Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.
flavor_text_3: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokemon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.
flavor_text_4: People believe this Pokemon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_5: Even if it loses one of its heads, it can live relatively problem-free. It makes snow clouds inside its body.
flavor_text_6: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokemon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.
flavor_text_7: Vanilluxe is born when two Vanillish, half-melted by the day's light, stick to each other and freeze together in the cold return of night.
flavor_text_8: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: deerling
flavor_text_0: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.
flavor_text_1: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.
flavor_text_2: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokemon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: sawsbuck
flavor_text_0: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns.
flavor_text_1: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.
flavor_text_2: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

name: emolga
flavor_text_0: It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.
flavor_text_1: They store up electricity to fly through the air. When thunder cracks at night, sometimes there are almost enough of them to blot out the sky.
flavor_text_2: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can't fly properly.
flavor_text_4: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokemon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.
flavor_text_5: It grills berries and bug Pokemon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.
flavor_text_6: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokemon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.
flavor_text_7: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.
flavor_text_8: It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricity stored in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: karrablast
flavor_text_0: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokemon to evolve.
flavor_text_1: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.
flavor_text_2: These mysterious Pokemon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.
flavor_text_3: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet's shell. Karrablast doesn't eat the shell-- it eats only the contents.
flavor_text_4: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokemon targets Shelmet.

name: escavalier
flavor_text_0: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.
flavor_text_1: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch'd.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.
flavor_text_3: They use shells they've stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They're very popular Pokemon in the Galar region.
flavor_text_4: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: foongus
flavor_text_0: For some reason, this Pokemon resembles a Poke Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.
flavor_text_1: No one knows what the Poke Ball-like pattern on Foongus means or why Foongus has it.
flavor_text_2: It lures people in with its Poke Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poke Ball is unknown.
flavor_text_3: The spores released from this Pokemon's hands are highly poisonous, but when thoroughly dried, the spores can be used as stomach medicine.
flavor_text_4: It lures Pokemon with its pattern that looks just like a Poke Ball, then releases poison spores.
flavor_text_5: It lures Pokemon with its pattern that looks just like a Poke Ball then releases poison spores.

name: amoonguss
flavor_text_0: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poke Balls, in a swaying motion.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren't washed off quickly, they'll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.
flavor_text_2: They show off their Poke Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokemon are fooled by this.
flavor_text_3: It moves the caps on both arms and does a dance to lure prey. It prefers damp places.
flavor_text_4: Amoonguss generally doesn't move much. It tends to stand still near Poke Balls that have been dropped on the ground.

name: frillish
flavor_text_0: It wraps its veillike arms and legs around prey swimming by and drags them down to the depths of the ocean.
flavor_text_1: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.
flavor_text_2: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.
flavor_text_3: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean's surface.
flavor_text_5: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.
flavor_text_6: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: jellicent
flavor_text_0: Jellicent is always hanging around fancy cruise ships and tankers, hoping to drag away its prey.
flavor_text_1: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.
flavor_text_2: Most of this Pokemon's body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.
flavor_text_3: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.
flavor_text_4: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.
flavor_text_5: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.
flavor_text_6: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It's rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.

name: alomomola
flavor_text_0: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokemon gather in the area around Alomomola.
flavor_text_1: Fishermen take them along on long voyages, because if you have an Alomomola with you, there'll be no need for a doctor or medicine.
flavor_text_2: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.
flavor_text_3: The reason it helps Pokemon in a weakened condition is that any Pokemon coming after them may also attack Alomomola.
flavor_text_4: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokemon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.
flavor_text_5: It gently holds injured and weak Pokemon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.
flavor_text_6: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokemon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

name: joltik
flavor_text_0: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokemon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.
flavor_text_1: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.
flavor_text_2: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokemon. It's soaking up static electricity because it can't produce a charge on its own.
flavor_text_3: Joltik latch on to other Pokemon and suck out static electricity. They're often found sticking to Yamper's hindquarters.
flavor_text_4: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokemon and absorbs static electricity.

name: galvantula
flavor_text_0: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.
flavor_text_1: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
flavor_text_2: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
flavor_text_3: It creates barriers from electrified silk that stun foes. This works as a weapon as well as a defense.
flavor_text_4: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokemon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.

name: ferroseed
flavor_text_0: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.
flavor_text_1: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn't very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.
flavor_text_2: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed's spikes grow big and strong.
flavor_text_3: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.
flavor_text_4: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: ferrothorn
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.
flavor_text_1: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.
flavor_text_2: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.
flavor_text_3: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokemon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
flavor_text_4: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.

name: klink
flavor_text_0: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
flavor_text_1: Two bodies comprise a fixed pair. They spin around each other to generate energy.
flavor_text_2: The two minigears that compose this Pokemon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.
flavor_text_3: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.
flavor_text_4: It's suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people's invention of the first gears.

name: klang
flavor_text_0: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don't return.
flavor_text_1: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.
flavor_text_2: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokemon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.
flavor_text_3: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.
flavor_text_4: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokemon's rotation speed increases sharply.

name: klinklang
flavor_text_0: The three gears that compose this Pokemon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn't a living creature.
flavor_text_1: The minigear spins at high speed. Then the energy from the red core charges the minigear to make it ready to fire.
flavor_text_2: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.
flavor_text_3: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.
flavor_text_4: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

name: tynamo
flavor_text_0: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.
flavor_text_2: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: eelektrik
flavor_text_0: These Pokemon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
flavor_text_1: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.
flavor_text_2: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

name: eelektross
flavor_text_0: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.
flavor_text_1: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
flavor_text_2: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: elgyem
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.
flavor_text_1: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.
flavor_text_2: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is shrouded in mystery. It's said to have appeared from a UFO that fell from the sky about 50 years ago.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.
flavor_text_5: It controls tremendous psychic power. Most reports of alien sightings are actually just people mistaking Elgyem for an alien.
flavor_text_6: If this Pokemon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: beheeyem
flavor_text_0: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.
flavor_text_1: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.
flavor_text_2: It has strong psychic powers. Using its fingers that flash three different colors, it controls its opponents and rewrites their memories.
flavor_text_3: With its psychic powers, it rewrites its opponents' memories. You, too, may have already had your memories rewritten.
flavor_text_4: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven't been decoded.
flavor_text_5: It can manipulate an opponent's memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.
flavor_text_6: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokemon can control the memories of its opponents.

name: litwick
flavor_text_0: The younger the life this Pokemon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.
flavor_text_1: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokemon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.
flavor_text_2: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.
flavor_text_3: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokemon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.
flavor_text_4: Its flame is usually out, but it starts shining when it absorbs life force from people or Pokemon.

name: lampent
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon appears just before someone passes away, so it's feared as an emissary of death.
flavor_text_1: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.
flavor_text_2: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.
flavor_text_3: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.
flavor_text_4: This ominous Pokemon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: chandelure
flavor_text_0: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.
flavor_text_2: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.
flavor_text_3: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.
flavor_text_4: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence-- or so it's said.

name: axew
flavor_text_0: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.
flavor_text_1: They play with each other by knocking their large tusks together. Their tusks break sometimes, but they grow back so quickly that it isn't a concern.
flavor_text_2: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
flavor_text_3: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.
flavor_text_4: These Pokemon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other's strength.

name: fraxure
flavor_text_0: Its skin is as hard as a suit of armor. Fraxure's favorite strategy is to tackle its opponents, stabbing them with its tusks at the same time.
flavor_text_1: After battle, this Pokemon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks--if one breaks, it will never grow back.
flavor_text_2: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.
flavor_text_3: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they've been fighting.
flavor_text_4: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

name: haxorus
flavor_text_0: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokemon are covered in hard armor.
flavor_text_1: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.
flavor_text_2: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.
flavor_text_3: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
flavor_text_4: While usually kindhearted, it can be terrifying if angered. Tusks that can slice through steel beams are how Haxorus deals with its adversaries.

name: cubchoo
flavor_text_0: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.
flavor_text_1: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.
flavor_text_2: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.
flavor_text_3: It sniffles before performing a move, using its frosty snot to provide an icy element to any move that needs it.
flavor_text_4: When this Pokemon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

name: beartic
flavor_text_0: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.
flavor_text_1: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.
flavor_text_2: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.
flavor_text_3: It swims energetically through frigid seas. When it gets tired, it freezes the seawater with its breath so it can rest on the ice.
flavor_text_4: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.

name: cryogonal
flavor_text_0: With its icy chains, Cryogonal freezes those it encounters. It then takes its victims away to somewhere unknown.
flavor_text_1: When the weather gets hot, these Pokemon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.
flavor_text_2: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.
flavor_text_4: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
flavor_text_5: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148deg F.

name: shelmet
flavor_text_0: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.
flavor_text_1: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.
flavor_text_2: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.
flavor_text_3: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.
flavor_text_4: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.

name: accelgor
flavor_text_0: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.
flavor_text_1: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.
flavor_text_2: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.
flavor_text_3: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.
flavor_text_4: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

name: stunfisk
flavor_text_0: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
flavor_text_1: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokemon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.
flavor_text_2: For some reason, this Pokemon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.
flavor_text_3: When its opponent can't be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.
flavor_text_4: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: mienfoo
flavor_text_0: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.
flavor_text_1: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.
flavor_text_2: They can often be seen in packs in the morning, slowly moving their bodies through a series of poses.
flavor_text_3: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.
flavor_text_4: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.
flavor_text_5: Though small, Mienfoo's temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.
flavor_text_6: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: mienshao
flavor_text_0: They use the long fur on their arms as a whip to strike their opponents.
flavor_text_1: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!
flavor_text_2: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokemon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.
flavor_text_3: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.
flavor_text_4: It overwhelms its opponents with continuous attacks and then slowly stores up power before delivering the finishing blow.
flavor_text_5: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.
flavor_text_6: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

name: druddigon
flavor_text_0: It infiltrates tunnels that Pokemon like Diglett and Dugtrio have dug and quietly waits for prey to pass through.
flavor_text_1: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.
flavor_text_2: The red skin on its face is harder than rock. In narrow caves, it squares off against its enemies and charges face-first right into them.
flavor_text_3: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.
flavor_text_4: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokemon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.
flavor_text_5: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
flavor_text_6: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing--it won't be able to move if its body gets too cold.

name: golett
flavor_text_0: Although ancient people apparently built it by working with clay, the source of its energy is unclear.
flavor_text_1: Ancient science fashioned this Pokemon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.
flavor_text_3: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.
flavor_text_5: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.
flavor_text_6: Its movements are powered by a mysterious energy. It has continued to move since ancient times, so its power may soon run out.

name: golurk
flavor_text_0: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokemon by the ancient people who made them.
flavor_text_1: Some say that ancient people invented Golurk to serve as a laborer. It follows its master's orders faithfully.
flavor_text_2: When the seal on its chest is removed, it rages indiscriminately, turning the whole town around it into a mountain of rubble.
flavor_text_3: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokemon. They run on a mysterious energy.
flavor_text_4: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.
flavor_text_5: There's a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn't been proven.
flavor_text_6: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: pawniard
flavor_text_0: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.
flavor_text_1: It follows Bisharp's orders to a tee when it attacks enemies. After slashing an opponent, Pawniard clangs both of its blades together.
flavor_text_2: After shredding its prey, it sharpens its blades on a stone by the river. Each Pawniard has its own favorite sharpening stone.
flavor_text_3: Blades comprise this Pokemon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.
flavor_text_4: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.
flavor_text_5: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.
flavor_text_6: A pack of these Pokemon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

name: bisharp
flavor_text_0: This pitiless Pokemon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.
flavor_text_1: No matter how strong the Bisharp, it's said that if the blade on its head is chipped, it will retire from its position as the boss.
flavor_text_2: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
flavor_text_3: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.
flavor_text_4: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.
flavor_text_5: It leads a group of Pawniard. Bisharp doesn't even change its expression when it deals the finishing blow to an opponent.
flavor_text_6: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

name: bouffalant
flavor_text_0: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
flavor_text_1: They are known to charge so wildly that if a train were to enter their territory, they would send it flying.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.
flavor_text_3: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.
flavor_text_4: These Pokemon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

name: rufflet
flavor_text_0: If it spies a strong Pokemon, Rufflet can't resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.
flavor_text_1: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.
flavor_text_2: A combative Pokemon, it's ready to pick a fight with anyone. It has talons that can crush hard berries.
flavor_text_3: With its powerful legs and sturdy claws, it can crack even the hard shells of Shellder and pluck out their insides.
flavor_text_4: Known as a natural-born warrior, soon after its hatching, it will challenge its parent to a fight in order to gain their acceptance.
flavor_text_5: It stands up to massive opponents, not out of courage, but out of recklessness. But that is how it gets stronger.
flavor_text_6: With its sharp claws, this Pokemon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it's a carnivore at heart.
flavor_text_7: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.
flavor_text_8: Its chick-like looks belie its hotheadedness. It challenges its parents at every opportunity, desperate to prove its strength.
flavor_text_9: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.

name: braviary
flavor_text_0: Because this Pokemon is hotheaded and belligerent, it's Corviknight that's taken the role of transportation in Galar.
flavor_text_1: With its brave disposition, it fears nothing--not even death. Ancient Alolan people respected it, referring to it as "the hero of the sky."
flavor_text_2: Known as "the hero of the skies," this Pokemon is so proud and so brave that it will never retreat, even when it's injured.
flavor_text_3: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokemon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.
flavor_text_4: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.
flavor_text_5: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky  get from their peers.
flavor_text_6: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
flavor_text_7: The more scars it has on its front, the more heroic it's considered to be. Those with many scars on their back are mocked by the flock.
flavor_text_8: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokemon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water's surface.
flavor_text_9: It's thought that people disturbed their habitats in the past, so Braviary banded together to fight back.

name: vullaby
flavor_text_0: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.
flavor_text_1: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.
flavor_text_2: It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.
flavor_text_3: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: Mandibuzz gives it the bones it wears. Vullaby's wings are short, so it can't fly yet, but it jumps around, dreaming of wide open skies.
flavor_text_5: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.
flavor_text_6: It can't fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it's still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.
flavor_text_7: Its healthy appetite leads to visible growth spurts. It often has to replace the bones it wears as its size increases.
flavor_text_8: It protects its plump posterior with the bones of prey it has consumed. As it grows, it  replaces the bones.

name: mandibuzz
flavor_text_0: Although it's a bit of a ruffian, this Pokemon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they're ready to leave the nest.
flavor_text_1: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.
flavor_text_2: It skillfully arranges the bones of its prey to construct its nest. Most of the bones are Cubone.
flavor_text_3: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokemon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.
flavor_text_4: It's always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokemon, Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.
flavor_text_5: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.
flavor_text_6: It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokemon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.
flavor_text_7: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.
flavor_text_8: They adorn themselves beautifully with bones. This is supposedly an effort to attract males, but no male Mandibuzz have ever been found.

name: heatmor
flavor_text_0: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.
flavor_text_1: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.
flavor_text_2: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokemon will fall ill.
flavor_text_3: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.
flavor_text_4: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

name: durant
flavor_text_0: With their large mandibles, these Pokemon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.
flavor_text_1: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.
flavor_text_2: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.
flavor_text_3: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.
flavor_text_4: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels into mazes.

name: deino
flavor_text_0: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.
flavor_text_1: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.
flavor_text_2: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.
flavor_text_3: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.
flavor_text_4: Because it can't see, this Pokemon is constantly biting at everything it touches, trying to keep track of its surroundings.

name: zweilous
flavor_text_0: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.
flavor_text_1: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.
flavor_text_2: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.
flavor_text_3: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.
flavor_text_4: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

name: hydreigon
flavor_text_0: This brutal Pokemon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.
flavor_text_1: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.
flavor_text_2: The three heads take turns sinking their teeth into the opponent. Their attacks won't slow until their target goes down.
flavor_text_3: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokemon devours everything in its path!
flavor_text_4: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

name: larvesta
flavor_text_0: When battling opponents, it sprays fire from its five horns. The max temperature of the flames can reach nearly 5,500 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.
flavor_text_3: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.
flavor_text_4: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.
flavor_text_5: Larvesta's body is warm all over. It spouts fire from the tips of its horns to intimidate predators and scare prey.
flavor_text_6: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.

name: volcarona
flavor_text_0: As it flies, it scatters its flaming scales. It was feared by ancient people, who referred to it as "the rage of the sun."
flavor_text_1: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
flavor_text_2: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
flavor_text_3: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokemon that were suffering from the cold.
flavor_text_4: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it's trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.
flavor_text_5: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokemon from freezing.
flavor_text_6: This Pokemon emerges from a cocoon formed of raging flames. Ancient murals depict Volcarona as a deity of fire.

name: cobalion
flavor_text_0: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokemon obey it.
flavor_text_1: From the moment it's born, this Pokemon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.
flavor_text_2: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: This legendary Pokemon battled against humans to protect Pokemon. Its personality is calm and composed.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region's Pokemon.

name: terrakion
flavor_text_0: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokemon.
