flavor_text_1: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: Spoken of in legend, this Pokemon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon came to the defense of Pokemon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.
flavor_text_4: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokemon is spoken of in legends.

name: virizion
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.
flavor_text_1: A legend tells of this Pokemon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokemon of the Unova region.
flavor_text_2: Legends say this Pokemon confounded opponents with its swift movements.
flavor_text_3: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
flavor_text_4: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.

name: tornadus
flavor_text_0: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
flavor_text_1: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.
flavor_text_2: This storm-stirring Pokemon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.
flavor_text_3: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: thundurus
flavor_text_0: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.
flavor_text_1: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
flavor_text_2: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.
flavor_text_3: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: reshiram
flavor_text_0: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.
flavor_text_2: Flames spew from its tail as it flies through the sky like a jet airplane. It's said that this Pokemon will scorch the world.
flavor_text_3: This legendary Pokemon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.
flavor_text_4: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

name: zekrom
flavor_text_0: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.
flavor_text_1: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom's lightning.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.
flavor_text_3: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.
flavor_text_4: This legendary Pokemon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

name: landorus
flavor_text_0: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
flavor_text_1: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.
flavor_text_2: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.
flavor_text_3: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

name: kyurem
flavor_text_0: It can produce ultracold air. Its body is frozen.
flavor_text_1: It appears that this Pokemon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.
flavor_text_2: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
flavor_text_3: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.
flavor_text_4: This legendary ice Pokemon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

name: keldeo
flavor_text_0: Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion taught this Pokemon how to fight. It dashes across the world, seeking more opportunities to further its training.
flavor_text_1: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
flavor_text_2: They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokemon's true power will awaken.
flavor_text_3: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
flavor_text_4: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

name: meloetta
flavor_text_0: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
flavor_text_1: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.
flavor_text_2: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokemon that hear them happy or sad.

name: genesect
flavor_text_0: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.
flavor_text_1: This ancient bug Pokemon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: chespin
flavor_text_0: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.
flavor_text_1: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

name: quilladin
flavor_text_0: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators' attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.
flavor_text_1: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

name: chesnaught
flavor_text_0: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.
flavor_text_1: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: fennekin
flavor_text_0: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
flavor_text_1: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: braixen
flavor_text_0: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
flavor_text_1: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

name: delphox
flavor_text_0: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
flavor_text_1: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

name: froakie
flavor_text_0: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.
flavor_text_1: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: frogadier
flavor_text_0: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.
flavor_text_1: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

name: greninja
flavor_text_0: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.
flavor_text_1: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

name: bunnelby
flavor_text_0: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.
flavor_text_1: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.
flavor_text_2: It's very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight's flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.
flavor_text_3: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

name: diggersby
flavor_text_0: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.
flavor_text_2: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It's a huge help during tunnel construction.
flavor_text_3: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

name: fletchling
flavor_text_0: While it's an amiable Pokemon, if you touch it unexpectedly, it will heat up its body in an instant, and you'll be burned.
flavor_text_1: These friendly Pokemon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.
flavor_text_2: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.
flavor_text_3: Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.
flavor_text_4: Its melodious cries are actually warnings. Fletchling will mercilessly peck at anything that enters its territory.
flavor_text_5: When this Pokemon gets excited, its body temperature increases sharply. If you touch a Fletchling with bare hands, you might get burned.
flavor_text_6: This amiable Pokemon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.
flavor_text_7: When it's excited, its temperature can double, spiking hormone production in its body.

name: fletchinder
flavor_text_0: Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: It scatters embers in the tall grass. Then bug Pokemon, frightened by the flames, come flying out, and Fletchinder gobbles them up.
flavor_text_2: Fletchinder are exceedingly territorial and aggressive. These Pokemon fight among themselves over feeding grounds.
flavor_text_3: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.
flavor_text_4: It will not tolerate other Fletchinder entering its territory, which has a radius of several miles.
flavor_text_5: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.
flavor_text_6: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.
flavor_text_7: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder's sharp talons finish it off.

name: talonflame
flavor_text_0: Its tough wings don't allow fire to pass through them. A long time ago, firefighters' outfits were made from Talonflame wings.
flavor_text_1: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokemon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.
flavor_text_2: Bird Pokemon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.
flavor_text_3: Talonflame dives toward prey at speeds of up to 310 mph and assaults them with powerful kicks, giving the prey no chance to escape.
flavor_text_4: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.
flavor_text_5: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.
flavor_text_6: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.
flavor_text_7: It zooms directly at its prey at flight speeds of close to 310 mph, while fiery embers scatter from gaps in its feathers.

name: scatterbug
flavor_text_0: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
flavor_text_1: When under attack from bird Pokemon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

name: spewpa
flavor_text_0: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.
flavor_text_1: The beaks of bird Pokemon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

name: vivillon
flavor_text_0: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.
flavor_text_1: The patterns on this Pokemon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

name: litleo
flavor_text_0: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.
flavor_text_1: This hot-blooded Pokemon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.
flavor_text_2: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokemon are quick to fight.
flavor_text_3: When they're young, they live with a pride. Once they're able to hunt prey on their own, they're kicked out and have to make their own way.

name: pyroar
flavor_text_0: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.
flavor_text_1: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn't use it on its prey. This Pokemon prefers to eat raw meat.
flavor_text_2: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.
flavor_text_3: The males are usually lazy, but when attacked by a strong foe, a male will protect its friends with no regard for its own safety.

name: flabebe
flavor_text_0: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
flavor_text_1: It's not safe without the power of a flower, but it will keep traveling around until it finds one with the color and shape it wants.
flavor_text_2: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabebe holds is most likely part of its body.
flavor_text_3: Flabebe wears a crown made from pollen it's collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.

name: floette
flavor_text_0: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
flavor_text_1: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.
flavor_text_2: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.
flavor_text_3: It raises flowers and uses them as weapons. The more gorgeous the blossom, the more power it contains.

name: florges
flavor_text_0: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.
flavor_text_1: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.
flavor_text_2: It controls the flowers it grows. The petal blizzards that Florges triggers are overwhelming in their beauty and power.
flavor_text_3: Its life can span several hundred years. It's said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.

name: skiddo
flavor_text_0: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.
flavor_text_1: Thought to be one of the first Pokemon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: gogoat
flavor_text_0: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.
flavor_text_1: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

name: pancham
flavor_text_0: It follows Pangoro around like a henchman. When Pancham makes a big mistake, its leaf gets taken away.
flavor_text_1: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master's actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.
flavor_text_2: It's desperate to intimidate its opponents. Be nice and pretend to be scared if you catch it glaring at you intensely.
flavor_text_3: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.
flavor_text_4: There's no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It's mischievous, so it's not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.
flavor_text_5: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.
flavor_text_6: It grows up imitating the behavior of Pangoro, which it looks up to as a leader.
flavor_text_7: Wanting to make sure it's taken seriously, Pancham's always giving others a glare. But if it's not focusing, it ends up smiling.

name: pangoro
flavor_text_0: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.
flavor_text_1: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won't put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.
flavor_text_2: This rowdy Pokemon boasts great physical strength. Many Trainers are also smitten by its lively character.
flavor_text_3: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro's Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.
flavor_text_4: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.
flavor_text_6: From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.
flavor_text_7: Pangoro is the type to talk with its fists. It doesn't say much as it pummels opponents with enough force to send a dump truck flying.

name: furfrou
flavor_text_0: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokemon were the designated guardians of the king.
flavor_text_1: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.
flavor_text_2: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.
flavor_text_3: There was an era when aristocrats would compete to see who could trim their Furfrou's fur into the most exquisite style.

name: espurr
flavor_text_0: Though Espurr's expression never changes, behind that blank stare is an intense struggle to contain its devastating psychic power.
flavor_text_1: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.
flavor_text_2: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can't be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.
flavor_text_3: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

name: meowstic
flavor_text_0: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.
flavor_text_1: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.
flavor_text_2: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
flavor_text_3: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

name: honedge
flavor_text_0: Apparently this Pokemon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
flavor_text_1: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.
flavor_text_2: Honedge's soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge's body.
flavor_text_3: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

name: doublade
flavor_text_0: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.
flavor_text_1: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
flavor_text_2: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.
flavor_text_3: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

name: aegislash
flavor_text_0: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokemon to build a kingdom to its liking.
flavor_text_1: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokemon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.
flavor_text_3: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

name: spritzee
flavor_text_0: A scent pouch within this Pokemon's body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.
flavor_text_1: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.
flavor_text_2: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.
flavor_text_3: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

name: aromatisse
flavor_text_0: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
flavor_text_1: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent's will to fight.
flavor_text_2: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokemon's companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.
flavor_text_3: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

name: swirlix
flavor_text_0: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix's fluffy fur. This Pokemon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.
flavor_text_1: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.
flavor_text_2: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.
flavor_text_3: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn't get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: slurpuff
flavor_text_0: By taking in a person's scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It's hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.
flavor_text_1: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.
flavor_text_2: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!
flavor_text_3: Slurpuff's fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.

name: inkay
flavor_text_0: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.
flavor_text_1: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.
flavor_text_2: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.
flavor_text_3: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.
flavor_text_4: It draws prey near with its blinking lights and then wraps them up in its long tentacles and holds them in place.
flavor_text_5: When exchanging information with others of its kind, it flashes the light-emitting spots on its body in a complex rhythm.

name: malamar
flavor_text_0: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.
flavor_text_1: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.
flavor_text_2: It flashes the pattern on its torso to control its prey and draw them in. The edges of its fins are supremely sharp.
flavor_text_3: When it comes to strong hypnosis, there's an endless number of people who utilize Malamar for their nefarious deeds.
flavor_text_4: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokemon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.
flavor_text_5: It's said that Malamar's hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.

name: binacle
flavor_text_0: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.
flavor_text_1: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.
flavor_text_2: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.
flavor_text_3: If the two don't work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won't survive.

name: barbaracle
flavor_text_0: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.
flavor_text_1: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy's defeat.
flavor_text_2: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.
flavor_text_3: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

name: skrelp
flavor_text_0: Skrelp looks like a piece of rotten seaweed, so it can blend in with seaweed drifting on the ocean and avoid being detected by enemies.
flavor_text_1: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.
flavor_text_2: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.
flavor_text_3: It vanishes into seaweed and remains perfectly still to avoid attacks from large Pokemon. Rotten seaweed is its main food source.
flavor_text_4: It's not good at swimming, so it clings to the seaweed. In the Alola region, it's often found near Dhelmise.
flavor_text_5: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokemon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

name: dragalge
flavor_text_0: It blends in with seaweed to ambush its prey and then takes them down with a poisonous liquid strong enough to melt metal.
flavor_text_1: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.
flavor_text_2: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean's surface and bathing it in sunlight.
flavor_text_3: This vicious Pokemon sprays a poisonous liquid on opponents that come near. For whatever reason, it gets along really well with Dhelmise.
flavor_text_4: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.
flavor_text_5: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

name: clauncher
flavor_text_0: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw, this Pokemon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.
flavor_text_1: It moves around by jetting water from its right pincer. It has a poor sense of balance, so it's terrible at swimming straight.
flavor_text_2: Clauncher's claws can fall off during battle, but they'll regenerate. The meat inside the claws is popular as a delicacy in Galar.
flavor_text_3: Its claws occasionally fall off, and it keeps a low profile until they grow back. The meat of its claws is so delicious!
flavor_text_4: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.
flavor_text_5: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

name: clawitzer
flavor_text_0: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.
flavor_text_1: It compresses the water it has sucked up and then projects it with enough power to punch a hole right through a thick sheet of iron.
flavor_text_2: Clawitzer's right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer's cannon arm can sink a tanker.
flavor_text_3: After using the feelers on its oversized claw to detect the location of prey, Clawitzer launches a cannonball of water at its target.
flavor_text_4: Its right arm is packed with meat. When its pincer falls off, it's exported to be used as a cooking ingredient.
flavor_text_5: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

name: helioptile
flavor_text_0: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.
flavor_text_1: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.
flavor_text_2: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokemon's electric moves.
flavor_text_3: The sun powers this Pokemon's electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.

name: heliolisk
flavor_text_0: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.
flavor_text_1: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.
flavor_text_2: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.
flavor_text_3: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokemon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

name: tyrunt
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn't like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.
flavor_text_1: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.
flavor_text_2: This is an ancient Pokemon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it'll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.
flavor_text_4: Tyrunt is spoiled and selfish. It may just be trying to frolic, but sometimes the ones it's trying to frolic with are gravely injured.
flavor_text_5: Its large jaw has incredible destructive power. Some theories suggest that its restored form is different from its form of long ago.

name: tyrantrum
flavor_text_0: A single bite of Tyrantrum's massive jaws will demolish a car. This Pokemon was the king of the ancient world.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.
flavor_text_2: Complete restoration is impossible, allowing room for theories that its entire body was once covered in a feather-like coat.
flavor_text_3: The king of the ancient world, it can easily crunch a car with the devastating strength of its enormous jaws.
flavor_text_4: Nothing could stop this Pokemon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.
flavor_text_5: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

name: amaura
flavor_text_0: Amaura was restored successfully, but it's not expected to live long because of the heat of the current environment.
flavor_text_1: This calm Pokemon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.
flavor_text_2: This ancient Pokemon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.
flavor_text_3: Amaura is an ancient Pokemon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.
flavor_text_4: It lived in cold areas in ancient times. It's said that when Amaura whinnies, auroras appear in the night sky.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

name: aurorus
flavor_text_0: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.
flavor_text_1: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It's said that when this Pokemon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.
flavor_text_2: This usually quiet and kindly Pokemon has a surface temperature of around -240 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.
flavor_text_4: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.
flavor_text_5: An Aurorus was found frozen solid within a glacier, just as it appeared long ago, which became quite a big event in the news.

name: sylveon
flavor_text_0: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.
flavor_text_1: There's a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.
flavor_text_3: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.
flavor_text_4: Sylveon wraps its ribbonlike feelers around its Trainer's arm because this touch enables it to read its Trainer's feelings.
flavor_text_5: It emits a soothing aura from its ribbon-shaped organs. It wraps these appendages around quarrelers to instantly restore calm to the situation.
flavor_text_6: Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura that weakens hostility in its prey, causing them to let down their guard. Then it attacks.
flavor_text_7: When this Pokemon sights its prey, it swirls its ribbonlike feelers as a distraction. A moment later, it pounces.
flavor_text_8: Once a fight breaks out, it will unflinchingly charge at dragon Pokemon that are many times larger than itself.

name: hawlucha
flavor_text_0: In combat, Hawlucha leaps nimbly about, taking advantage of its opponents' blind spots. It's also skilled at using superb submission holds.
flavor_text_1: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.
flavor_text_2: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
flavor_text_3: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.
flavor_text_4: It overwhelms opponents with quick moves, but sometimes it showboats for too long when it's using a special move and gets itself into a pinch.
flavor_text_5: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: dedenne
flavor_text_0: It sneaks into people's homes and steals electricity from their outlets. When your electric bill seems off, it's the handiwork of this rascal.
flavor_text_1: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.
flavor_text_2: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.
flavor_text_3: Since Dedenne can't generate much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: A Dedenne's whiskers pick up electrical waves other Dedenne send out. These Pokemon share locations of food or electricity with one another.
flavor_text_5: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

name: carbink
flavor_text_0: Although this Pokemon is not especially rare, its glittering, jewel-draped body draws attention from people.
flavor_text_1: It's said that somewhere in the world, there's a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It's also said that this pack has a queen.
flavor_text_2: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.
flavor_text_3: Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.
flavor_text_4: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
flavor_text_5: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.
flavor_text_6: Some say that deep beneath the surface of the world, a pack of Carbink live with their queen in a kingdom of jewels.
flavor_text_7: To keep the jewels on their bodies free of tarnish, packs of Carbink use their soft manes to polish one another's jewels.

name: goomy
flavor_text_0: Because most of its body is water, it will dry up if the weather becomes too arid. It's considered the weakest dragon Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Its body is mostly water. If it dries out, it will die, so it's always sitting with perfect stillness in the shade.
flavor_text_2: The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokemon, it's unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.
flavor_text_3: Goomy hides away in the shade of trees, where it's nice and humid. If the slime coating its body dries out, the Pokemon instantly becomes lethargic.
flavor_text_4: Its source of protection is its slimy, germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone who touches it needs some thorough hand-washing.
flavor_text_5: The weakest Dragon-type Pokemon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn't dry out.
flavor_text_6: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they've survived.
flavor_text_7: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.
flavor_text_8: It uses its horns to check out its surroundings. They're very sensitive, so if you grab them, it will feel a strong shock and be unable to move.

name: sliggoo
flavor_text_0: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.
flavor_text_1: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.
flavor_text_2: It crawls along sluggishly. The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with its brain and other organs.
flavor_text_3: It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.
flavor_text_4: Its entire body is covered with gooey mucus that can dissolve anything. Be sure to put gloves on if you're going to touch it.
flavor_text_5: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.
flavor_text_6: This Pokemon's mucous can dissolve anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous on its prey. Once they're nicely dissolved, it slurps them up.
flavor_text_7: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.
flavor_text_8: Although this Pokemon isn't very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

name: goodra
flavor_text_0: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokemon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.
flavor_text_1: Underneath its slimy skin is a thick layer of fat, and the combination of the two makes enemies' attacks slide right off.
flavor_text_2: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.
flavor_text_3: An amazingly friendly Pokemon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.
flavor_text_4: It's very friendly toward people. If you grow close to it, Goodra will hug you with its sticky, slime-covered body. Don't get mad.
flavor_text_5: Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.
flavor_text_6: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.
flavor_text_7: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy--it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.
flavor_text_8: It gets picked on because it's meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.

name: klefki
flavor_text_0: This even-tempered Pokemon has a habit of collecting keys. It will sneak into people's homes to steal their keys.
flavor_text_1: Although it's unclear why it collects keys, giving it a key makes Klefki very happy. However, it apparently only likes master keys.
flavor_text_2: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
flavor_text_3: It inserts its horn into chinks in metal, absorbing metal ions. For some reason, it collects keys.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is constantly collecting keys. Entrust a Klefki with important keys, and the Pokemon will protect them no matter what.
flavor_text_5: Klefki sucks in metal ions with the horn topping its head. It seems this Pokemon loves keys so much that its head needed to look like one, too.
flavor_text_6: Long ago it lived in mines, but once the minerals that make up its diet became scarcer, Klefki began appearing in human settlements.
flavor_text_7: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: phantump
flavor_text_0: According to legend, medicine to cure any illness can be made by plucking the green leaves on its head, brewing them, and boiling down the liquid.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.
flavor_text_2: According to old tales, these Pokemon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.
flavor_text_3: With a voice like a human child's, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.
flavor_text_4: By imitating the voice of a child, it causes people to get hopelessly lost deep in the forest. It's trying to make friends with them.
flavor_text_5: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokemon.
flavor_text_6: An unknown spirit came to lodge in a tree stump, creating this Pokemon. A cure-all can be made from an infusion of its green leaves.
flavor_text_7: These Pokemon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

name: trevenant
flavor_text_0: Through its roots, it exerts control over other trees. A deadly curse falls upon anyone cutting down trees in forests where Trevenant dwell.
flavor_text_1: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokemon that reside in its body.
flavor_text_2: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokemon it shares its woods with, it's kind.
flavor_text_3: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon controls trees via roots stretching from its feet, and it will attack anyone that dares to ravage the forest.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.
flavor_text_6: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokemon's feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.
flavor_text_7: It's feared as a ghost of the forest. Lumberjacks bring along Fire types, which Trevenant hates, when they enter the forest.

name: pumpkaboo
flavor_text_0: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokemon that see it.
flavor_text_1: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo's body. They're then moved on to the afterlife.
flavor_text_2: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
flavor_text_3: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: gourgeist
flavor_text_0: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.
flavor_text_1: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.
flavor_text_2: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.
flavor_text_3: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

name: bergmite
flavor_text_0: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.
flavor_text_1: They chill the air around them to -150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.
flavor_text_2: It blocks opponents' attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.
flavor_text_3: Lives on mountains blanketed in perennial snow. It freezes water vapor in the air to make the ice helmet that it dons for defense.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon lives in areas of frigid cold. It secures itself to the back of an Avalugg by freezing its feet in place.

name: avalugg
flavor_text_0: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokemon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.
flavor_text_1: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.
flavor_text_2: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.
flavor_text_3: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokemon's body returns to a pristine state overnight.
flavor_text_4: At high latitudes, this Pokemon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

name: noibat
flavor_text_0: No wavelength of sound is beyond Noibat's ability to produce. The ultrasonic waves it generates can overcome much larger Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Fruits are its favorite foods. This gourmet carefully picks out just the ripe ones using its sonar.
flavor_text_2: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.
flavor_text_3: It flies around in search of fruit to eat. It uses ultrasonic waves to detect which fruits are ripe.
flavor_text_4: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.
flavor_text_5: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

name: noivern
flavor_text_0: This hot-blooded Pokemon attacks anything it sees with ultrasonic waves that can crush boulders.
flavor_text_1: Aggressive and cruel, this Pokemon will ruthlessly torment enemies that are helpless in the dark.
flavor_text_2: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.
flavor_text_3: Although it has a violent disposition, if you give it a nice ripe fruit that it loves, Noivern will suddenly become tame.
flavor_text_4: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.
flavor_text_5: Flying through the darkness, it weakens enemies with ultrasonic waves that could crush stone. Its fangs finish the fight.

name: xerneas
flavor_text_0: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
flavor_text_1: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: yveltal
flavor_text_0: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
flavor_text_1: When this legendary Pokemon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: zygarde
flavor_text_0: This is Zygarde's form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.
flavor_text_1: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
flavor_text_2: This is Zygarde's form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.
flavor_text_3: When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.
flavor_text_4: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.
flavor_text_5: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: diancie
flavor_text_0: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
flavor_text_1: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: hoopa
flavor_text_0: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
flavor_text_1: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.
flavor_text_2: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.
flavor_text_3: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

name: volcanion
flavor_text_0: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
flavor_text_1: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It's said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

name: rowlet
flavor_text_0: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer's pocket or bag as a nest.
flavor_text_1: During the day, it builds up energy via photosynthesis. At night, it flies silently through the sky, on the prowl for prey.
flavor_text_2: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.
flavor_text_3: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.
flavor_text_4: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.
flavor_text_5: Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.
flavor_text_6: This wary Pokemon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

name: dartrix
flavor_text_0: This narcissistic Pokemon is a clean freak. If you don't groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.
flavor_text_1: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power--presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.
flavor_text_2: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.
flavor_text_3: It never slacks when it comes to the task of cleaning its feathers. Thorough preening keeps it looking spiffy and its blade quills nice and sharp.
flavor_text_4: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.
flavor_text_5: It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.
flavor_text_6: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: decidueye
flavor_text_0: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.
flavor_text_1: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.
flavor_text_2: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent's weak point before they notice what's happening.
flavor_text_3: Although basically cool and cautious, when it's caught by surprise, it's seized by panic.
flavor_text_4: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye's feathers insulates the Pokemon against Hisui's extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.
flavor_text_5: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can't afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.
flavor_text_6: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.

name: litten
flavor_text_0: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won't open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.
flavor_text_1: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.
flavor_text_2: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.
flavor_text_3: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.
flavor_text_4: It doesn't allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.
flavor_text_5: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.

name: torracat
flavor_text_0: It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.
flavor_text_1: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokemon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer's whole body covered in scratches.
flavor_text_2: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokemon spits fire.
flavor_text_3: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it's feeling good. When it isn't feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.
flavor_text_4: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat's fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.
flavor_text_5: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat's neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.

name: incineroar
flavor_text_0: It excels at violent, no-holds-barred battles. The temperature of the flames that issue from its navel exceeds 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.
flavor_text_2: After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.
flavor_text_3: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.
flavor_text_4: Incineroar's rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokemon shows that it has a kind side as well.
flavor_text_5: Although it's rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

name: popplio
flavor_text_0: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokemon to develop their skills.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.
flavor_text_2: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.
flavor_text_3: Popplio gets on top of its bouncy water balloons to jump higher. It's quite the acrobatic fighter!
flavor_text_4: It creates special bouncy balloons to send at its opponents. When the balloons pop, the sheer force of their bursting is what deals damage.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.

name: brionne
flavor_text_0: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that's leading them.
flavor_text_1: As if dancing, it artfully dodges the attacks of its enemies. All the while, it's busy forming a bunch of balloons to overwhelm its foes.
flavor_text_2: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.
flavor_text_3: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn't know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.
flavor_text_4: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.
flavor_text_5: It attacks by smacking its enemies with the exploding water balloons that it creates.

name: primarina
flavor_text_0: Also known as a songstress, it has a fantastical look on moonlit nights when it leads its colony in song.
flavor_text_1: With its mouth, it makes sonic waves that sound like beautiful singing. It uses the sonic waves to control its water balloons.
flavor_text_2: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokemon's Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.
flavor_text_3: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.
flavor_text_4: For Primarina, every battle's a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.
flavor_text_5: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

name: pikipek
flavor_text_0: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.
flavor_text_1: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.
flavor_text_2: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.

name: trumbeak
flavor_text_0: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.
flavor_text_1: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.
flavor_text_2: By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.
flavor_text_3: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

name: toucannon
flavor_text_0: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.
flavor_text_1: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.
flavor_text_2: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokemon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.
flavor_text_3: Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.

name: yungoos
flavor_text_0: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.
flavor_text_1: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.
flavor_text_2: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It's a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.
flavor_text_3: Although it will eat anything, it prefers fresh living things, so it marches down streets in search of prey.

name: gumshoos
flavor_text_0: Although it wasn't originally found in Alola, this Pokemon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.
flavor_text_1: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokemon boasts incredible patience.
flavor_text_2: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it's always snoozing by nightfall.
flavor_text_3: Patient by nature, this Pokemon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal--Rattata!

name: grubbin
flavor_text_0: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.
flavor_text_1: If you find its nest, you shouldn't stick your hand inside. You'll get bitten by an irritated Grubbin.
flavor_text_2: They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokemon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.
flavor_text_4: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
flavor_text_5: It spits a sticky thread to stop opponents in their tracks, and then it grabs them in its sharp, sturdy mandibles to take them down.

name: charjabug
flavor_text_0: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.
flavor_text_1: It buries itself in fallen leaves and barely moves, munching away on humus. If you accidentally step on one, you'll get a shock!
flavor_text_2: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.
flavor_text_3: From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.
flavor_text_4: Its stout shell provides excellent defense from attacks. It uses electricity on persistent opponents.
flavor_text_5: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: vikavolt
flavor_text_0: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokemon with shocking beams of electrical energy.
flavor_text_1: It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.
flavor_text_2: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.
flavor_text_3: Vikavolt flusters opponents with acrobatic flying maneuvers. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electric beam attack.
flavor_text_4: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.
flavor_text_5: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.

name: crabrawler
flavor_text_0: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.
flavor_text_1: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.
flavor_text_2: Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.
flavor_text_3: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

name: crabominable
flavor_text_0: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokemon evolved and grew fur.
flavor_text_1: It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.
flavor_text_2: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.
flavor_text_3: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

name: oricorio
flavor_text_0: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.
flavor_text_1: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.
flavor_text_2: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokemon becomes fiercely angry.
flavor_text_3: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

name: cutiefly
flavor_text_0: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.
flavor_text_1: Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of people who have auras resembling those of flowers.
flavor_text_2: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes' movements and make fools of them.
flavor_text_3: An opponent's aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent's next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.
flavor_text_4: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur's pollen.
flavor_text_5: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes with Butterfree over food.

name: ribombee
flavor_text_0: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs' effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.
flavor_text_1: Some of Ribombee's pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.
flavor_text_2: Rain makes pollen damp, so Ribombee hates rain. When it sees ominous clouds, it finds a hollow in a tree, where it waits stock-still.
flavor_text_3: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
flavor_text_4: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.
flavor_text_5: It can predict the weather from moisture levels and wind direction. Ribombee only reveals itself when there are a few clear days in a row.

name: rockruff
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.
flavor_text_1: It's considered to be a good Pokemon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.
flavor_text_2: As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches, Rockruff attacks.
flavor_text_4: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

name: lycanroc
flavor_text_0: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.
flavor_text_1: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.
flavor_text_2: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.
flavor_text_3: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.
flavor_text_4: With swift movements, this Pokemon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.
flavor_text_5: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

name: wishiwashi
flavor_text_0: When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.
flavor_text_1: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.
flavor_text_2: When it's in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.
flavor_text_3: It's awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.
flavor_text_4: Individually, they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.
flavor_text_5: They're weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.

name: mareanie
flavor_text_0: They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.
flavor_text_1: Unlike their Alolan counterparts, the Mareanie of the Galar region have not yet figured out that the branches of Corsola are delicious.
flavor_text_2: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.
flavor_text_3: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.
flavor_text_4: It's found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on Corsola's head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: Aside from its head, its body parts regenerate quickly if they're cut off. After a good night's sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.

name: toxapex
flavor_text_0: To attack, this Pokemon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.
flavor_text_1: Within the poison sac in its body is a poison so toxic that Pokemon as large as Wailord will still be suffering three days after it first takes effect.
flavor_text_2: With its 12 legs, it creates a dome to shelter within. The flow of the tides doesn't affect Toxapex in there, so it's very comfortable.
flavor_text_3: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokemon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.
flavor_text_4: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.
flavor_text_5: Those attacked by Toxapex's poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

name: mudbray
flavor_text_0: It eats dirt to create mud and smears this mud all over its feet, giving them the grip needed to walk on rough terrain without slipping.
flavor_text_1: Possessing mighty power, Mudbray can be loaded with 50 times its own body weight and will be totally fine.
flavor_text_2: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.
flavor_text_3: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokemon. It's skilled at making use of mud.
flavor_text_4: It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.
flavor_text_5: It loves playing in the mud. If it isn't showered with mud on a daily basis, it gets stressed out and stops listening to its Trainer.

name: mudsdale
flavor_text_0: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.
flavor_text_1: It remains calm and unmoving no matter the situation. It mixes dirt with the saliva in its mouth to make a special kind of mud.
flavor_text_2: Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks to scrap without breaking a sweat.
flavor_text_3: It can trudge mountain roads without rest for three days and three nights, all the while dragging a 10-ton load.
flavor_text_4: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokemon to scrap a truck with a single kick.
flavor_text_5: Mudsdale has so much stamina that it could carry over 10 tons across the Galar region without rest or sleep.

name: dewpider
flavor_text_0: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.
flavor_text_1: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.
flavor_text_2: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.
flavor_text_3: It can only breathe oxygen that has dissolved in water, so it wears a water bubble on its head when it walks around on land.
flavor_text_4: When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokemon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.
flavor_text_5: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other's way.

name: araquanid
flavor_text_0: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.
flavor_text_1: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokemon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.
flavor_text_2: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokemon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.
flavor_text_3: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn't watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!
flavor_text_4: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokemon can then take its time to savor its meal.
flavor_text_5: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.

name: fomantis
flavor_text_0: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokemon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokemon to gather around it.
flavor_text_1: They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.
flavor_text_2: During the day, Fomantis basks in sunlight and sleeps peacefully. It wakes and moves around at night.
flavor_text_3: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.
flavor_text_4: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.
flavor_text_5: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

name: lurantis
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.
flavor_text_1: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokemon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.
flavor_text_2: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis's vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.
flavor_text_3: The petals on this Pokemon's arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.
flavor_text_4: It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.
flavor_text_5: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokemon.

name: morelull
flavor_text_0: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.
flavor_text_1: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.
flavor_text_2: It likes damp dark places. When night falls, the spores filling the caps of its mushrooms glow.
flavor_text_3: Pokemon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull's head. The caps regrow overnight.
flavor_text_4: It scatters its shining spores around itself. Even though they're dangerous, nighttime tours of forests where Morelull live are popular.
