flavor_text_5: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

name: shiinotic
flavor_text_0: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokemon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.
flavor_text_1: When it starts fighting for territory with Parasect, the entire area gets completely coated in spores!
flavor_text_2: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.
flavor_text_3: It puts its prey to sleep and siphons off their vitality through the tip of its arms. If one of its kind is weakened, it helps by sending it vitality.
flavor_text_4: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don't go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.
flavor_text_5: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokemon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: salandit
flavor_text_0: This sneaky Pokemon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.
flavor_text_1: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokemon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's poisonous gas.
flavor_text_2: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.
flavor_text_3: It weakens opponents and sends them reeling with its poisonous gas. Salandit doesn't deal well with Spinda, since it's always reeling.
flavor_text_4: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can't evolve.
flavor_text_5: Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokemon, then attacks them.

name: salazzle
flavor_text_0: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.
flavor_text_1: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.
flavor_text_2: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.
flavor_text_3: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.
flavor_text_4: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.
flavor_text_5: It punishes Salandit that couldn't bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

name: stufful
flavor_text_0: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokemon could result in painful retaliation.
flavor_text_1: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.
flavor_text_2: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.
flavor_text_3: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It's an incredibly dangerous Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: It boasts power enough to split large trees in half. The organ on its rear releases an odor that it uses to communicate with others of its kind.
flavor_text_5: Stufful hates to be hugged or touched in any way. It will squirm, thrash, and resist with amazing power.

name: bewear
flavor_text_0: This immensely dangerous Pokemon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.
flavor_text_1: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous--it could easily shatter your bones.
flavor_text_2: It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn't run away as fast as possible.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.
flavor_text_4: It boasts tremendous physical strength. Many people call it the most dangerous Pokemon in the Alola region.
flavor_text_5: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.

name: bounsweet
flavor_text_0: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.
flavor_text_1: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.
flavor_text_3: It tries to resist being swallowed by a bird Pokemon by spinning the sepals on its head. It's usually a fruitless attempt.
flavor_text_4: Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokemon are always after it, but it's not intelligent enough to care.
flavor_text_5: Although it's too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet's sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

name: steenee
flavor_text_0: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.
flavor_text_1: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokemon, this Pokemon is totally fine.
flavor_text_2: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokemon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokemon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.
flavor_text_4: It bounces around, swinging the sepals on its head with abandon. They're quite painful when they smack you!
flavor_text_5: It's protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokemon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn't care.

name: tsareena
flavor_text_0: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.
flavor_text_1: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokemon's legs leaves a wound in the opponent's body and soul that will never heal.
flavor_text_2: A Pokemon with an aggressive personality and a mastery of kicking, it cackles every time it kicks an opponent.
flavor_text_3: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.
flavor_text_4: This feared Pokemon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.

name: comfey
flavor_text_0: Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokemon is a hit with many people.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon smell very nice. All Comfey wear different flowers, so each of these Pokemon has its own individual scent.
flavor_text_2: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.
flavor_text_3: It picks flowers and sticks them to its body with fluids it produces. The aroma that wafts from its petals has a healing effect.
flavor_text_4: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.
flavor_text_5: It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn't have any flowers, it feels uneasy.

name: oranguru
flavor_text_0: It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poke Balls and gives other Pokemon orders as it pleases.
flavor_text_1: Oranguru don't get along with each other, so they're always engaging in battles of wits to decide which one is superior.
flavor_text_2: With waves of its fan--made from leaves and its own fur--Oranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokemon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.
flavor_text_4: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokemon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
flavor_text_5: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokemon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it's best suited to veteran Trainers.

name: passimian
flavor_text_0: They use their saliva to stick leaves to their shoulders. You can tell what troop they belong to from the position of the leaves.
flavor_text_1: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.
flavor_text_2: Berries are its weapons as well as the staple of its diet. The one that can throw a berry the farthest is the boss of the troop.
flavor_text_3: They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.
flavor_text_4: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.
flavor_text_5: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable--they will never let down a comrade.

name: wimpod
flavor_text_0: It's nature's cleaner--it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.
flavor_text_1: Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.
flavor_text_3: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy's presence.
flavor_text_4: It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.
flavor_text_5: An astonishingly cowardly Pokemon, Wimpod will whir its legs at high speeds to run away if anything comes near it.

name: golisopod
flavor_text_0: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater--or even air--right in two.
flavor_text_1: Its claws, which it can extend and retract at will, are its greatest weapons. Golisopod is sometimes accompanied by Wimpod.
flavor_text_2: It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.
flavor_text_3: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner's meal.
flavor_text_4: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.
flavor_text_5: The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokemon will do anything it takes to win.

name: sandygast
flavor_text_0: If you build sand mounds when you're playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.
flavor_text_1: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.
flavor_text_2: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokemon embodies the grudges of the departed.
flavor_text_3: It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygast will get serious and fight any children who come to take it back.
flavor_text_4: Sandygast mainly inhabits beaches. It takes control of anyone who puts their hand into its mouth, forcing them to make its body bigger.
flavor_text_5: Grudges of the dead have possessed a mound of sand and become a Pokemon. Sandygast is fond of the shovel on its head.

name: palossand
flavor_text_0: Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokemon snatches away their vitality.
flavor_text_1: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon lives on beaches, but it hates water. Palossand can't maintain its castle-like shape if it gets drenched by a heavy rain.
flavor_text_3: Each of its grains of sand has its own will. Palossand eats small Pokemon and siphons away their vital essence while they're still alive.
flavor_text_4: Possessed people controlled by this Pokemon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.
flavor_text_5: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.

name: pyukumuku
flavor_text_0: These Pokemon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!
flavor_text_1: It's covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.
flavor_text_2: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If you accidentally step on one, you'll slip, and it will get mad and smack you!
flavor_text_3: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.
flavor_text_4: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.
flavor_text_5: The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.

name: type-null
flavor_text_0: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokemon being created in the Galar region.
flavor_text_1: There's danger of its going on a rampage, so its true power is sealed away beneath its control mask.
flavor_text_2: A Pokemon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.
flavor_text_3: Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokemon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.
flavor_text_4: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokemon has some hidden special power.
flavor_text_5: It was modeled after a mighty Pokemon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.

name: silvally
flavor_text_0: This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.
flavor_text_1: Through the bond it formed with its Trainer, its will was strengthened, and it was able to destroy its control mask.
flavor_text_2: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokemon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.
flavor_text_3: Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.
flavor_text_4: The final factor needed to release this Pokemon's true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.
flavor_text_5: A solid bond of trust between this Pokemon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

name: minior
flavor_text_0: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.
flavor_text_1: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokemon was born from mutated nanoparticles.
flavor_text_2: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokemon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.
flavor_text_3: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

name: komala
flavor_text_0: The log it holds was given to it by its parents at birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.
flavor_text_1: It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.
flavor_text_2: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.
flavor_text_3: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.

name: turtonator
flavor_text_0: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.
flavor_text_1: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.
flavor_text_2: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.
flavor_text_3: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.
flavor_text_4: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.
flavor_text_5: It lives in volcanoes and eats sulfur and other minerals. Materials from the food it eats form the basis of its explosive shell.

name: togedemaru
flavor_text_0: When it's in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.
flavor_text_1: When it's surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.
flavor_text_2: Its capacity to produce electricity is somewhat limited, so it gets charged up by letting lightning strike it!
flavor_text_3: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.
flavor_text_4: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokemon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.
flavor_text_5: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokemon takes in electricity from other electric Pokemon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: mimikyu
flavor_text_0: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu's old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.
flavor_text_1: Although it's a quiet, lonely Pokemon, if you try to look at what's under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.
flavor_text_2: A gust of wind revealed what hides under this Pokemon's rag to a passing Trainer, who went home and died painfully that very night.
flavor_text_3: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.
flavor_text_4: A lonely Pokemon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: bruxish
flavor_text_0: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder's shell is no match for it.
flavor_text_1: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.
flavor_text_2: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.
flavor_text_3: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

name: drampa
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.
flavor_text_1: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokemon--up until it's angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.
flavor_text_2: If a child it has made friends with is bullied, Drampa will find the bully's house and burn it to the ground.
flavor_text_3: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
flavor_text_4: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.
flavor_text_5: It appears in towns and plays with the children. Drampa will protect kids when they're in danger, so their moms don't have to worry.

name: dhelmise
flavor_text_0: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokemon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.
flavor_text_1: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.
flavor_text_2: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.
flavor_text_4: Its chain-like green seaweed can stretch outward for hundreds of yards. For some reason, it gets along well with Skrelp.
flavor_text_5: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.

name: jangmo-o
flavor_text_0: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.
flavor_text_1: They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow little by little as they battle one another.
flavor_text_2: It will never show an enemy its back in battle. Ancient warriors liked Jangmo-o for its valiant disposition and made it one of their own.
flavor_text_3: It smacks the scales on its head against rocks or against the ground to frighten its opponents. It can also contact its friends with these noises.
flavor_text_4: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.
flavor_text_5: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that's become as hard as metal.

name: hakamo-o
flavor_text_0: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.
flavor_text_1: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.
flavor_text_2: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.
flavor_text_3: The scales it sheds can be molded and processed to make pots and pans. They conduct heat well, so they're a popular item.
flavor_text_4: It makes noise by clanging its scales together. When the rhythm has reached its peak, Hakamo-o attacks.
flavor_text_5: It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they're regrown.

name: kommo-o
flavor_text_0: Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.
flavor_text_1: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokemon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.
flavor_text_2: When it howls after finishing off its prey, the metallic sounds of its celebrating comrades can be heard from all around.
flavor_text_3: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.
flavor_text_4: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.
flavor_text_5: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

name: tapu-koko
flavor_text_0: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.
flavor_text_1: Although it's called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokemon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.
flavor_text_2: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.
flavor_text_3: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

name: tapu-lele
flavor_text_0: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.
flavor_text_1: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.
flavor_text_2: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.
flavor_text_3: It heals the wounds of people and Pokemon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

name: tapu-bulu
flavor_text_0: The guardian deity of Ula'ula is a lazy Pokemon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.
flavor_text_1: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula'ula controls plants.
flavor_text_2: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.
flavor_text_3: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

name: tapu-fini
flavor_text_0: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.
flavor_text_1: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.
flavor_text_2: The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.
flavor_text_3: Although it's called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

name: cosmog
flavor_text_0: Cosmog is very curious but not very cautious, often placing itself in danger. If things start to look dicey, it teleports away.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon came from another universe. Its gaseous body is so light that even a gentle breeze can blow it away.
flavor_text_2: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.
flavor_text_3: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It's said to be a Pokemon from another world, but no specific details are known.
flavor_text_4: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.
flavor_text_5: Whether or not it's a Pokemon from this world is a mystery. When it's in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

name: cosmoem
flavor_text_0: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.
flavor_text_1: The absorption of starlight fuels this Pokemon's growth. The shell that encases it is harder than any known material.
flavor_text_2: It sucks in dust from the air at an astounding rate, frantically building up energy within its core as preparation for evolution.
flavor_text_3: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the "cocoon of the stars" and built an altar to worship it.
flavor_text_4: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.
flavor_text_5: There's something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokemon may come from another world.

name: solgaleo
flavor_text_0: When light radiates from its body, this Pokemon could almost appear to be the sun. It will dispel any darkness and light up the world.
flavor_text_1: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.
flavor_text_2: In writings from the distant past, it's called by the name "the beast that devours the sun."
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.
flavor_text_4: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.
flavor_text_5: Solgaleo was once known as the Beast That Devours the Sun. Energy in the form of light radiates boundlessly from it.

name: lunala
flavor_text_0: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name "the beast that calls the moon."
flavor_text_1: Known as the Beast That Calls the Moon, this Pokemon lives by taking in any and all light and converting it into its own energy.
flavor_text_2: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.
flavor_text_3: It steals the light from its surroundings and then becomes the full moon, showering its own light across the night sky.
flavor_text_4: Said to live in another world, this Pokemon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.
flavor_text_5: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

name: nihilego
flavor_text_0: One of the Ultra Beasts. It's unclear whether or not this Pokemon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.
flavor_text_1: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.
flavor_text_2: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

name: buzzwole
flavor_text_0: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_1: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.
flavor_text_2: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.
flavor_text_3: A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.

name: pheromosa
flavor_text_0: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_1: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.
flavor_text_2: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.
flavor_text_3: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.

name: xurkitree
flavor_text_0: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.
flavor_text_1: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_2: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.
flavor_text_3: They've been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

name: celesteela
flavor_text_0: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_1: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.
flavor_text_2: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.
flavor_text_3: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

name: kartana
flavor_text_0: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_1: One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.
flavor_text_2: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.
flavor_text_3: This Ultra Beast's body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

name: guzzlord
flavor_text_0: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
flavor_text_1: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry--it is certainly always devouring something.
flavor_text_2: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It's one of the Ultra Beasts.
flavor_text_3: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.

name: necrozma
flavor_text_0: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.
flavor_text_1: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.
flavor_text_2: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.
flavor_text_3: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.
flavor_text_4: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.
flavor_text_5: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

name: magearna
flavor_text_0: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.
flavor_text_1: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.
flavor_text_2: This artificial Pokemon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.
flavor_text_3: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name: marshadow
flavor_text_0: By slipping into the shadow of a martial arts master and copying their movements, this Pokemon learned the ultimate techniques.
flavor_text_1: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon can conceal itself in any shadow, so it went undiscovered for a long time.
flavor_text_3: It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their movements and powers. This Pokemon is craven and cowering.
flavor_text_4: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.
flavor_text_5: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokemon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.

name: poipole
flavor_text_0: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.
flavor_text_1: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

name: naganadel
flavor_text_0: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.
flavor_text_1: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

name: stakataka
flavor_text_0: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute's true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.
flavor_text_1: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

name: blacephalon
flavor_text_0: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents' surprise to rob them of their vitality.
flavor_text_1: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: zeraora
flavor_text_0: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.
flavor_text_1: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.
flavor_text_2: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.
flavor_text_3: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

name: meltan
flavor_text_0: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.
flavor_text_1: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.
flavor_text_2: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

name: melmetal
flavor_text_0: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal's heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
flavor_text_2: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: grookey
flavor_text_0: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
flavor_text_1: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: thwackey
flavor_text_0: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.
flavor_text_1: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

name: rillaboom
flavor_text_0: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
flavor_text_1: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: scorbunny
flavor_text_0: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
flavor_text_1: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokemon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

name: raboot
flavor_text_0: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
flavor_text_1: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

name: cinderace
flavor_text_0: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.
flavor_text_1: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

name: sobble
flavor_text_0: When scared, this Pokemon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.
flavor_text_1: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokemon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

name: drizzile
flavor_text_0: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
flavor_text_1: A clever combatant, this Pokemon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

name: inteleon
flavor_text_0: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
flavor_text_1: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: skwovet
flavor_text_0: It eats berries nonstop--a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.
flavor_text_1: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokemon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

name: greedent
flavor_text_0: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokemon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.
flavor_text_1: It stashes berries in its tail--so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokemon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.

name: rookidee
flavor_text_0: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokemon benefits from every battle--even a defeat increases its strength a bit.
flavor_text_1: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokemon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

name: corvisquire
flavor_text_0: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokemon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.
flavor_text_1: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

name: corviknight
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
flavor_text_1: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokemon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

name: blipbug
flavor_text_0: A constant collector of information, this Pokemon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.
flavor_text_1: Often found in gardens, this Pokemon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: dottler
flavor_text_0: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.
flavor_text_1: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: orbeetle
flavor_text_0: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.
flavor_text_1: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it--and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

name: nickit
flavor_text_0: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
flavor_text_1: Cunning and cautious, this Pokemon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

name: thievul
flavor_text_0: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
flavor_text_1: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

name: gossifleur
flavor_text_0: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: eldegoss
flavor_text_0: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokemon can benefit from them.
flavor_text_1: The cotton on the head of this Pokemon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn--a Galar regional specialty.

name: wooloo
flavor_text_0: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokemon is surprisingly strong.
flavor_text_1: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokemon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: dubwool
flavor_text_0: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
flavor_text_1: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: chewtle
flavor_text_0: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.
flavor_text_1: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokemon bites down and never lets go.

name: drednaw
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.
flavor_text_1: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokemon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: yamper
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.
flavor_text_1: This gluttonous Pokemon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

name: boltund
flavor_text_0: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

name: rolycoly
flavor_text_0: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokemon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.
flavor_text_1: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

name: carkol
flavor_text_0: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokemon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

name: coalossal
flavor_text_0: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

name: applin
flavor_text_0: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokemon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.
flavor_text_1: As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

name: flapple
flavor_text_0: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.
flavor_text_1: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: appletun
flavor_text_0: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokemon it preys on.
flavor_text_1: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

name: silicobra
flavor_text_0: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.
flavor_text_1: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

name: sandaconda
flavor_text_0: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.
flavor_text_1: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

name: cramorant
flavor_text_0: This hungry Pokemon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokemon other than its preferred prey.
flavor_text_1: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

name: arrokuda
flavor_text_0: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.
flavor_text_1: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokemon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.

name: barraskewda
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.
flavor_text_1: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

name: toxel
flavor_text_0: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.
flavor_text_1: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokemon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: toxtricity
flavor_text_0: When this Pokemon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
flavor_text_1: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokemon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

name: sizzlipede
flavor_text_0: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.
flavor_text_1: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

name: centiskorch
flavor_text_0: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
flavor_text_1: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokemon also has large and very sharp fangs.

name: clobbopus
flavor_text_0: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.
flavor_text_1: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens--it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: grapploct
flavor_text_0: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
flavor_text_1: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokemon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: sinistea
flavor_text_0: The teacup in which this Pokemon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

name: polteageist
flavor_text_0: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokemon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.
flavor_text_1: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

name: hatenna
flavor_text_0: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.
flavor_text_1: If this Pokemon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

name: hattrem
flavor_text_0: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.
flavor_text_1: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokemon, it will silence you violently.

name: hatterene
flavor_text_0: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokemon is also known as the Forest Witch.
flavor_text_1: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: impidimp
flavor_text_0: It sneaks into people's homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.
flavor_text_1: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokemon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: morgrem
flavor_text_0: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.
flavor_text_1: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: grimmsnarl
flavor_text_0: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.
flavor_text_1: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokemon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: obstagoon
flavor_text_0: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
flavor_text_1: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout--this move is known as Obstruct.

name: perrserker
flavor_text_0: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.
flavor_text_1: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokemon lives for the thrill of battle.

name: cursola
flavor_text_0: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You'll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
flavor_text_1: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokemon's core spirit.

name: sirfetchd
flavor_text_0: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
flavor_text_1: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokemon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.

name: mr-rime
flavor_text_0: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
flavor_text_1: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

name: runerigus
flavor_text_0: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
flavor_text_1: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

name: milcery
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
flavor_text_1: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

name: alcremie
flavor_text_0: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.
flavor_text_1: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

name: falinks
flavor_text_0: The six of them work together as one Pokemon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.
flavor_text_1: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

name: pincurchin
flavor_text_0: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
flavor_text_1: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

name: snom
flavor_text_0: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.
flavor_text_1: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

name: frosmoth
flavor_text_0: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than -290 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

name: stonjourner
flavor_text_0: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokemon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.
flavor_text_1: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

name: eiscue
flavor_text_0: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

name: indeedee
flavor_text_0: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.
flavor_text_1: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

name: morpeko
flavor_text_0: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokemon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.
flavor_text_1: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they're precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

name: cufant
flavor_text_0: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.
flavor_text_1: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokemon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.

name: copperajah
flavor_text_0: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

name: dracozolt
flavor_text_0: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.
flavor_text_1: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

name: arctozolt
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.
flavor_text_1: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

name: dracovish
flavor_text_0: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokemon can't breathe unless it's underwater.
flavor_text_1: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

name: arctovish
flavor_text_0: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokemon go extinct anyway.
flavor_text_1: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

name: duraludon
flavor_text_0: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokemon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.
flavor_text_1: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: dreepy
flavor_text_0: If this weak Pokemon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.
flavor_text_1: After being reborn as a ghost Pokemon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

name: drakloak
flavor_text_0: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it'll try to substitute any Pokemon it finds for the missing Dreepy.
flavor_text_1: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: dragapult
flavor_text_0: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.
flavor_text_1: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult's horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

name: zacian
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon has slumbered for many years. Some say it's Zamazenta's elder sister--others say the two Pokemon are rivals.
flavor_text_1: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokemon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: zamazenta
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.
flavor_text_1: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: eternatus
flavor_text_0: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.
flavor_text_1: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokemon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

name: kubfu
flavor_text_0: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.
flavor_text_1: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

name: urshifu
flavor_text_0: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.
flavor_text_1: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokemon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

name: zarude
flavor_text_0: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
flavor_text_1: Within dense forests, this Pokemon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokemon of the forest fear it.

name: regieleki
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon is a cluster of electrical energy. It's said that removing the rings on Regieleki's body will unleash the Pokemon's latent power.
flavor_text_1: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar's electricity.

name: regidrago
flavor_text_0: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago's arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokemon. The theory remains unproven.

name: glastrier
flavor_text_0: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It's also a belligerent Pokemon--anything it wants, it takes by force.
flavor_text_1: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

name: spectrier
flavor_text_0: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one--it doesn't use its sense of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to separate soul from body.
flavor_text_1: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

name: calyrex
flavor_text_0: Calyrex is a merciful Pokemon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.
flavor_text_1: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

name: wyrdeer
flavor_text_0: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokemon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

name: kleavor
flavor_text_0: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokemon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.

name: ursaluna
flavor_text_0: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

name: basculegion
flavor_text_0: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

name: sneasler
flavor_text_0: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

name: overqwil
flavor_text_0: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname "sea fiend." It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

name: enamorus
flavor_text_0: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokemon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

name: deoxys
flavor_text_0: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKeMON's chest appears to be its brain.
flavor_text_1: When it changes form, an aurora appears. It absorbs attacks by altering its cellular structure.
flavor_text_2: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokemon's chest appears to be its brain.
flavor_text_3: This DEOXYS has transformed into its aggressive guise. It can fool enemies by altering its appearance.
flavor_text_4: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokemon. It appears where auroras are seen.
flavor_text_5: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokemon.
flavor_text_6: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokemon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.
flavor_text_7: DEOXYS emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This POKeMON shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.
flavor_text_8: A POKeMON that mutated from an extraterrestrial virus exposed to a laser beam. Its body is configured for superior agility and speed.

flavor_text_8: A POKeMON that mutated from an extraterrestrial virus exposed to a laser beam. Its body is configured for superior agility and speed.

name: wormadam
flavor_text_0: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
flavor_text_1: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.
flavor_text_2: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.
flavor_text_3: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
flavor_text_4: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: wormadam
flavor_text_0: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.
flavor_text_1: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.
flavor_text_2: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.
flavor_text_3: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
flavor_text_4: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: shaymin
flavor_text_0: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.
flavor_text_1: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.
flavor_text_2: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.
flavor_text_3: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
flavor_text_4: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
flavor_text_5: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings  of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: giratina
flavor_text_0: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
flavor_text_1: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
flavor_text_3: A Pokemon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: rotom
flavor_text_0: Research continues on this Pokemon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
flavor_text_1: This bizarre Pokemon appears to be a will-o'-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.
flavor_text_2: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
flavor_text_3: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.
flavor_text_4: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.
flavor_text_5: With a body made of plasma, it can inhabit all sorts of machines. It loves to surprise others.

name: rotom
flavor_text_0: Research continues on this Pokemon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

name: basculin
flavor_text_0: In the past, it often appeared on the dinner table. The meat of red-striped Basculin is on the fatty side, and it's more popular with the youth.
flavor_text_1: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor--this one is gentle--I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
flavor_text_2: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.
flavor_text_3: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they'll start fighting instantly. These Pokemon are very hostile.
flavor_text_4: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.
flavor_text_5: When a school of Basculin appears in a lake, everything else disappears, except for Corphish and Crawdaunt. That's how violent Basculin are.
flavor_text_6: Savage, violent Pokemon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.
flavor_text_7: Anglers love the fight this Pokemon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch-- many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: darmanitan
flavor_text_0: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokemon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.
flavor_text_1: Its internal fire burns at 2,500deg F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_2: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_3: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
flavor_text_4: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: meloetta
flavor_text_0: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
flavor_text_1: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.
flavor_text_2: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokemon that hear them happy or sad.

name: tornadus
flavor_text_0: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
flavor_text_1: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.
flavor_text_2: This storm-stirring Pokemon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.
flavor_text_3: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: thundurus
flavor_text_0: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.
flavor_text_1: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
flavor_text_2: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.
flavor_text_3: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: landorus
flavor_text_0: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
flavor_text_1: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.
flavor_text_2: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.
flavor_text_3: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

name: kyurem
flavor_text_0: It can produce ultracold air. Its body is frozen.
flavor_text_1: It appears that this Pokemon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.
flavor_text_2: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
flavor_text_3: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.
flavor_text_4: This legendary ice Pokemon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

flavor_text_1: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
flavor_text_2: They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokemon's true power will awaken.
flavor_text_3: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
flavor_text_4: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

name: meowstic
flavor_text_0: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.
flavor_text_1: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.
flavor_text_2: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
flavor_text_3: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

name: aegislash
flavor_text_0: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokemon to build a kingdom to its liking.
flavor_text_1: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokemon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_2: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.
flavor_text_3: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

name: pumpkaboo

flavor_text_1: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo's body. They're then moved on to the afterlife.
flavor_text_2: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
flavor_text_3: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: blastoise
flavor_text_0: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
flavor_text_1: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokemon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.
flavor_text_2: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punch ing holes through thick steel.
flavor_text_3: The waterspouts that protrude from its shell are highly accurate. Their bullets of water can precisely nail tin cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_4: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.
flavor_text_5: BLASTOISE has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_6: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
flavor_text_7: A brutal POKeMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
flavor_text_8: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_9: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.
flavor_text_10: It firmly plants its feet on the ground before shooting water from the jets on its back.
