name: alakazam
flavor_text_0: ALAKAZAM's brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this POKeMON an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.
flavor_text_1: A POKeMON that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns-- that's why this POKeMON is smart.
flavor_text_2: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.
flavor_text_3: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
flavor_text_4: Its highly developed brain is on par with a supercomputer. It can use all forms of psychic abilities.
flavor_text_5: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
flavor_text_6: ALAKAZAM's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This POKeMON holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
flavor_text_7: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.
flavor_text_8: It has an IQ of 5000. It calcu lates many things in order to gain the edge in every battle.
flavor_text_9: It does not like physical attacks very  much. Instead, it freely uses extra sensory powers to defeat foes.
flavor_text_10: Alakazam wields potent psychic powers. It's said that this Pokemon used these powers to create the spoons it holds.
flavor_text_11: Its superb memory lets it recall everything it has experienced from birth. Its IQ exceeds 5,000.
flavor_text_12: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokemon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
flavor_text_13: Its brain cells continue to increase in number until its death. The older the Alakazam, the larger its head.
flavor_text_14: If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that spoon is apparently delicious.
flavor_text_15: While it has strong psychic abilities and high intelligence, an ALAKAZAM's muscles are very weak. It uses psychic power to move its body.
flavor_text_16: Its brain cells multiply continu ally until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.

name: gengar
flavor_text_0: Lurking in the shadowy corners of rooms, it awaits chances to steal its prey's life force.
flavor_text_1: A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_2: A GENGAR is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_3: Under a full moon, this POKeMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.
flavor_text_4: It steals heat from its surround ings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_5: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
flavor_text_6: It hides in shadows. It is said that if Gengar is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_7: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_8: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be GENGAR's doing.
flavor_text_9: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_10: Even your home isn't safe. Gengar will lurk in whatever dark corner of a room it can find and wait for its chance to catch its prey.
flavor_text_11: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!
flavor_text_12: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.
flavor_text_13: It apparently wishes for a traveling companion. Since it was once human itself, it tries to create one by taking the lives of other humans.
flavor_text_14: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.
flavor_text_15: It steals heat from its surroundings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_16: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_17: Deep in the night, your shadow cast by a streetlight may suddenly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_18: It hides in shadows. It is said that if GENGAR is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees F.
flavor_text_19: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a GENGAR delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_20: Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.
flavor_text_21: You can hear tales told all over the world about how Gengar will pay a visit to children who are naughty.
flavor_text_22: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

name: kangaskhan
flavor_text_0: To avoid crushing the baby it carries in its pouch, it always sleeps standing up.
flavor_text_1: If you come across a young KANGASKHAN playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby POKeMON's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.
flavor_text_2: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokemon's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.
flavor_text_3: You shouldn't get close to the child when it's playing outside its mother's pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.
flavor_text_4: The child in its pouch leaves home after roughly three years. That is the only time the mother is heard to cry wildly.
flavor_text_5: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is three years old.
flavor_text_6: The female raises its offspring in a pouch on its belly. It is skilled at attacking using COMET PUNCH.
flavor_text_7: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.
flavor_text_8: Raises its young in its belly pouch. Won't run from any fight to keep its young protected.
flavor_text_9: Kangaskhan's maternal love is so deep that it will brave death to protect its offspring.
flavor_text_10: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.
flavor_text_11: If you come across a young KANGASKHAN playing by itself, never try to catch it. The baby's parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged.
flavor_text_12: Although it's carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.
flavor_text_13: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.
flavor_text_14: To protect its young, it will never give up during battle, no matter how badly wounded it is.
flavor_text_15: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.
flavor_text_16: Kangaskhan protects its child by keeping it in its pouch. It has zero forgiveness for those who harm its child and will beat them down.

name: pinsir
flavor_text_0: With its pincer horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.
flavor_text_1: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.
flavor_text_2: Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can't move if it's cold, so it lives in warm places.
flavor_text_3: Their pincers are strong enough to shatter thick logs. Because they dislike cold, PINSIR burrow and sleep under the ground on chilly nights.
flavor_text_4: It grips prey with its powerful pincers and will not let go until the prey is torn in half.
flavor_text_5: It gets into territorial disputes with Vikavolt. For some reason, it apparently gets along well with Heracross in Alola.
flavor_text_6: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokemon's movements turn sluggish in cold places.
flavor_text_7: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.
flavor_text_8: Its two long pincer horns are powerful. Once they grip an enemy, they won't release until the foe is torn.
flavor_text_9: PINSIR has a pair of massive horns  Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe's body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.
flavor_text_10: These Pokemon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.
flavor_text_11: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.
flavor_text_12: This Pokemon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.
flavor_text_13: Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can't move if it's cold out, so it lives in warm places.
flavor_text_14: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.
flavor_text_15: Swings its long antlers wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.
flavor_text_16: If it fails to crush the foe in its pincers, it will swing around and toss the opponent.
flavor_text_17: Pinsir has a pair of massive horns. Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe's body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.
flavor_text_18: It grips its prey in its pincers and splits them apart. Although it is a powerful Pokemon, it can't deal with the cold.
flavor_text_19: With its horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.
flavor_text_20: Although it's tough, it can't handle cold well. When night falls, it buries itself in leafage and sleeps.
flavor_text_21: PINSIR is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This POKeMON's movements turn sluggish in cold places.
flavor_text_22: When the tempera ture drops at night, it sleeps on treetops or among roots where it is well hidden.

name: gyarados
flavor_text_0: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
flavor_text_1: It is an extremely vicious and violent POKeMON. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames.
flavor_text_2: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.
flavor_text_3: Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.
flavor_text_4: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.
flavor_text_5: They say that during past strife, GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.
flavor_text_6: Once it appears, it goes on a ram page. It remains enraged until it demolishes every thing around it.
flavor_text_7: Once GYARADOS goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn't calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this POKeMON's rampages lasting a whole month.
flavor_text_8: The energy from evolution stimulated its brain cells strongly, causing it to become very ferocious.
flavor_text_9: They say that during past wars, GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.
flavor_text_10: I suspect this Pokemon to be the true identity of a dragon written of in ancient texts, which claimed that it razed an entire village with white-hot beams from its maw.
flavor_text_11: Once it appears, its rage never settles until it has razed the fields and mountains around it.
flavor_text_12: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.
flavor_text_13: Once Gyarados goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn't calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this Pokemon's rampages lasting a whole month.
flavor_text_14: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The HYPER BEAM it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.
flavor_text_15: A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind.
flavor_text_16: In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared.
flavor_text_17: Once it begins to rampage, a GYARADOS will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.
flavor_text_18: When MAGIKARP evolves into GYARADOS, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this POKeMON's wildly violent nature.
flavor_text_19: It appears when ever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.
flavor_text_20: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokemon's wildly violent nature.
flavor_text_21: There are people who swear that any place Gyarados appears is fated for destruction.
flavor_text_22: It fires hyper beams in all directions, burning the surrounding area to ash. There are some regions where it's called "the deity of destruction."
flavor_text_23: In ancient literature, there is a record of a GYARADOS that razed a village when violence flared.

flavor_text_1: A Pokemon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

flavor_text_3: A Pokemon from the age of the dinosaurs. It used its sawlike fangs to shred its prey before eating them.
flavor_text_4: It flew through the open skies over the ancient continent as if they were its own. When it touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.
flavor_text_5: This vicious POKe MON is said to have flown in an cient skies while shrieking high- pitched cries.
flavor_text_6: A savage POKeMON that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.
flavor_text_7: AERODACTYL is a POKeMON from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from DNA extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies.
flavor_text_8: A vicious Pokemon from the distant past, it appears to have flown by spreading its wings and gliding.
flavor_text_9: In prehistoric times, this POKeMON flew freely and fearlessly through the skies.
flavor_text_10: Aerodactyl is a Pokemon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

flavor_text_13: A savage Pokemon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

name: ampharos
flavor_text_0: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.
flavor_text_1: The light from its tail can be seen from space. This is why you can always tell exactly where it is, which is why it usually keeps the light off.
flavor_text_2: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.
flavor_text_3: AMPHAROS gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this POKeMON to send signals back and forth with others far away.
flavor_text_4: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean's surface.
flavor_text_5: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.
flavor_text_6: The tip of its tail shines so brightly it can be used to send sea-navigation beacons to distant foreign shores.
flavor_text_7: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokemon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

flavor_text_9: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: scizor
flavor_text_0: Once it has identified something as an enemy, it will continue beating them with its steel-hard pincers until there's nothing left but scraps.
flavor_text_1: A SCIZOR has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.
flavor_text_2: Though its body is slim, Scizor has tremendous attacking power. Even Scizor's muscles are made of metal.
flavor_text_3: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.
flavor_text_4: Its body is like steel. Its tough, heavy pincers are more suited to smashing enemies than grabbing them.
flavor_text_5: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
flavor_text_6: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets ahold of into bits.
flavor_text_8: This POKeMON's pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets a hold of into bits.

flavor_text_13: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.
flavor_text_14: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.
flavor_text_15: Evolved by way of a curious item. The shell covering its body has been shown to be stronger than forged steel.
flavor_text_16: Once it has identified an enemy, this Pokemon smashes it mercilessly with pincers hard as steel.

name: heracross
flavor_text_0: It roams through forests searching for sweet nectar. Although it boasts fantastic physical strength, it's not that good at flying.
flavor_text_1: It loves sweet honey. To keep all the honey to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.
flavor_text_2: It gathers in forests to search for tree sap, its favorite food. It's strong enough to hurl foes.
flavor_text_3: Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokemon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.
flavor_text_4: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.
flavor_text_5: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.
flavor_text_6: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw arou nd an object that is 100 times its own weight.

flavor_text_8: HERACROSS has sharp claws on its feet. These are planted firmly into the ground or the bark of a tree, giving the POKeMON a secure and solid footing to forcefully fling away foes with its proud horn.

flavor_text_10: Usually docile, but if disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

flavor_text_20: It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

name: houndoom
flavor_text_0: In a HOUNDOOM pack, the one with its horns raked sharply back serves a leadership role. They choose their leader by fighting among themselves.
flavor_text_1: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
flavor_text_2: The pungent- smelling flame that shoots from its mouth results from toxins burn ing in its body.
flavor_text_3: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other POKeMON get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.
flavor_text_4: They spew flames mixed with poison to finish off their opponents. They divvy up their prey evenly among the members of their pack.
flavor_text_5: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokemon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

flavor_text_10: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokemon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

name: mawile
flavor_text_0: A cunning and terrifying Pokemon, its cuteness makes opponents let down their guard--and then it swallows them whole with its huge jaws.
flavor_text_1: Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

name: garchomp

flavor_text_11: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.

flavor_text_6: A powerful Pokemon that can split huge boulders with ease. Dislikes associating with others and chooses to live quietly deep within the mountains, playing with the snow.

flavor_text_3: It raises flowers and uses them as weapons. The more gorgeous the blossom, the more power it contains.

flavor_text_1: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokemon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

flavor_text_8: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokemon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.

flavor_text_0: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
flavor_text_1: Sharply attuned to others' wishes for help, this Pokemon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.

flavor_text_0: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.
flavor_text_1: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

flavor_text_4: This Pokemon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures' feelings and physical conditions.

name: sharpedo
flavor_text_0: Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokemon's drawback is its inability to swim long distances.
flavor_text_1: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.
flavor_text_2: Nicknamed "the bully of the sea," SHARPEDO is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these POKeMON can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
flavor_text_3: The vicious and sly gangster of the sea. Its skin is specially textured to minimize drag in water. Its speed tops out at over 75 miles per hour.
flavor_text_4: The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that crunch through iron. It swims by jetting water from its rear.
flavor_text_5: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.
flavor_text_6: SHARPEDO can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This POKeMON's drawback is its inability to swim long distances.
flavor_text_7: Nicknamed "the bully of the sea," Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokemon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
flavor_text_8: People believe that carrying one of its discarded fangs will prevent mishaps at sea, so the fangs are made into accessories.
flavor_text_9: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."
flavor_text_10: It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokemon became a victim of overfishing.
flavor_text_11: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It's very sensitive to the scent of blood.
flavor_text_12: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.
flavor_text_13: This Pokemon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked--no exceptions.

name: slowbro
flavor_text_0: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.
flavor_text_1: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to SHELLDER's seeping poison.
flavor_text_2: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the SHELLDER on its tail bites down.
flavor_text_3: Its tail has a SHELLDER firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.
flavor_text_4: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.
flavor_text_5: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

flavor_text_9: An attached SHELLDER won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
flavor_text_10: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder's poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.
flavor_text_11: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
flavor_text_12: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.
flavor_text_13: Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.
flavor_text_14: The SHELLDER that latches onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's leftover scraps.
flavor_text_15: Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.
flavor_text_16: Lives lazily by the sea. If the SHELLDER on its tail comes off, it becomes a SLOWPOKE again.
flavor_text_17: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.

flavor_text_20: Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more sweetness from Slowbro's tail, has metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.
flavor_text_21: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordi nary SLOWPOKE.

name: steelix
flavor_text_0: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokemon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokemon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
flavor_text_1: The many small metal particles that cover this POKeMON's body reflect bright light well.
flavor_text_2: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.
flavor_text_3: It's said that if an ONIX lives for 100 years, its composition becomes diamondlike as it evolves into a STEELIX.
flavor_text_4: STEELIX live even further underground than ONIX. This POKeMON is known to dig toward the earth's core, reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
flavor_text_5: STEELIX lives even further underground than ONIX. This POKeMON is known to dig towards the earth's core. There are records of this POKeMON reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.
flavor_text_6: This Pokemon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard--not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.
flavor_text_7: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.
flavor_text_8: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than diamond.
flavor_text_9: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
flavor_text_10: The iron it ingested with the soil it swallowed transformed its body and made it harder than diamonds.
flavor_text_11: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.
flavor_text_12: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.
flavor_text_13: It is said that if an ONIX lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: pidgeot
flavor_text_0: This POKeMON has gorgeous, glossy feathers. Many TRAINERS are so captivated by the beautiful feathers on its head that they choose PIDGEOT as their POKeMON.
flavor_text_1: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.
flavor_text_2: Its well-developed chest muscles make it strong enough to whip up a gusty windstorm with just a few flaps.
flavor_text_3: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.
flavor_text_4: Its outstanding vision allows it to spot splashing MAGIKARP, even while flying at 3300 feet.
flavor_text_5: It spreads its beautiful wings wide to frighten its enemies. It can fly at Mach 2 speed.
flavor_text_6: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.
flavor_text_7: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
flavor_text_8: This Pokemon has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many Trainers are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose Pidgeot as their Pokemon.
flavor_text_9: By flapping its wings with all its might, PIDGEOT can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
flavor_text_10: This POKeMON flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.
flavor_text_11: This POKeMON has a dazzling plumage of beautifully glossy feathers. Many TRAINERS are captivated by the striking beauty of the feathers on its head, compelling them to choose PIDGEOT as their POKeMON.
flavor_text_12: This Pokemon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

name: glalie
flavor_text_0: A GLALIE has the power to instantaneously freeze moisture in the atmosphere. A dazzling cloud of diamondlike ice crystals forms around its body.
flavor_text_1: Glalie has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its prey solid. After immobilizing its prey in ice, this Pokemon enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.
flavor_text_2: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they're in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.
flavor_text_3: It covers its body with an armor of ice harder than steel. Uses its breath to freeze prey, which it then devours as if they were frozen desserts.
flavor_text_4: Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokemon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.
flavor_text_5: GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This POKeMON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.
flavor_text_6: To protect itself, it clads its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.
flavor_text_7: To protect itself, it clad its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.
flavor_text_8: It has a body of ice that won't melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.
flavor_text_9: Legend says a boulder on an icy mountain absorbed the distress and regrets of a stranded mountaineer, giving rise to Glalie.
flavor_text_10: GLALIE has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its foe solid. After immobilizing its foe in ice, this POKeMON enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.
flavor_text_11: It freezes its prey and chews them whole. However, it prefers to eat Pokemon like Vanillite that are already frozen.
flavor_text_12: Its actual body is a rock that isn't particularly hard. Glalie absorbs moisture from the air and drapes itself in an armor of ice.
flavor_text_13: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.
flavor_text_14: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: diancie
flavor_text_0: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
flavor_text_1: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: metagross
flavor_text_0: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
flavor_text_1: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.
flavor_text_2: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokemon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
flavor_text_3: It boasts not only psychic powers but also fantastic strength. It grabs its prey with its four legs and holds them in place with its claws.
flavor_text_4: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokemon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.
flavor_text_5: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.
flavor_text_6: It is formed by two METANG fusing. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.
flavor_text_7: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokemon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.
flavor_text_8: METAGROSS has four brains that are joined by a complex neural network. As a result of integration, this POKeMON is smarter than a supercomputer.
flavor_text_9: METAGROSS is the result of two METANG achieving fusion. When hunting, this POKeMON pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large  mouth on its stomach.
flavor_text_10: METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKeMON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.
flavor_text_11: METANG combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
flavor_text_12: With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.
flavor_text_13: It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.
flavor_text_14: Metagross is the result of two Metang achieving fusion. When hunting, this Pokemon pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large mouth on its stomach.
flavor_text_15: A linkage of two Metang, this Pokemon can perform any calculation in a flash by utilizing parallel processing in its four brains.

name: kyogre
flavor_text_0: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
flavor_text_1: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.
flavor_text_2: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKeMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.
flavor_text_3: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
flavor_text_4: KYOGRE is named in mythology as the POKeMON that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with GROUDON.
flavor_text_5: A mythical Pokemon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.
flavor_text_6: KYOGRE has appeared in mythology as the creator of the sea. After long years of feuding with GROUDON, it took to sleep at the bottom of the sea.
flavor_text_7: A mythical Pokemon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with GROUDON.
flavor_text_8: This POKeMON is said to have expanded the sea by bringing heavy rains. It has the power to control water.

name: groudon
flavor_text_0: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought KYOGRE long ago.
flavor_text_1: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.
flavor_text_2: This legendary POKeMON is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling KYOGRE.
flavor_text_3: GROUDON has the power to scatter rain clouds and make water evaporate with light and heat. It came as a savior to people who had been suffering from terrible floods.
flavor_text_4: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
flavor_text_5: GROUDON has appeared in mythology as the creator of the land. It sleeps in magma underground and is said to make volcanoes erupt on awakening.
flavor_text_6: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKeMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKeMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.
flavor_text_7: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.
flavor_text_8: This legendary Pokemon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.
flavor_text_9: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.
flavor_text_10: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with KYOGRE.

name: rayquaza
flavor_text_0: A POKeMON that flies endlessly in the ozone layer. It is said it would descend to the ground if KYOGRE and GROUDON were to fight.
flavor_text_1: It has lived for hundreds of millions of years in the ozone layer. Its flying form looks like a meteor.
flavor_text_2: RAYQUAZA is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth's ozone layer, above the clouds. Its existence had been completely unknown because it lived so high in the sky.
flavor_text_3: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.
flavor_text_4: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.
flavor_text_5: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth's ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKeMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.
flavor_text_6: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
flavor_text_7: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

name: pikachu
flavor_text_0: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.
flavor_text_1: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_2: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow PIKACHU that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_3: This POKeMON has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while PIKACHU sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_4: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokemon mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_5: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
flavor_text_6: This forest-dwelling Pokemon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you'll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.
flavor_text_7: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_8: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_10: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
flavor_text_11: When it is anger ed, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
flavor_text_12: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.
flavor_text_13: Whenever PIKACHU comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this POKeMON mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_14: This intelligent POKeMON roasts hard BERRIES with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_15: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.
flavor_text_16: This intelligent Pokemon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_17: It raises its tail to check its sur roundings. The tail is sometimes struck by light ning in this pose.
flavor_text_18: When Pikachu meet, they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.
flavor_text_19: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
flavor_text_20: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.
flavor_text_21: It keeps its tail raised to monitor its surroundings. If you yank its tail, it will try to bite you.
flavor_text_22: While sleeping, it generates electricity in the sacs in its cheeks. If it's not getting enough sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.
flavor_text_23: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
flavor_text_24: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.
flavor_text_25: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

flavor_text_5: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
flavor_text_6: This forest-dwelling Pokemon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you'll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.
flavor_text_7: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_8: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.

flavor_text_12: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.
flavor_text_13: Whenever PIKACHU comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this POKeMON mistook the intensity of its charge.

flavor_text_23: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
flavor_text_24: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.

name: hoopa
flavor_text_0: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
flavor_text_1: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.
flavor_text_2: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.
flavor_text_3: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

name: camerupt
flavor_text_0: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokemon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
flavor_text_1: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.
flavor_text_2: The humps on Camerupt's back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokemon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.
flavor_text_3: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKeMON's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.
flavor_text_4: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.
flavor_text_5: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.
flavor_text_6: A POKeMON that lives in the crater of a volcano. Every 10 years, the volcanoes on its back erupt violently. Research is under way on the cause of eruption.
flavor_text_7: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
flavor_text_8: The humps on CAMERUPT's back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This POKeMON apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

name: lopunny
flavor_text_0: It's notably wary and has a dislike of fighting, but at the same time, it can deliver powerful kicks with its lithe legs.
flavor_text_1: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
flavor_text_2: An extremely cautious Pokemon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.
flavor_text_3: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.
flavor_text_4: It sheds its fur twice a year. Its winter fur is soft and fluffy.
flavor_text_5: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokemon responds with superdestructive kicks.
flavor_text_6: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.
flavor_text_7: Once hot seasons are over, Lopunny's coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.
flavor_text_8: Lopunny regrows its coat twice a year. Mufflers and hats made from its fur are really warm.
flavor_text_9: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokemon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.

name: salamence
flavor_text_0: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.
flavor_text_1: By evolving into SALAMENCE, this POKeMON finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.
flavor_text_2: It's uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.
flavor_text_3: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokemon's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.
flavor_text_4: Thanks to its fervent wishes, the cells in its body finally mutated, and at last it has its heart's desire--wings.
flavor_text_5: Salamence is an unusual Pokemon in that it was able to evolve a body with wings just by constantly wishing to be able to fly.
flavor_text_6: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
flavor_text_7: SALAMENCE came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this POKeMON's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.
flavor_text_8: When angered, it loses all sense of itself and destroys everything around it. The destruction will continue until Salamence has tired itself out.
flavor_text_9: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.
flavor_text_10: After many long years, its cellular structure underwent a sudden mutation to grow wings. When angered, it loses all thought and rampages out of control.
flavor_text_11: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps this Pokemon in high spirits, Salamence turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.
flavor_text_12: By evolving into Salamence, this Pokemon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.
flavor_text_13: Overjoyed at finally being able to fly, it flies all over the place and usually doesn't land until it's completely exhausted and needs to sleep.

name: beedrill
flavor_text_0: It can take down any opponent with its powerful poi son stingers. It sometimes attacks in swarms.
flavor_text_1: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
flavor_text_2: It uses sharp, poisonous stings to defeat prey, then takes the victim back to its nest for food.
flavor_text_3: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.
flavor_text_4: It has 3 poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
flavor_text_5: BEEDRILL is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest - this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.
flavor_text_6: A BEEDRILL is extremely territorial. For safety reasons, no one should  ever approach its nest. If angered, they will attack in a swarm.
flavor_text_7: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.
flavor_text_8: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
flavor_text_9: Beedrill is extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest--this is for their own safety. If angered, they will attack in a furious swarm.
flavor_text_10: It has three poison barbs. The barb on its tail secretes the most powerful poison.
flavor_text_11: It can take down any opponent with its powerful poison stingers. It sometimes attacks in swarms.
flavor_text_12: It flies at high speed and attacks using  the large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

name: rattata
flavor_text_0: Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scav enges for edibles the entire day.
flavor_text_1: Its incisors continue growing until its death. If its Trainer doesn't offer it a file to gnaw on, it will gnaw on door frames, table legs, and so on.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.
flavor_text_3: With their strong capacity for survival, they can live in dirty places without concern. Left unchecked, their numbers multiply rapidly.
flavor_text_4: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.
flavor_text_5: RATTATA is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives - it will make its nest anywhere.
flavor_text_6: Will chew on any thing with its fangs. If you see one, it is certain that 40 more live in the area.
flavor_text_7: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.
flavor_text_8: A RATTATA is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly moves its ears and listens for danger. It will make its nest anywhere.
flavor_text_9: Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scavenges for edibles the entire day.
flavor_text_10: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
flavor_text_11: Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokemon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.
flavor_text_12: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.
flavor_text_13: It eats anything. Wherever food is available, it will settle down and produce offspring continuously.
flavor_text_14: This POKeMON's impressive vital ity allows it to live anywhere. It also multiplies very quickly.
flavor_text_15: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.
flavor_text_16: Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives--it will make its nest anywhere.

name: raticate
flavor_text_0: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.
flavor_text_1: RATICATE's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
flavor_text_2: It uses its whis kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
flavor_text_3: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokemon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.
flavor_text_4: Gnaws on anything with its tough fangs. It can even topple concrete buildings by gnaw ing on them.
flavor_text_5: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop grow ing, so it gnaws to pare them down.
flavor_text_6: Raticate's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
flavor_text_7: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.
flavor_text_8: Gnaws on anything with its tough fangs. It can even topple concrete buildings by gnawing on them.
flavor_text_9: Its hind feet are webbed, so it's a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.
flavor_text_10: A RATICATE's sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.
flavor_text_11: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.
flavor_text_12: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.
flavor_text_13: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.
flavor_text_14: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.
flavor_text_15: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
flavor_text_16: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It search es wide areas for food.
flavor_text_17: Its disposition is far more violent than its looks would suggest. Don't let your hand get too close to its face, as it could bite your hand clean off.
flavor_text_18: Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.

flavor_text_0: SANDSLASH can roll up its body as if it were a ball covered with large spikes. In battle, this POKeMON will try to make the foe flinch by jabbing it with its spines. It then leaps at the stunned foe to tear wildly with its sharp claws.
flavor_text_1: Although they are sharp, its claws and spikes often break off. They grow back the next day, so it is not bothered by the temporary loss.
flavor_text_2: Sandslash's body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.
flavor_text_3: Its claws and horns often break off. The broken claws and horns can be used to carve plows for tilling farm fields.
flavor_text_4: Adept at climbing trees, it rolls into a spiny ball, then attacks its enemies from above.
flavor_text_5: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.
flavor_text_6: In an attempt to hide itself, it will run around at top speed to kick up a blinding dust storm.
flavor_text_7: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

name: meowth
flavor_text_0: It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and se cretly hoards.

name: persian
flavor_text_0: Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it's mostly made of the same material.
flavor_text_1: Getting this prideful Pokemon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.
flavor_text_2: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.
flavor_text_3: It has a violent temperament. It will attack anything that looks it in the eye. Its sharp claws inflict deep wounds.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is popular with rich people. It's also targeted by hunters who are after the jewel in its forehead.
flavor_text_5: The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.
flavor_text_6: Behind its lithe, elegant appearance lies a barbaric side. It will tear apart its prey on a mere whim.
flavor_text_7: Many adore it for its sophisticated air. However, it will lash out and scratch for little reason.
flavor_text_8: Has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. It is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.
flavor_text_9: PERSIAN has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers   sense air movements to determine what is in the POKeMON's surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.
flavor_text_10: A PERSIAN's six bold whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in its vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.
flavor_text_11: It has a high opinion of itself, although not to the same extent as the Alolan Persian. It's quite difficult to make friends with this Pokemon.
flavor_text_12: Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokemon's surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.
flavor_text_13: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
flavor_text_14: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.
flavor_text_15: A very haughty Pokemon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

name: geodude
flavor_text_0: It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.
flavor_text_1: Many live on mountain trails and remain half buried while keeping an eye on climbers.
flavor_text_2: Its round form makes it easy to pick up. Some people have used them to hurl at each other in a snowball fight.
flavor_text_3: When GEODUDE sleeps deeply, it buries itself halfway into the ground. It will not awaken even if hikers step on it unwittingly. In the morning, this POKeMON rolls downhill in search of food.
flavor_text_4: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome--carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.
flavor_text_5: Its round body makes it easy to pick up, but it is hard and heavy. It's dangerous to play with them as if they were snowballs.
flavor_text_6: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.
flavor_text_7: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.
flavor_text_8: The longer a Geodude lives, the more its edges are chipped and worn away, making it more rounded in appearance. However, this Pokemon's heart will remain hard, craggy, and rough always.
flavor_text_9: The longer a GEODUDE lives, the more its edges are chipped and worn away, making it more rounded in appearance. However, this POKeMON's heart will remain hard, craggy, and rough always.
flavor_text_10: There are plenty of them to be found along any road. A scholar with too much free time once counted a hundred of them along a single route.
flavor_text_11: It uses its arms to steadily climb steep mountain paths. It swings its fists around if angered.
flavor_text_12: It climbs mountain paths using only the power of its arms. Because they look just like boulders lining paths, hikers may step on them without noticing.
flavor_text_13: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.
flavor_text_14: Proud of their sturdy bodies, they bash against each other in a contest to prove whose is harder.
flavor_text_15: When Geodude sleeps deeply, it buries itself halfway into the ground. It will not awaken even if hikers step on it unwittingly. In the morning, this Pokemon rolls downhill in search of food.
flavor_text_16: Most people may not notice, but a closer look should reveal that there are many GEODUDE around.
flavor_text_17: Commonly found near mountain trails, etc. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.
flavor_text_18: Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they're totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.
flavor_text_19: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

name: graveler
flavor_text_0: GRAVELER grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This POKeMON eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.
flavor_text_1: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.
flavor_text_2: Be careful while hiking on mountain trails. GRAVELER may come rolling down the path without slowing.
flavor_text_3: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.
flavor_text_4: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokemon can stop it without difficulty.
flavor_text_5: They descend from mountains by tumbling down steep slopes. They are so brutal, they smash aside obstructing trees and massive boulders with thunderous tackles.
flavor_text_6: This slow-footed Pokemon moves by curling up and rolling instead of walking. With enough momentum, its speed can exceed 60 mph.
flavor_text_7: It tumbles down slopes, heedless of any body parts chipping off. It eats a ton of rocks daily.
flavor_text_8: Rocks are GRAVELER's favorite food. This POKeMON will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.
flavor_text_9: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
flavor_text_10: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.
flavor_text_11: It travels by rol ling on mountain paths. If it gains too much speed, it stops by running into huge rocks.
flavor_text_12: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.
flavor_text_13: GRAVELER make their homes on sheer cliff faces by gouging out numerous horizontal holes.
flavor_text_14: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokemon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.
flavor_text_15: With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn't mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.
flavor_text_16: Rocks are Graveler's favorite food. This Pokemon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.
flavor_text_17: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.
flavor_text_18: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.

name: golem
flavor_text_0: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.
flavor_text_1: It detonates its own body. The power from that explosion can propel it up steep mountain paths with amazing speed.
flavor_text_2: It sheds its skin once a year. The discarded shell immediately hard ens and crumbles away.
flavor_text_3: It sheds its skin once a year. The discarded shell immediately hardens and crumbles away.
flavor_text_4: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.
flavor_text_5: It is capable of blowing itself up. It uses this explosive force to jump from mountain to mountain.
flavor_text_6: Its rock-like body is so durable, even high-powered dynamite blasts fail to scratch its rugged hide.
flavor_text_7: Once a year, this Pokemon molts, and its shed shell returns to the soil. This process creates enriched soil, so farmers collect the shells.
flavor_text_8: GOLEM live up on mountains. If there is a large earthquake, these POKeMON will come rolling down off the mountains en masse to the foothills below.
flavor_text_9: It tumbles down mountains, leaving grooves from peak to base. Stay clear of these grooves.
flavor_text_10: GOLEM is known for rolling down from mountains. To prevent them from rolling into the homes of people downhill, grooves have been dug into the sides of mountains to serve as guideways for diverting this POKeMON's course.
flavor_text_11: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.
flavor_text_12: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.
flavor_text_13: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can't harm it.
flavor_text_14: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.
flavor_text_15: It is said to live in volcanic craters on mountain peaks. Once a year, it sheds its hide and grows larger. The shed hide crumbles and returns to the soil.
flavor_text_16: Golem is known for rolling down from mountains. To prevent them from rolling into the homes of people downhill, grooves have been dug into the sides of mountains to serve as guideways for diverting this Pokemon's course.
flavor_text_17: Golem live up on mountains. If there is a large earthquake, these Pokemon will come rolling down off the mountains en masse to the foothills below.
flavor_text_18: Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.
flavor_text_19: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.
flavor_text_20: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without taking damage.
flavor_text_21: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it's exposed to air.

name: grimer
flavor_text_0: Sludge exposed to X rays from the moon transformed into GRIMER. It loves feeding on filthy things.
flavor_text_1: Made of hardened sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.
flavor_text_2: GRIMER emerged from the sludge that settled on a polluted seabed. This POKeMON loves anything filthy. It constantly leaks a horribly germ- infested fluid from all over its body.
flavor_text_3: Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
flavor_text_4: Wherever GRIMER has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.
flavor_text_5: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.
flavor_text_6: Grimer emerged from the sludge that settled on a polluted seabed. This Pokemon loves anything filthy. It constantly leaks a horribly germ-infested fluid from all over its body.
flavor_text_7: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.
flavor_text_8: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
flavor_text_9: As it moves, it loses bits of its body, from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.
flavor_text_10: Sludge exposed to X-rays from the moon transformed into Grimer. It loves feeding on filthy things.
flavor_text_11: Born from sludge, these Pokemon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.
flavor_text_12: GRIMER's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This POKeMON enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.
flavor_text_13: When two of these POKeMON's bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.
flavor_text_14: The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They're said to be on the verge of extinction.
flavor_text_15: It was born from sludge transformed by exposure to X-rays from the moon. When its internal load of germs decreases, it dies.
flavor_text_16: Born from polluted sludge in the sea, GRIMER's favorite food is anything filthy. They feed on wastewater pumped out from factories.
flavor_text_17: Grimer's sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokemon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.
flavor_text_18: As it moves, it loses bits of its body from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.
flavor_text_19: It was born from sludge on the ocean floor. In a sterile environment, the germs within its body can't multiply, and it dies.
flavor_text_20: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokemon's numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

name: muk
flavor_text_0: As it moves, a very strong poison leaks from it, making the ground there barren for three years.
flavor_text_1: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they've long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.
flavor_text_2: This Pokemon's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, Muk are certain to gather.
flavor_text_3: From Muk's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokemon's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
flavor_text_4: From MUK's body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this POKeMON's body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.
flavor_text_5: Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.
flavor_text_6: They love to gath er in smelly areas where sludge ac cumulates, making the stench around them worse.
flavor_text_7: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that's a good thing.
flavor_text_8: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
flavor_text_9: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.
flavor_text_10: This POKeMON's favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, MUK are certain to gather.
flavor_text_11: Its body is made of a powerful poi son. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.
flavor_text_12: It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.
flavor_text_13: It's so stinky! Muk's body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.
flavor_text_14: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration, it lost its sense of smell.
flavor_text_15: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.
flavor_text_16: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.
flavor_text_17: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates, making the stench around them worse.
flavor_text_18: After recent environmental improvements, this Pokemon is now hardly seen at all. People speculate that it may go extinct at some point.
flavor_text_19: It prefers warm and humid habitats. In the summertime, the toxic substances in its body intensify, making MUK reek like putrid kitchen garbage.

name: exeggutor
flavor_text_0: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.
flavor_text_1: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_2: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokemon sluggish.
flavor_text_3: Each of its heads has its own will. They use telepathy to discuss their plans before coming to a joint decision.
flavor_text_4: Its three heads think independent ly. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.
flavor_text_5: Its three heads think independently. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.
flavor_text_6: It is called "The Walking Tropical Rainforest." Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.
flavor_text_7: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.
flavor_text_8: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the 3 heads thinks about whatever it likes.
flavor_text_9: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_10: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.
flavor_text_11: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_12: It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.
flavor_text_13: Living in a good environment makes it grow lots of heads. A head that drops off becomes an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_14: Originally from the tropics, EXEGGUTOR's heads grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall, they group to form an EXEGGCUTE.
flavor_text_15: When the time comes, one of its three heads falls off. Before long, the fallen head grows into an Exeggcute.
flavor_text_16: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
flavor_text_17: If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an EXEGGCUTE cluster.
flavor_text_18: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.
flavor_text_19: EXEGGUTOR originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form EXEGGCUTE.

name: marowak
flavor_text_0: It collects bones from an unknown place. Some whisper that a MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world.
flavor_text_1: It throws bones at Mandibuzz to knock it down. It's thought that Marowak is trying to avenge its parent.
flavor_text_2: Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.
flavor_text_3: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.
flavor_text_4: Somewhere in the world is a ceme tery just for MAROWAK. It gets its bones from those graves.
flavor_text_5: When this Pokemon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak's temperament also turned vicious at the same time.
flavor_text_6: Small and weak, this Pokemon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_7: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.
flavor_text_8: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.
flavor_text_10: MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This POKeMON's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_11: This Pokemon is out for vengeance on its natural enemy, Mandibuzz. It throws bones like boomerangs to try to take it down.
flavor_text_12: It collects bones from an unknown place. A MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world, rumors say.
flavor_text_13: From its birth, this savage Pokemon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.
flavor_text_14: A MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has grown tough by overcoming the grief of losing its mother. Its tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_15: Small and weak, this POKeMON is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_16: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.
flavor_text_17: Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokemon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_18: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out mes sages to others.

name: greninja
flavor_text_0: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.
flavor_text_1: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
