flavor_text_1: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
flavor_text_2: This is Zygarde's form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.
flavor_text_3: When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.
flavor_text_4: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.
flavor_text_5: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: gumshoos
flavor_text_0: Although it wasn't originally found in Alola, this Pokemon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.
flavor_text_1: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokemon boasts incredible patience.
flavor_text_2: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it's always snoozing by nightfall.
flavor_text_3: Patient by nature, this Pokemon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal--Rattata!

name: vikavolt
flavor_text_0: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokemon with shocking beams of electrical energy.
flavor_text_1: It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.
flavor_text_2: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.
flavor_text_3: Vikavolt flusters opponents with acrobatic flying maneuvers. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electric beam attack.
flavor_text_4: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.
flavor_text_5: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.

name: oricorio
flavor_text_0: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.
flavor_text_1: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.
flavor_text_2: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokemon becomes fiercely angry.
flavor_text_3: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

name: lycanroc
flavor_text_0: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.
flavor_text_1: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.
flavor_text_2: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.
flavor_text_3: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.
flavor_text_4: With swift movements, this Pokemon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.
flavor_text_5: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

name: wishiwashi
flavor_text_0: When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.
flavor_text_1: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.
flavor_text_2: When it's in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.
flavor_text_3: It's awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.
flavor_text_4: Individually, they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.
flavor_text_5: They're weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.

name: lurantis
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.
flavor_text_1: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokemon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.
flavor_text_2: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis's vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.
flavor_text_3: The petals on this Pokemon's arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.
flavor_text_4: It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.
flavor_text_5: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokemon.

name: salazzle
flavor_text_0: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.
flavor_text_1: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.
flavor_text_2: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.
flavor_text_3: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.
flavor_text_4: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.
flavor_text_5: It punishes Salandit that couldn't bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

name: minior
flavor_text_0: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.
flavor_text_1: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokemon was born from mutated nanoparticles.
flavor_text_2: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokemon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.
flavor_text_3: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

name: mimikyu
flavor_text_0: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu's old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.
flavor_text_1: Although it's a quiet, lonely Pokemon, if you try to look at what's under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.
flavor_text_2: A gust of wind revealed what hides under this Pokemon's rag to a passing Trainer, who went home and died painfully that very night.
flavor_text_3: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.
flavor_text_4: A lonely Pokemon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokemon.
flavor_text_5: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: kommo-o
flavor_text_0: Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.
flavor_text_1: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokemon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.
flavor_text_2: When it howls after finishing off its prey, the metallic sounds of its celebrating comrades can be heard from all around.
flavor_text_3: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.
flavor_text_4: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.
flavor_text_5: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

name: magearna
flavor_text_0: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.
flavor_text_1: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.
flavor_text_2: This artificial Pokemon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.
flavor_text_3: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name: pikachu
flavor_text_0: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.
flavor_text_1: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_2: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow PIKACHU that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_3: This POKeMON has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while PIKACHU sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_4: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokemon mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_5: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
flavor_text_6: This forest-dwelling Pokemon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you'll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.
flavor_text_7: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_8: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_10: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
flavor_text_11: When it is anger ed, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
flavor_text_12: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.
flavor_text_13: Whenever PIKACHU comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this POKeMON mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_14: This intelligent POKeMON roasts hard BERRIES with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_15: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.
flavor_text_16: This intelligent Pokemon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_17: It raises its tail to check its sur roundings. The tail is sometimes struck by light ning in this pose.
flavor_text_18: When Pikachu meet, they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.
flavor_text_19: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
flavor_text_20: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.
flavor_text_21: It keeps its tail raised to monitor its surroundings. If you yank its tail, it will try to bite you.
flavor_text_22: While sleeping, it generates electricity in the sacs in its cheeks. If it's not getting enough sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.
flavor_text_23: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
flavor_text_24: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.
flavor_text_25: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

name: marowak
flavor_text_0: It collects bones from an unknown place. Some whisper that a MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world.
flavor_text_1: It throws bones at Mandibuzz to knock it down. It's thought that Marowak is trying to avenge its parent.
flavor_text_2: Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.
flavor_text_3: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.
flavor_text_4: Somewhere in the world is a ceme tery just for MAROWAK. It gets its bones from those graves.
flavor_text_5: When this Pokemon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak's temperament also turned vicious at the same time.
flavor_text_6: Small and weak, this Pokemon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_7: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.
flavor_text_8: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.
flavor_text_10: MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This POKeMON's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_11: This Pokemon is out for vengeance on its natural enemy, Mandibuzz. It throws bones like boomerangs to try to take it down.
flavor_text_12: It collects bones from an unknown place. A MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world, rumors say.
flavor_text_13: From its birth, this savage Pokemon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.
flavor_text_14: A MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has grown tough by overcoming the grief of losing its mother. Its tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_15: Small and weak, this POKeMON is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.
flavor_text_16: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.
flavor_text_17: Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokemon's tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.
flavor_text_18: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out mes sages to others.

name: ribombee
flavor_text_0: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs' effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.
flavor_text_1: Some of Ribombee's pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.
flavor_text_2: Rain makes pollen damp, so Ribombee hates rain. When it sees ominous clouds, it finds a hollow in a tree, where it waits stock-still.
flavor_text_3: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
flavor_text_4: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.
flavor_text_5: It can predict the weather from moisture levels and wind direction. Ribombee only reveals itself when there are a few clear days in a row.

name: rockruff
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.
flavor_text_1: It's considered to be a good Pokemon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.
flavor_text_2: As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches, Rockruff attacks.
flavor_text_4: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

name: lycanroc
flavor_text_0: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.
flavor_text_1: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.
flavor_text_2: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.
flavor_text_3: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.
flavor_text_4: With swift movements, this Pokemon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.
flavor_text_5: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

name: araquanid
flavor_text_0: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.
flavor_text_1: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokemon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.
flavor_text_2: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokemon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.
flavor_text_3: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn't watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!
flavor_text_4: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokemon can then take its time to savor its meal.
flavor_text_5: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.

name: togedemaru
flavor_text_0: When it's in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.
flavor_text_1: When it's surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.
flavor_text_2: Its capacity to produce electricity is somewhat limited, so it gets charged up by letting lightning strike it!
flavor_text_3: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.
flavor_text_4: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokemon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.
flavor_text_5: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokemon takes in electricity from other electric Pokemon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: necrozma
flavor_text_0: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.
flavor_text_1: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.
flavor_text_2: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.
flavor_text_3: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.
flavor_text_4: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.
flavor_text_5: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

flavor_text_0: Every time it ya wns, SHELLDER injects more poi son into it. The poison makes it more intelligent.

flavor_text_2: It's constantly coming up with new ideas that would change the world, but as soon as it hits upon a new idea, it forgets it.
flavor_text_3: It undertakes research every day to solve the mysteries of the world. However, it apparently forgets everything if the SHELLDER on its head comes off.
flavor_text_4: SLOWKING undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this POKeMON apparently forgets everything it has learned if the SHELLDER on its head comes off.
flavor_text_5: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
flavor_text_6: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokemon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon is so famed for its intellect that a proverb still persists in some regions: "When in doubt, ask Slowking."
flavor_text_8: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke's latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.
flavor_text_9: Slowking can solve any problem presented to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.
flavor_text_10: Being bitten by SHELLDER gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.
flavor_text_11: It's called "the sage of the sea." It engages in battles of wits with Oranguru, but the result is usually a draw.
flavor_text_12: A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.
flavor_text_13: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.
flavor_text_14: When its head was bitten, toxins entered SLOWPOKE's head and unlocked an extraordinary power.
flavor_text_15: It has incredible intellect and in tuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

name: corsola
flavor_text_0: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these POKeMON.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon live in warm seas. In prehistoric times, many lived in the oceans around the Galar region as well.
flavor_text_2: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.
flavor_text_3: In Alola, where their natural enemies Mareanie are plentiful, many Corsola have stubby branches on their heads.
flavor_text_4: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokemon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.
flavor_text_5: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.
flavor_text_6: Clusters of CORSOLA congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller POKeMON. When the water temperature falls, this POKeMON migrates to the southern seas.
flavor_text_7: The pink of Corsola that live in Alola is deep and vibrant, thanks to seas filled with nutrition.
flavor_text_8: Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.
flavor_text_9: In a south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokemon.
flavor_text_10: CORSOLA live in warm southern seas. If the sea becomes polluted, the beautiful coral stalks become discolored and crumble away in tatters.
flavor_text_11: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokemon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokemon migrates to the southern seas.
flavor_text_12: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.
flavor_text_13: In a south sea nation, the people live in communi ties that are built on groups of these POKeMON.
flavor_text_14: CORSOLA's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this POKeMON grows it back in just one night.
flavor_text_15: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.
flavor_text_16: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.
flavor_text_17: Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokemon grows it back in just one night.
flavor_text_18: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

name: zigzagoon
flavor_text_0: It gets interested in everything, which is why it zigs and zags. It is good at finding items.
flavor_text_1: It walks in zigzag fashion. It's good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
flavor_text_2: A POKeMON with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigs and zags.
flavor_text_3: ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKeMON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.
flavor_text_4: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
flavor_text_5: The hair on ZIGZAGOON's back is  bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This POKeMON may play dead to fool foes in battle.
flavor_text_6: Rubbing its nose against the ground, it always wanders about back and forth in search of something. It is distinguished by the zigzag footprints it leaves.
flavor_text_7: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.
flavor_text_8: A Pokemon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.
flavor_text_9: Zigzagoon that adapted to regions outside Galar acquired this appearance. If you've lost something, this Pokemon can likely find it.
flavor_text_10: The hair on Zigzagoon's back is bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This Pokemon may play dead to fool foes in battle.
flavor_text_11: Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokemon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

name: linoone
flavor_text_0: When hunting, Linoone will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this Pokemon is capable of topping 60 mph, it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.
flavor_text_1: Its fur is strong and supple. Shaving brushes made with shed Linoone hairs are highly prized.
flavor_text_2: When running in a straight line, it can top 60 miles per hour. However, it has a tough time with curved roads.
flavor_text_3: When running in a straight line, it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.
flavor_text_4: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.
flavor_text_5: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
flavor_text_6: It is exceedingly fast if it only has to run in a straight line. When it spots pond- dwelling prey underwater, it quickly leaps in and catches it with its sharp claws.
flavor_text_7: LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKeMON is very challenged by gently curving roads.
flavor_text_8: Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokemon is very challenged by gently curving roads.
flavor_text_9: When hunting, LINOONE will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this POKeMON is capable of topping 60 mph, it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.

name: darumaka
flavor_text_0: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokemon will immediately fall asleep.
flavor_text_1: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it's pushed or pulled.
flavor_text_2: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_3: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.
flavor_text_4: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100deg F.
flavor_text_5: Darumaka's droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

name: darmanitan
flavor_text_0: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokemon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.
flavor_text_1: Its internal fire burns at 2,500deg F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_2: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_3: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
flavor_text_4: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: darmanitan
flavor_text_0: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokemon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.
flavor_text_1: Its internal fire burns at 2,500deg F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_2: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
flavor_text_3: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
flavor_text_4: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: yamask
flavor_text_0: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokemon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
flavor_text_1: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that's said to have been the face it had when it was still human.
flavor_text_2: These Pokemon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.
flavor_text_3: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
flavor_text_4: These Pokemon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: stunfisk
flavor_text_0: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
flavor_text_1: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokemon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.
flavor_text_2: For some reason, this Pokemon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.
flavor_text_3: When its opponent can't be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.
flavor_text_4: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: zygarde
flavor_text_0: This is Zygarde's form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.
flavor_text_1: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
flavor_text_2: This is Zygarde's form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.
flavor_text_3: When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.
flavor_text_4: It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.
flavor_text_5: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: cramorant
flavor_text_0: This hungry Pokemon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokemon other than its preferred prey.
flavor_text_1: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

name: cramorant
flavor_text_0: This hungry Pokemon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokemon other than its preferred prey.
flavor_text_1: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

name: toxtricity
flavor_text_0: When this Pokemon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
flavor_text_1: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokemon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

name: eiscue
flavor_text_0: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

name: indeedee
flavor_text_0: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.
flavor_text_1: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

name: morpeko
flavor_text_0: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokemon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.
flavor_text_1: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they're precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

name: zacian
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon has slumbered for many years. Some say it's Zamazenta's elder sister--others say the two Pokemon are rivals.
flavor_text_1: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokemon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: zamazenta
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.
flavor_text_1: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: eternatus
flavor_text_0: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.
flavor_text_1: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokemon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

name: urshifu
flavor_text_0: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.
flavor_text_1: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokemon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

name: zarude
flavor_text_0: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
flavor_text_1: Within dense forests, this Pokemon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokemon of the forest fear it.

name: calyrex
flavor_text_0: Calyrex is a merciful Pokemon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.
flavor_text_1: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

name: calyrex
flavor_text_0: Calyrex is a merciful Pokemon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.
flavor_text_1: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

name: venusaur
flavor_text_0: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.
flavor_text_1: There is a large flower on VENUSAUR's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.
flavor_text_2: VENUSAUR's flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.
flavor_text_3: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: There is a large flower on Venusaur's back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower's aroma soothes the emotions of people.
flavor_text_5: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
flavor_text_6: It is able to convert sunlight into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.
flavor_text_7: The flower on its back catches the sun's rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy.
flavor_text_8: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun's rays, it fills its body with power.
flavor_text_9: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
flavor_text_10: It is able to con vert sunlight into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.
flavor_text_11: As it warms it self and absorbs the sunlight, its flower petals release a pleasant fragrance.

name: charizard
flavor_text_0: Breathing intense, hot flames, it can melt almost any thing. Its breath inflicts terrible pain on enemies.
flavor_text_1: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.
flavor_text_2: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.
flavor_text_3: If CHARIZARD becomes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a light blue shade.
flavor_text_4: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.
flavor_text_5: It uses its wings to fly high. The temperature of its fire increases as it gains exper ience in battle.
flavor_text_6: A CHARIZARD flies about in search of strong opponents. It breathes intense flames that can melt any material. However, it will never torch a weaker foe.
flavor_text_7: When expelling a blast of super hot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.
flavor_text_8: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
flavor_text_9: If CHARIZARD be comes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a whitish- blue color.
flavor_text_10: When this Pokemon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.
flavor_text_11: CHARIZARD flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.
flavor_text_12: It is said that CHARIZARD's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
flavor_text_13: Its wings can carry this Pokemon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.
flavor_text_14: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
flavor_text_15: Its wings can carry this POKeMON close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.
flavor_text_16: Breathing intense, hot flames, it can melt almost anything. Its breath inflicts terrible pain on enemies.

name: blastoise
flavor_text_0: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
flavor_text_1: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokemon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.
flavor_text_2: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punch ing holes through thick steel.
flavor_text_3: The waterspouts that protrude from its shell are highly accurate. Their bullets of water can precisely nail tin cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_4: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.
flavor_text_5: BLASTOISE has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_6: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
flavor_text_7: A brutal POKeMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
flavor_text_8: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
flavor_text_9: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.
flavor_text_10: It firmly plants its feet on the ground before shooting water from the jets on its back.
flavor_text_11: The pressurized water jets on this brutal POKeMON's shell are used for high- speed tackles.
flavor_text_12: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.
flavor_text_13: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can with stand the recoil of the water jets it fires.

name: butterfree
flavor_text_0: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.
flavor_text_1: Its wings, covered with poisonous powders, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.
flavor_text_2: Water-repellent powder on its wings enables it to collect honey, even in the heav iest of rains.
flavor_text_3: It has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can seek, extract, and carry honey from flowers blooming over six miles away.
flavor_text_4: When attacked by other Pokemon, it defends itself by scattering its poisonous scales and fluttering its wings.
flavor_text_5: Nectar from pretty flowers is its favorite food. In fields of flowers, it has heated battles with Cutiefly for territory.
flavor_text_6: Water-repellent powder on its wings enables it to collect honey, even in the heaviest of rains.
flavor_text_7: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this POKeMON can fly about even in rain.
flavor_text_8: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
flavor_text_9: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.
flavor_text_10: It flits from flower to flower, collecting honey. It can even identify distant flowers in bloom.
flavor_text_11: BUTTERFREE has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.
flavor_text_12: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.
flavor_text_13: Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.
flavor_text_14: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this Pokemon can fly about even in rain.
flavor_text_15: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.
flavor_text_16: Its wings are covered in toxic scales. If it finds bird Pokemon going after Caterpie, Butterfree sprinkles its scales on them to drive them off.
flavor_text_17: Butterfree has a superior ability to search for delicious honey from flowers. It can even search out, extract, and carry honey from flowers that are blooming over six miles from its nest.

name: pikachu
flavor_text_0: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.
flavor_text_1: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_2: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow PIKACHU that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_3: This POKeMON has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while PIKACHU sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_4: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokemon mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_5: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
flavor_text_6: This forest-dwelling Pokemon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you'll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.
flavor_text_7: When several of these POKeMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
flavor_text_8: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
flavor_text_9: This Pokemon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.
flavor_text_10: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
flavor_text_11: When it is anger ed, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.
flavor_text_12: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.
flavor_text_13: Whenever PIKACHU comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this POKeMON mistook the intensity of its charge.
flavor_text_14: This intelligent POKeMON roasts hard BERRIES with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_15: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.
flavor_text_16: This intelligent Pokemon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.
flavor_text_17: It raises its tail to check its sur roundings. The tail is sometimes struck by light ning in this pose.
flavor_text_18: When Pikachu meet, they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.
flavor_text_19: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
flavor_text_20: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.
flavor_text_21: It keeps its tail raised to monitor its surroundings. If you yank its tail, it will try to bite you.
flavor_text_22: While sleeping, it generates electricity in the sacs in its cheeks. If it's not getting enough sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.
flavor_text_23: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
flavor_text_24: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.
flavor_text_25: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

name: meowth
flavor_text_0: It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and se cretly hoards.
flavor_text_1: It loves to collect shiny things. If it's in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.
flavor_text_2: It lies around all day, becoming active near dusk. At night, it wanders the city in search of loose change.
flavor_text_3: It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can make friends with Meowth easily. But it's fickle, so you can't count on that friendship lasting.
flavor_text_4: When visiting a junkyard, you may catch sight of it having an intense fight with Murkrow over shiny objects.
flavor_text_5: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.
flavor_text_6: It loves shiny things. It often fights with Murkrow over prey they're both trying to catch.
flavor_text_7: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
flavor_text_8: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can't stop itself from picking them up.
flavor_text_9: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn't get along with Galarian Meowth.
flavor_text_10: MEOWTH withdraws its sharp claws into its paws to slinkily sneak about without making any incriminating footsteps. For some reason, this POKeMON loves shiny coins that glitter with light.
flavor_text_11: It is fascinated by round objects. It can't stop playing with them until it tires and falls asleep.
flavor_text_12: MEOWTH withdraw their sharp claws into their paws to silently sneak about. For some reason, this POKeMON loves shiny coins that glitter with light.
flavor_text_13: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can't stop from picking them up.
flavor_text_14: Meowth withdraws its sharp claws into its paws to slinkily sneak about without making any incriminating footsteps. For some reason, this Pokemon loves shiny coins that glitter with light.
flavor_text_15: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.
flavor_text_16: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
flavor_text_17: It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and secretly hoards.
flavor_text_18: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines too.

name: machamp
flavor_text_0: Its superpowerful punches are said to knock the victim flying clear over the horizon.
flavor_text_1: It can knock a train flying with a punch. However, it is terrible at delicate work using its fingers.
flavor_text_2: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.
flavor_text_3: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.
flavor_text_4: It is impossible to defend against punches and chops doled out by its four arms. Its fighting spirit flares up when it faces a tough opponent.
flavor_text_5: With four arms, it can attack and defend simultaneously. It's said to have mastered every martial art in the world.
flavor_text_6: It uses its four powerful arms to pin the limbs of its foe, then throws the victim over the horizon.
flavor_text_7: It can lift heavy loads with the greatest of ease. It can even heft dump trucks. But its clumsy fingers prevent it from doing any precision work.
flavor_text_8: One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this POKeMON fires off awesome punches.
flavor_text_9: One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this Pokemon fires off awesome punches.
flavor_text_10: MACHAMP is known as the POKeMON that has mastered every kind of martial arts. If it grabs hold of the foe with its four arms, the battle is all but over. The hapless foe is thrown far over the horizon.
flavor_text_11: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.
flavor_text_12: Machamp has the power to hurl anything aside. However, trying to do any work requiring care and dexterity causes its arms to get tangled. This Pokemon tends to leap into action before it thinks.
flavor_text_13: Machamp is known as the Pokemon that has mastered every kind of martial arts. If it grabs hold of the foe with its four arms, the battle is all but over. The hapless foe is thrown far over the horizon.
flavor_text_14: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.
flavor_text_15: It unleashes megaton-level punches that send opponents flying clear over the horizon.
flavor_text_16: MACHAMP has the power to hurl anything aside. However, trying to do any work requiring care and dexterity causes its arms to get tangled. This POKeMON tends to leap into action before it thinks.
flavor_text_17: It grasps its opponents with its four arms and twists them up in an intricate hold. People call it "the Machamp special."
flavor_text_18: Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.
flavor_text_19: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokemon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.
flavor_text_20: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: gengar
flavor_text_0: Lurking in the shadowy corners of rooms, it awaits chances to steal its prey's life force.
flavor_text_1: A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_2: A GENGAR is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.
flavor_text_3: Under a full moon, this POKeMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.
flavor_text_4: It steals heat from its surround ings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_5: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.
flavor_text_6: It hides in shadows. It is said that if Gengar is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_7: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_8: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be GENGAR's doing.
flavor_text_9: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_10: Even your home isn't safe. Gengar will lurk in whatever dark corner of a room it can find and wait for its chance to catch its prey.
flavor_text_11: Possesses potential victims' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!
flavor_text_12: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.
flavor_text_13: It apparently wishes for a traveling companion. Since it was once human itself, it tries to create one by taking the lives of other humans.
flavor_text_14: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.
flavor_text_15: It steals heat from its surroundings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.
flavor_text_16: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_17: Deep in the night, your shadow cast by a streetlight may suddenly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.
flavor_text_18: It hides in shadows. It is said that if GENGAR is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees F.
flavor_text_19: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a GENGAR delighting in casting curses on people.
flavor_text_20: Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.
flavor_text_21: You can hear tales told all over the world about how Gengar will pay a visit to children who are naughty.
flavor_text_22: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

name: kingler
flavor_text_0: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
flavor_text_1: One claw grew massively and as hard as steel. It has 10,000-HP strength. However, it is too heavy.
flavor_text_2: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.
flavor_text_3: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.
flavor_text_4: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it's not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.
flavor_text_5: It can hardly lift its massive, overgrown pincer. The pincer's size makes it difficult to aim properly.
flavor_text_6: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokemon quickly tires.
flavor_text_7: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.
flavor_text_8: The large pincer has 10,000-horsepower crushing force. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
flavor_text_9: KINGLER has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the POKeMON quickly tires.
flavor_text_10: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.
flavor_text_11: It waves its huge, oversized claw in the air to communicate with others. But since the claw is so heavy, this POKeMON quickly tires.
flavor_text_12: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its bal ance and staggers.
flavor_text_13: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: lapras
flavor_text_0: They've been so cherished that there's now an overabundance. The fish Pokemon population has declined in waters with too many Lapras.
flavor_text_1: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokemon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.
flavor_text_2: This gentle POKeMON loves to give people rides and provides a ve ry comfortable way to get around.
flavor_text_3: They have gentle hearts. Because they rarely fight, many have been caught. Their num ber has dwindled.
flavor_text_4: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.
flavor_text_5: These Pokemon were once near extinction due to poaching. Following protective regulations, there is now an overabundance of them.
flavor_text_6: A smart and kindhearted Pokemon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.
flavor_text_7: A POKeMON that has been over hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.
flavor_text_8: A POKeMON that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people on its back.
flavor_text_9: People have driven LAPRAS almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this POKeMON is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.
flavor_text_10: A gentle soul that can understand human speech. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.
flavor_text_11: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.
flavor_text_12: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, this Pokemon is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.
flavor_text_13: Its high intelligence enables it to comprehend human speech. When it's in a good mood, it sings in its beautiful voice.
flavor_text_14: A gentle soul that can read the minds of people. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.
flavor_text_15: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokemon on its back. It understands human speech.
flavor_text_16: It likes swimming around with people on its back. In the Alola region, it's an important means of transportation over water.
flavor_text_17: People have driven LAPRAS almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, it is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.
flavor_text_18: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.
flavor_text_19: They have gentle hearts. Because they rarely fight, many have been caught. Their number has dwindled.

name: eevee
flavor_text_0: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.
flavor_text_1: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.
flavor_text_2: It has the ability to alter the com position of its body to suit its surrounding envi ronment.
flavor_text_3: Current studies show it can evolve into an incredible eight different species of Pokemon.
flavor_text_4: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee's genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokemon evolution.
flavor_text_5: Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.
flavor_text_6: Its irregularly configured DNA is affected by its surroundings. It evolves if its environment changes.
flavor_text_7: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONES.
flavor_text_8: The question of why only Eevee has such unstable genes has still not been solved.
flavor_text_9: Eevee has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various stones causes this Pokemon to evolve.
flavor_text_10: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokemon conceals many different possible evolutions.
flavor_text_11: EEVEE has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to the environment in which it lives. Radiation from various STONES causes this POKeMON to evolve.
flavor_text_12: Its irregularly configured DNA is affected by its surroundings. It evolves if its en vironment changes.
flavor_text_13: Its genes are easily influenced by its surroundings. Even its face starts to look like that of its Trainer.
flavor_text_14: An extremely rare POKeMON that may evolve in a number of different ways depending on stimuli.
flavor_text_15: Its genetic code is unstable, so it could evolve in a variety of ways. There are only a few alive.
flavor_text_16: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.
flavor_text_17: A rare Pokemon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.
flavor_text_18: An EEVEE has an unstable genetic makeup that suddenly mutates due to its environment. Radiation from various STONES causes this POKeMON to evolve.
flavor_text_19: Harbors the potential to evolve into manifold forms. Within Eevee lies the key to the mysteries of Pokemon evolution--I'm certain of it.
flavor_text_20: Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.

name: snorlax
flavor_text_0: This POKeMON's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.
flavor_text_1: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.
flavor_text_2: Its stomach's di gestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. It can even eat things off the ground.
flavor_text_3: Snorlax's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokemon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.
flavor_text_4: What sounds like its cry may actually be its snores or the rumblings of its hungry belly.
flavor_text_5: It has no interest in anything other than eating. Even if you climb up on its stomach while it's napping, it doesn't seem to mind at all!
flavor_text_6: It eats nearly 900 pounds of food every day. It starts nodding off while eating--and continues to eat even while it's asleep.
flavor_text_7: This Pokemon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.
flavor_text_8: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
flavor_text_9: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.
flavor_text_10: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.
flavor_text_11: It doesn't do anything other than eat and sleep. When prompted to make a serious effort, though, it apparently displays awesome power.
flavor_text_12: It stops eating only to sleep. It doesn't feel full unless it eats nearly 900 pounds a day.
flavor_text_13: What sounds like its cry may ac tually be its snores or the rumblings of its hungry belly.
flavor_text_14: Its stomach's digestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. It can even eat things off the ground.
flavor_text_15: SNORLAX's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile POKeMON that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.
flavor_text_16: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries--such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.
flavor_text_17: SNORLAX's typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile POKeMON that there are children who use its big belly as a place to play.
flavor_text_18: Its stomach is said to be incomparably strong. Even Muk's poison is nothing more than a hint of spice on Snorlax's tongue.
flavor_text_19: Will eat anything, even if the food happens to be a little moldy. It never gets an upset stomach.

name: garbodor
flavor_text_0: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.
flavor_text_1: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.
flavor_text_2: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
flavor_text_3: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.
flavor_text_4: Some say the reason Garbodor in Alola are a little stronger than their counterparts elsewhere is the presence of Muk, their natural enemy.
flavor_text_5: This Pokemon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.
flavor_text_6: It locks opponents in place with its left hand, immobilizing them by entirely dousing their bodies with poisonous liquid.
flavor_text_7: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.
flavor_text_8: For a time, their numbers increased explosively in Alola. Since the arrival of Grimer, their population has decreased dramatically.

name: melmetal
flavor_text_0: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal's heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokemon.
flavor_text_1: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
flavor_text_2: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: rillaboom
flavor_text_0: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
flavor_text_1: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: cinderace
flavor_text_0: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.
flavor_text_1: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

name: inteleon
flavor_text_0: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
flavor_text_1: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: corviknight
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
flavor_text_1: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokemon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

name: orbeetle
flavor_text_0: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.
flavor_text_1: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it--and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

name: drednaw
flavor_text_0: This Pokemon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.
flavor_text_1: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokemon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: coalossal
flavor_text_0: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
flavor_text_1: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

name: flapple
flavor_text_0: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.
flavor_text_1: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: appletun
flavor_text_0: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokemon it preys on.
flavor_text_1: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

name: sandaconda
flavor_text_0: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.
flavor_text_1: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

name: toxtricity
flavor_text_0: When this Pokemon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
flavor_text_1: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokemon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

name: centiskorch
flavor_text_0: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
flavor_text_1: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokemon also has large and very sharp fangs.

name: hatterene
flavor_text_0: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokemon is also known as the Forest Witch.
flavor_text_1: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: grimmsnarl
flavor_text_0: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.
flavor_text_1: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokemon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: alcremie
flavor_text_0: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.
flavor_text_1: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

name: copperajah
flavor_text_0: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.
flavor_text_1: These Pokemon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

name: duraludon
flavor_text_0: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokemon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.
flavor_text_1: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: urshifu
flavor_text_0: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.
flavor_text_1: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokemon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

name: urshifu
flavor_text_0: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.
flavor_text_1: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokemon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

name: toxtricity
flavor_text_0: When this Pokemon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.
flavor_text_1: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokemon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

name: growlithe
flavor_text_0: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
flavor_text_1: GROWLITHE has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this POKeMON won't forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.
flavor_text_2: It has lived alongside humans since ages ago. Its bones have been found in excavations of ruins from the Stone Age.
flavor_text_3: While it's quite friendly toward humans once it's grown used to them, in the wild it must be quite fierce to defend its territory from Rockruff.
flavor_text_4: A POKeMON with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.
flavor_text_5: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.
flavor_text_6: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this Pokemon won't forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.
flavor_text_7: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.
flavor_text_8: It has a brave and trustworthy na ture. It fear lessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.
flavor_text_9: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.
flavor_text_10: Its superb sense of smell ensures that this POKeMON won't forget any scent, no matter what. It uses its sense of smell to detect the emotions of others.
flavor_text_11: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.
flavor_text_12: A Pokemon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.
flavor_text_13: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any oppo nent to protect its own trainer from harm.
flavor_text_14: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
flavor_text_15: A Pokemon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.
flavor_text_16: It looks cute, but when you approach another Trainer's Growlithe, it will bark at you and bite.
flavor_text_17: It controls a big territory. If it detects an unknown smell, it roars loudly to force out the intruder.
flavor_text_18: It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.
flavor_text_19: It is very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

name: arcanine
flavor_text_0: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.
flavor_text_1: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were attracted to its movement as it ran through prairies.
flavor_text_2: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokemon's body is its source of power.
flavor_text_3: This legendary Chinese Pokemon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.
flavor_text_4: A Pokemon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_5: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.
flavor_text_6: Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.
flavor_text_7: Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokemon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.
flavor_text_8: A legendary POKe MON in China. Many people are charmed by its grace and beauty while running.
flavor_text_9: The fire burning inside its body serves as the energy to fuel it as it runs great distances. It appears in many legends.
flavor_text_10: A POKeMON that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_11: There are so many old tales about them that they're called legendary Pokemon, but there are way more of them around than you'd expect.
flavor_text_12: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.
flavor_text_13: This fleet-footed POKeMON is said to run over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within its body is its source of power.
flavor_text_14: This legendary Chinese POKEMON is considered magnif icent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.
flavor_text_15: A POKeMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
flavor_text_16: A legendary Pokemon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.
flavor_text_17: A POKeMON that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.
flavor_text_18: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
flavor_text_19: ARCANINE is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this POKeMON's body is its source of power.

name: voltorb
flavor_text_0: VOLTORB was first sighted at a company that manufactures POKe BALLS. The link between that sighting and the fact that this POKeMON looks very similar to a POKe BALL remains a mystery.
flavor_text_1: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to SCREECH or suddenly SELFDESTRUCT.
flavor_text_2: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKe BALL, it has zapped many people.
flavor_text_3: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
