flavor_text_4: It bears an uncanny and unexplained resemblance to a POKe BALL. Because it explodes at the slightest shock, even veteran TRAINERS treat it with caution.
flavor_text_5: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poke Ball, it has zapped many people.
flavor_text_6: It was discovered when Poke Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.
flavor_text_7: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.
flavor_text_8: Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poke Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokemon looks very similar to a Poke Ball remains a mystery.
flavor_text_9: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.
flavor_text_10: An enigmatic Pokemon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poke Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.
flavor_text_11: It was discovered when POKe BALLS were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.
flavor_text_12: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKe BALL, they have zapped many people.
flavor_text_13: Voltorb is extremely sensitive--it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a Poke Ball was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.
flavor_text_14: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poke Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.
flavor_text_15: VOLTORB is extremely sensitive - it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a POKe BALL was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.
flavor_text_16: During the study of this POKeMON, it was discovered that its compo nents are not found in nature.
flavor_text_17: It is said to camouflage itself as a POKe BALL. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

name: electrode
flavor_text_0: It is dangerous. If it has too much electricity and has nothing to do, it amuses itself by exploding.
flavor_text_1: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.
flavor_text_2: One of ELECTRODE's characteristics is its attraction to electricity. It is a problematical POKeMON that congregates mostly at electrical power plants to feed on electricity that has just been generated.
flavor_text_3: ELECTRODE eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this POKeMON exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.
flavor_text_4: They appear in great numbers at electric power plants. Because they feed on electricity, they cause massive and chaotic blackouts in nearby cities.
flavor_text_5: It stores an over flowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
flavor_text_6: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokemon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.
flavor_text_7: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
flavor_text_8: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.
flavor_text_9: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."
flavor_text_10: Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokemon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.
flavor_text_11: One of Electrode's characteristics is its attraction to electricity. It is a problematical Pokemon that congregates mostly at electrical power plants to feed on electricity that has just been generated.
flavor_text_12: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.
flavor_text_13: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: typhlosion
flavor_text_0: TYPHLOSION obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This POKeMON creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.
flavor_text_1: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui's center.
flavor_text_2: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
flavor_text_3: When heat from its body causes the air around it to shimmer, this is a sign that it is ready to battle.
flavor_text_4: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.
flavor_text_5: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blaz  ing fur together to cause huge explosions.
flavor_text_6: It can hide behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intense flames. TYPHLOSION create blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.
flavor_text_7: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.
flavor_text_8: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokemon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

name: qwilfish
flavor_text_0: A QWILFISH uses the pressure of water it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming to be somewhat challenging.
flavor_text_1: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokemon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.
flavor_text_2: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
flavor_text_3: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They in ject a toxin that causes fainting.
flavor_text_4: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.
flavor_text_5: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.
flavor_text_6: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokemon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.
flavor_text_7: QWILFISH sucks in water, inflating itself. This POKeMON uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.
flavor_text_8: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent's size.
flavor_text_9: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of  water all at once.

name: sneasel
flavor_text_0: A smart and sneaky Pokemon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.
flavor_text_1: It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.
flavor_text_2: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel's grasp.
flavor_text_3: SNEASEL scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This POKeMON seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.
flavor_text_4: A SNEASEL scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. It seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.
flavor_text_5: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and feasts on the eggs that are left behind.
flavor_text_6: It blends into the dark of night to ambush its prey. Sneasel will attack Sandshrew, but its hard skin can cause Sneasel's claws to snap off.
flavor_text_7: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it sud denly extends the claws and startles its enemy.
flavor_text_8: They will cooperate to steal eggs from the nests of bird Pokemon, but fights break out to determine which one gets to eat the eggs.
flavor_text_9: It feeds on eggs stolen from nests. Its sharply hooked claws rip vulnerable spots on prey.
flavor_text_10: This cunning POKeMON hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.
flavor_text_11: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.
flavor_text_12: Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokemon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.
flavor_text_13: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.
flavor_text_14: It is extremely vicious and will not stop attacking until its foe is incapable of moving.
flavor_text_15: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and scavenges any leftovers it can find.
flavor_text_16: A smart and sneaky Pokemon, it makes its opponents flinch by suddenly showing the claws hidden in its paws.

name: samurott
flavor_text_0: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
flavor_text_1: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.
flavor_text_2: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.
flavor_text_3: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokemon's evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

name: lilligant
flavor_text_0: As soon as it finds a male to be its partner, the beautiful flower on its head darkens, droops, and withers away.
flavor_text_1: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.
flavor_text_2: Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they're also staggeringly expensive.
flavor_text_3: It's well liked by other Pokemon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.
flavor_text_4: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.
flavor_text_5: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokemon is popular with celebrities.
flavor_text_6: It's believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant's head to bloom.
flavor_text_7: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.
flavor_text_8: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
flavor_text_9: The fragrance of its flower differs slightly depending on the soil where it grew up. Sniffing the aroma calms your heart and mind.

name: zorua
flavor_text_0: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.
flavor_text_1: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.
flavor_text_2: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokemon.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon has a cowardly disposition, so when it's not around friends, it basically always stays transformed as something else.
flavor_text_4: Zorua sometimes transforms into a person and goes into cities to search for food. When Zorua does this, it usually takes on the form of a child.
flavor_text_5: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
flavor_text_6: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.
flavor_text_7: Zorua is a timid Pokemon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua's ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

name: zoroark
flavor_text_0: Bonds between these Pokemon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.
flavor_text_2: Seeking to ease the burden of their solitude, lonely Trainers tell Zoroark to show illusions to them.
flavor_text_3: It doesn't just transform itself--it also has the power to make hundreds of people see its illusions.
flavor_text_4: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
flavor_text_5: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.
flavor_text_6: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.
flavor_text_7: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.

name: braviary
flavor_text_0: Because this Pokemon is hotheaded and belligerent, it's Corviknight that's taken the role of transportation in Galar.
flavor_text_1: With its brave disposition, it fears nothing--not even death. Ancient Alolan people respected it, referring to it as "the hero of the sky."
flavor_text_2: Known as "the hero of the skies," this Pokemon is so proud and so brave that it will never retreat, even when it's injured.
flavor_text_3: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokemon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.
flavor_text_4: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.
flavor_text_5: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky  get from their peers.
flavor_text_6: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
flavor_text_7: The more scars it has on its front, the more heroic it's considered to be. Those with many scars on their back are mocked by the flock.
flavor_text_8: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokemon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water's surface.
flavor_text_9: It's thought that people disturbed their habitats in the past, so Braviary banded together to fight back.

name: sliggoo
flavor_text_0: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.
flavor_text_1: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.
flavor_text_2: It crawls along sluggishly. The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with its brain and other organs.
flavor_text_3: It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.
flavor_text_4: Its entire body is covered with gooey mucus that can dissolve anything. Be sure to put gloves on if you're going to touch it.
flavor_text_5: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can't see anything.
flavor_text_6: This Pokemon's mucous can dissolve anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous on its prey. Once they're nicely dissolved, it slurps them up.
flavor_text_7: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.
flavor_text_8: Although this Pokemon isn't very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

name: goodra
flavor_text_0: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokemon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.
flavor_text_1: Underneath its slimy skin is a thick layer of fat, and the combination of the two makes enemies' attacks slide right off.
flavor_text_2: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.
flavor_text_3: An amazingly friendly Pokemon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.
flavor_text_4: It's very friendly toward people. If you grow close to it, Goodra will hug you with its sticky, slime-covered body. Don't get mad.
flavor_text_5: Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.
flavor_text_6: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.
flavor_text_7: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy--it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.
flavor_text_8: It gets picked on because it's meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.

name: avalugg
flavor_text_0: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokemon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.
flavor_text_1: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.
flavor_text_2: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.
flavor_text_3: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokemon's body returns to a pristine state overnight.
flavor_text_4: At high latitudes, this Pokemon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

name: decidueye
flavor_text_0: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.
flavor_text_1: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.
flavor_text_2: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent's weak point before they notice what's happening.
flavor_text_3: Although basically cool and cautious, when it's caught by surprise, it's seized by panic.
flavor_text_4: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye's feathers insulates the Pokemon against Hisui's extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.
flavor_text_5: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can't afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.
flavor_text_6: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.

name: dialga
flavor_text_0: A Pokemon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.
flavor_text_1: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga's heart beats.
flavor_text_2: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
flavor_text_3: This Pokemon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.
flavor_text_5: A Pokemon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when DIALGA was born.
flavor_text_6: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when DIALGA's heart beats.

name: palkia
flavor_text_0: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.
flavor_text_1: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with PALKIA's every breath.
flavor_text_2: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.
flavor_text_3: A legendary Pokemon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia's every breath.
flavor_text_4: This Pokemon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.
flavor_text_5: Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.

name: basculin
flavor_text_0: In the past, it often appeared on the dinner table. The meat of red-striped Basculin is on the fatty side, and it's more popular with the youth.
flavor_text_1: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor--this one is gentle--I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
flavor_text_2: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.
flavor_text_3: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they'll start fighting instantly. These Pokemon are very hostile.
flavor_text_4: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other's school.
flavor_text_5: When a school of Basculin appears in a lake, everything else disappears, except for Corphish and Crawdaunt. That's how violent Basculin are.
flavor_text_6: Savage, violent Pokemon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.
flavor_text_7: Anglers love the fight this Pokemon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch-- many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: basculegion
flavor_text_0: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

name: enamorus
flavor_text_0: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokemon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

name: tauros
flavor_text_0: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.
flavor_text_1: This Pokemon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.
flavor_text_2: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won't allow people to ride on their backs.
flavor_text_3: When it is about to TACKLE, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.
flavor_text_4: Historically, people in areas all over the world have ridden Tauros, but the practice is said to have started in Alola.
flavor_text_5: Although it's known to be a fierce Pokemon, Tauros in the Alola region are said to possess a measure of calmness.
flavor_text_6: When it is about to tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.
flavor_text_7: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it's a warning that the Pokemon is about to charge with astounding speed.
flavor_text_8: It is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for TAUROS to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.
flavor_text_9: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd's protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.
flavor_text_10: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.
flavor_text_11: These violent POKeMON fight with other mem bers of their herd in order to prove their strength.
flavor_text_12: After heightening its will to fight by whipping itself with its three tails, it charges at full speed.
flavor_text_13: The climate seems to be related to the reason Tauros in Alola are a little calmer than those in other regions.
flavor_text_14: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd's protector takes pride in its bat tle-scarred horns.
flavor_text_15: A rowdy POKeMON with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won't stop until it hits something.
flavor_text_16: A rowdy Pokemon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won't stop until it hits something.
flavor_text_17: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.
flavor_text_18: This POKeMON is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for TAUROS to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.

name: wooper
flavor_text_0: This POKeMON lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
flavor_text_1: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
flavor_text_2: A mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it barehanded will cause a shooting pain.
flavor_text_3: WOOPER usually live in water but come out onto land seeking food occasionally. On land, they coat their bodies with a gooey, toxic film.
flavor_text_4: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.
flavor_text_5: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.
flavor_text_6: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.
flavor_text_7: WOOPER usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.
flavor_text_8: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.
flavor_text_9: When it walks a round on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.
flavor_text_10: This Pokemon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
